label: draft PulseNet Canada Salmonella submission standard
definition: The PulseNet Canada Salmonella submission standard details the fields required in a PuseNet Canada pathogen submission report for Salmonella in spreadsheet format

label: draft ReSeq Tuberculosis data platform standard
definition: The Relational Sequencing TB Data Platform (ReSeqTB) catalogs a vast amount of genotypic, phenotypic and related metadata from Mycobacterium tuberculosis (Mtb) strains to enable the development of clinically useful, WHO-endorsed in vitro diagnostic assays for rapid drug susceptibility testing of Mtb.

label: draft antibiogram drug test model
definition: This is the minimal set of parameters for drug test results for a particular antimicrobial agent.

label: draft isolate whole genome sequencing model
draft pathogenic epidemiology case investigation record
definition: This is a model of the datums involved in an epidemiology investigation.

label: draft sequence repository contextual data standard
definition: This draft specification provides a collection of fields related to the contextual data of a specimen, its genomic sequencing, and its pathogenic epidemiology.

label: draft tuberculosis - specimen contextual data standard
definition: The tuberculosis draft standard is a GenEpiO set of draft genomic and clinical data items related to Mycobacterium tuberculosis that various agencies are using in their own reporting.

label: draft tuberculosis contextual data standard
definition: The draft tuberculosis contextual data standard is a data standard for the collection of contextual information of a given tuberculosis case that pertain to typing, clinical treatment, and potential research questions.

label: draft whole genome sequencing lab test record
definition: This is a set of datums involved in laboratory processing of whole-genome-sequenced isolates.

label: NCBI Antibiogram standard
definition: The NCBI antibiogram standard details the reporting specifications for antimicrobial susceptibility and resistance data derived from drug resistant pathogens. This information is submitted as an antibiogram table on BioSample records.

label: NCBI BioProject standard
definition: The National Center for Biotechnology Information BioProject standard is a collection of datums that describe biological data related to a single initiative, originating from a single organization or from a consortium.  A BioProject record provides users a single place to find links to the diverse data types generated for that project.

label: NCBI BioSample Pathogen.cl standard
definition: A National Center for Biotechnology Information BioSample specification defines fields and terms that provide "descriptions of biological source materials used in experimental assays".

label: NCBI SRA meta information standard
definition: An NCBI SRA meta information item is a field specification for a NCBI Sequence Read Archive record.

label: travel end date
definition: The date of a person's return to some residence from a journey originating at that residence.

label: travel start date
definition: The date of a person's departure from their primary residence (at that time) on a journey to one or more other locations.

label: epi contact network model - animal
definition: This is a model that provides location and transportation information about an animal that may be involved in transmitting a pathogen to a human or other animal.

label: epi contact network model - human
definition: An epi contact network - human is contact information about a person who may be involved in transmitting a pathogen.

label: East Midlands Region
definition: One of the regions of England and consists of most of the eastern half of the traditional region of the Midlands. It encompasses the combined area of Derbyshire, Leicestershire, Rutland, Northamptonshire, Nottinghamshire and most of Lincolnshire.

label: East Region
definition: One of the nine official regions of England. It includes the ceremonial counties of Essex, Hertfordshire, Bedfordshire, Cambridgeshire, Norfolk and Suffolk.

label: Greater London Region
definition: The top-level administrative subdivision covering London, England.

label: North East Region
definition: One of the nine official regions of England and comprises the combined area of Northumberland, County Durham, Tyne and Wear, part of North Yorkshire and Tees Valley.

label: North West Region
definition: One of the nine official regions of England. It comprises five counties of England, Cumbria, Lancashire, Greater Manchester, Merseyside and Cheshire.

label: South East Region
definition: One of the nine official regions of England. Its boundaries include Berkshire, Buckinghamshire, East Sussex, Hampshire, Isle of Wight, Kent, Oxfordshire, Surrey and West Sussex.

label: South West Region
definition: One of the regions of England. It extends from Gloucestershire and Wiltshire to Cornwall and the Isles of Scilly. This includes the area often known as the West Country, and much of Wessex.

label: West Midlands Region
definition: An official region of England, covering the western half of the area traditionally known as the Midlands. It contains the second most populated British city, Birmingham, and the larger West Midlands conurbation, which includes the city of Wolverhampton and large towns of Dudley, Solihull, Walsall and West Bromwich. The city of Coventry is also located within the West Midlands county, but is separated from the conurbation to the west by several miles of green belt.

label: Yorkshire and the Humber
definition: One of the nine government office regions of England. It covers most of the historic county of Yorkshire, along with the part of northern Lincolnshire that was, from 1974 to 1996, within the former shire county of Humberside.

label: assembly project
definition: Genome assembly project utilizing already existing sequence data including data that was submitted by a different group

label: clone ends project
definition: a sequencing project involving clone-ends

label: epigenomics project
definition: A sequencing project involving DNA methylation, histone modification, and/or chromatin accessibility datasets

label: exome resequencing project
definition: exome resequencing project

label: genome sequencing project
definition: A whole, or partial, genome sequencing project (with or without a genome assembly)

label: map project
definition: Map: - project that results in non-sequence map data such as genetic map, radiation hybrid map, cytogenetic map, optical map, and etc.

label: metagenome assembly project
definition: Metagenome assembly: a genome assembly generated from sequenced environmental samples

label: metagenome project
definition: Metagenome: sequence analysis of environmental samples

label: other project data type
definition: Other: a free text description is provided to indicate Other data type

label: phenotype or genotype project
definition: Phenotype or Genotype: project correlating phenotype and genotype

label: proteome project
definition: Proteome: large scale proteomics experiment including mass spec. analysis

label: random survey project
definition: Random Survey: sequence generated from a random sampling of the collected sample; not intended to be comprehensive sampling of the material.

label: targeted locus (loci) project
definition: Targeted locus (loci): project to sequence specific loci, such as a 16S rRNA sequencing

label: transcriptome or gene expression
definition: Transcriptome or Gene expression: large scale RNA sequencing or expression analysis. Includes cDNA, EST, RNA_seq, and microarray.

label: variation project
definition: A sequencing project with a primary goal of identifying large or small sequence variation across populations.

label: less than
definition: The "less than" comparator indicates that a given substance was present at less than a given quantity or concentration.

label: less than or equal to
definition: The "less than or equal to" comparator indicates that a given substance was present at less than or equal to a given quantity or concentration.

label: equal to
definition: The "equal to" comparator indicates that a given substance was present at the given quantity or concentration.

label: greater than
definition: The "less than or equal to" comparator indicates that a given substance was present at less than or equal to a given quantity or concentration.

label: greater than or equal to
definition: The "greater than or equal to" comparator indicates that a given substance was present at greater than or equal to a given quantity or concentration.

label: treatment end date
definition: A treatment end date is a date/time datum which indicates the end of a particular medical treatment for a patient.

label: treatment start date
definition: A treatment start date is a date/time datum which indicates the start of a particular medical treatment for a patient.

label: second line or reserve tuberculosis drug
immigration year of arrival
definition: A time measurement datum indicating the year a person immigrated to a given country.

label: travel history item
definition: A datetime measurement related to a person's travel with respect to potential epidemilogical implications.

label: animal exposure event - contact or activity
number of passages
definition: The number of serial iterations that an isolate is grown in one environment.

label: passage protocol
definition: A passage protocol should detail the number of serial iterations that an isolate is grown in one environment, and the conditions of that environment.

label: infection aquired during travel
definition: Infection aquired during travel is a boolean datum indicating a diagnosis of a traveller's infection during a given trip.

label: travel destination
definition: A travel destination is a destination city (or populated place of some scale) which a given human has travelled to on a particular trip.

label: travel mode
definition: A travel mode is a type of transportation which a given human has used while travelling on a particular trip.

label: travel reason
definition: A travel reason is a motivation for traveling on a particular trip expressed by the traveller.

label: Birth Date
definition: The calendar date on which a person was born.

label: Date of Death
definition: The calendar date of subject's death.

label: Age Group
definition: Subgroups of populations based on age.

label: Pregnant
definition: Observed to be or have been pregnant.

label: Pregnant During the Study
definition: An indicator as to whether the female subject is pregnant during the study period.

label: body weights and measures
definition: Measurements of the height, weight, length, area, etc., of the human and animal body or its parts.

label: Mycobacterium tuberculosis lineage
definition: A Mycobacterium tuberculosis lineage is a named family of strains of tuberculosis, named usually with reference to their shared geographic origin.

label: specimen organism taxonomy (species)
definition: This is the taxonomic species descriptor of a specimen isolate (an organism found within a specimen.)

label: subject age - unit
definition: Age unit of the age measurement of a subject (individual organism).

label: virulence factor name
definition: The name of the virulence factor molecule produced by a pathogen that specifically causes disease, or that influences the host's function to allow the pathogen to thrive.

label: virulence testing protocol name
definition: The laboratory protocol used to determine virulence phenotypes and markers.

label: commensal role
definition: An organism and its host share physical space but no evidence exists to determine if one benefits from this arrangement.

label: symbiotic role
definition: Organism has a symbiotic relationship with host

label: person role
definition: a role which inheres in a person and is realized by the process of being in the context of civilization

label: genus of pathogen
definition: This is the genus-level taxonomic name of an organism playing a pathogen role

label: species of pathogen
definition: This is the species-level taxonomic name of an organism playing a pathogen role

label: Vaccination
definition: Administration of vaccines to stimulate the host's immune response. This includes any preparation intended for active immunological prophylaxis or treatment.

label: comorbidity
definition: A diagnosis that is the outcome of a diagnostic process targeting a second or additional health problem.

label: outcome of pregnancy associated with illness
pregnancy
definition: The status during which female mammals carry their developing young (EMBRYOS or FETUSES) in utero before birth, beginning from FERTILIZATION to BIRTH.

label: neonate
definition: A newborn child; especially: a child less than a month old.

label: infectious disease treatment
definition: A course of treatment designed to resolve an infectious disease

label: subject health status at time of specimen extraction
definition: Health or disease status of a given subject at time of specimen extraction.

label: disease cluster notification agency
definition: An agency that has reported a disease cluster.

label: exposure event location
definition: An epi case physical location type is a type of built structure that is suspected to be related to an outbreak investigation.

label: human exposure event - travel datum
definition: an epidemiology travel datum is a datum regarding a particular human's travel trip destination, mode, and motivation, with respect to an epidemiology investigation.

label: infectious disease exposure source
definition: Ingestion from contact with ...

label: animal specimen
definition: A specimen extracted from an animal

label: infection-specific food details
definition: Some bacteria are associated with particular foods.  Need relationship

label: Animal Model
definition: An animal that is amenable to experimentation and whose physiological or pathologic mechanisms are sufficiently similar to those of a human for the animal to serve as a model.

label: animal - laboratory
definition: no definition at source

label: animal - pet
definition: Animals kept by humans for companionship and enjoyment, as opposed to DOMESTIC ANIMALS such as livestock or farm animals, which are kept for economic reasons.

label: animal - wild
definition: Animals considered to be wild or feral or not adapted for domestic use. It does not include wild animals in zoos for which ANIMALS, ZOO is available.

label: livestock
definition: Domesticated farm animals raised for home use or profit but excluding POULTRY. Typically livestock includes CATTLE; SHEEP; HORSES; SWINE; GOATS; and others.

label: physician role
definition: A health care role borne by a human being and realized by promoting, maintaining or restoring human health through the study, diagnosis, and treatment of disease, injury and other physical and mental impairments.

label: symptom cessation date
definition: A symptom cessation date is a date-time entity that marks the end of one or more reported symptoms pertaining to an episode of human or animal illness

label: symptom duration
definition: A symptom duration is a date-time entity which is the duration (in hours or days or weeks etc.) that one or more symptoms persist for in a particular human or animal

label: symptom onset date
definition: A symptom onset date is a date-time entity that marks the start of one or more reported symptoms pertaining to an episode of human or animal illness

label: contact specification
definition: This is a collection of various human (and animal contact location) contact information specifications used in data standards.

label: draft WGS lab assembly quality metrics record
draft WGS lab bioinformatics process record
draft WGS lab sequencing quality metrics record
draft pathogenic epi case exposure record
definition: The draft epi case exposure model describes datums related to the possible transmission of a pathogen between a case person and other people, places, animals etc.

label: draft pathogenic epi case food record
definition: A description of a food item that a case patient has come in contact with.

label: draft pathogenic epi case general information record
definition: An epi case general info model contains datum specifications about an epidemiology investigation case including the person involved, contact information and their demographics.

label: draft pathogenic epi case isolate detail record
definition: A record of the details around how, when, and from what an isolate was extracted.

label: draft pathogenic epi case test record
definition: A laboratory test performed on a specimen from a patient with regard to potential pathogenic disease.

label: draft pathogenic epi case travel record
definition: A record of a patient's recent travel - departure and return, mode of travel and locations visited - as it may pertain to an outbreak pathogen transmission event.

label: draft sequence repository data - antibiogram
definition: A dataset of the minimal inhibitory concentrations (value, unit, sign (<,>, =)) and resistance phenotypes (resistant, sensitive or undetermined) of the sequenced isolate against different antibiotics tested.

label: draft sequence repository data - antibiogram MIC measurement
definition: This is a component of an antibiogram that enables a choice of MIC measurements based on either the diffusion or dilution method. These methods call for different numeric input ranges and units.

label: draft sequence repository data - food specimen
definition: This specification offers food source, product type, packaging and processing attributes relevant to describing a food specimen.

label: draft sequence repository data - geographic location
definition: The geographical origin of the sample by city, region, country or latitude and logitude.

label: draft sequence repository data - isolate passage history
draft sequence repository data - sequencing quality control
definition: Measurements or calculated quantities used to assess the extent and success of the sequence assembly process. Metric thresholds are species-specific.

label: draft sequence repository data - specimen collection
draft sequence repository data - submission to EBI
draft sequence repository data - submission to NCBI/DDBJ
draft sequence repository data - virulence
definition: The virulence factors determined to be present in the sequenced isolate by phenotypic or target amplification methods e.g. Shiga toxins, hemolysins.

label: draft travel log specification
definition: This record details a person's travel movement and duration for epidemiological analysis.

label: draft tuberculosis - dataset features and provenance
drug MIC unit specification
definition: The unit provided for an antibiotic drug test dosage.

label: food specimen specification
definition: A food specimen type is a categorization of a food specimen, by the organism it is or came from, or by a class of food products.

label: raw sequence data processing datum
definition: The procedures used to remove adapters from raw sequence reads, trim low quality bases and where applicable, merge paired-end reads.

label: specimen extraction site - geographic feature
definition: A landform, biome or built environment at site that a given specimen was extracted or collected from.

label: specimen source substance specification
definition: A specimen source substance is an organism substance or food product or environmental substance from which the specimen was extracted.

label: specimen strain or isolate identifier
definition: Name of strain from which sample was obtained OR name of isolate from which sample was obtained.

label: specimen collection time measurement datum
definition: A time measurement datum that is the measure of the time when the specimens are collected.

label: 16S rRNA sequencing
definition: 16S ribosomal RNA sequencing is a sequencing method used to identify and compare bacteria present within a given sample. 16S rRNA gene sequencing is a well-established method for studying phylogeny and taxonomy of samples from complex microbiomes or environments that are difficult or impossible to study.

label: AccuProbe test results
definition: AccuProbe results

label: Accuprobe Listeria monocytogenes Culture Identification Reagent Kit
definition: Nucleic acid hybridization tests are based on the ability of complementary nucleic acid strands to specifically align and associate to form stable double-stranded complexes (6). The ACCUPROBE method uses a single-stranded DNA probe with a chemiluminescent label that is complementary to the ribosomal RNA of the target organism. After the ribosomal RNA is released from the target organism, the labeled DNA probe combines with the target organism’s ribosomal RNA to form a stable DNA:RNA hybrid. The Selection Reagent allows for the differentiation of non-hybridized and hybridized probes.The light signal emitted by the DNA:RNA hybrids is measured by a GEN-PROBE luminometer. A positive result is a luminometer reading equal to or greater than the cut-off. A value below this cut-off is the negative result.

label: DuPont identification pattern library
definition: a library of RiboPrinter recognised patterns

label: MLST sequence type
definition: Multilocus sequence typing (MLST) is a technique in molecular biology for the typing of multiple loci. The procedure characterizes isolates of microbial species using the DNA sequences of internal fragments of multiple housekeeping genes. For each housekeeping gene, the different sequences present within a bacterial species are assigned as distinct alleles and, for each isolate, the alleles at each of the loci define the allelic profile or sequence type (ST).

label: Qualicon (DuPont) RiboPrinter Microbial Characterization System
definition: an automated system that takes a purified bacterial suspension, lyses the cells, extracts the DNA, restriction endonuclease digests the DNA, separates the digest on a gel, transfers the DNA bands to a membrane, probes the bands with non-radioisotope-labeled, 5S-16S-23S rRNA-specific probes (Southern hybridization), photographs the membrane, and finally compares the bar code-like pattern to databases in order to identify the genus and species.

label: RiboPrinter DUP Number
definition: DuPont identification number from the DuPont identification library

label: RiboPrinter DUP similarity
definition: Similarity of pattern to one of the patterns of the DuPont Identification library of the RiboPrinter

label: Shiga Toxin
definition: A bacterial toxin produced by Shigella dysenteriae and by some strains of E. coli that inhibits protein synthesis by blocking the interaction of ribosomal RNA with peptide elongation factors.  The non-catalytic beta subunit of Shiga toxin may be useful as a fusion vector for induction of antigen-specific cytotoxic T lymphocyte responses.

label: riboprinting
definition: This method is based on restriction endonuclease digestion of bacterial chromosomal DNA, followed by Southern hybridization to probes for sequences in the regions of bacterial DNA coding for the 5S-16S-23S (the Escherichia coli rrnB rRNA operon) rRNA operon. The probes have been developed that are directed to highly conserved regions of the rRNA operon present in all eubacteria and can therefore be used for ribotyping most bacteria

label: ribotyping
definition: Ribotyping involves the fingerprinting of genomic DNA restriction fragments that contain all or part of the genes coding for the 16S and 23S rRNA. By digesting the genes with a specific restriction enzyme, fragments of different lengths are generated. By performing a Gel electrophoresis with the digested samples, the fragments can be visualised as lines on the gel, where larger fragments are close to the start of the gel, and smaller fragments further down. After blotting onto a matrix and probing, these lines form a unique pattern for each species and can be used to identify the origin of the DNA, almost like a barcode can identify a product.

label: Bacterial 16S RNA
definition: The RNA component of the small (30S) subunit of prokaryotic ribosomes.

label: genome annotation algorithm
definition: Program used for annotation

label: genome annotation source
definition: For cases where annotation was provided by a community jamboree or model organism database rather than by a specific submitter

label: assembly method
definition: Assembly method refers to how the reads were assembled into contigs for which either a de novo or mapping (reference based) strategy is used.

label: contig
definition: A contiguous sequence derived from sequence assembly. Has no gaps, but may contain N's from unavailable bases.

label: contig_collection
definition: A collection of contigs.

label: assembly and annotation project objective
definition: The assembly and annotation objective is the set of objectives that assembly and annotation techniques (including instruments and software platforms) applied to a sample are meant to satisfy.  This impacts on the quality control thresholds applied to the sequencing project.

label: assembly name (identifier)
definition: Name/version of the assembly provided by the submitter that is used in the genome browsers and in the community

label: assembly quality control datum
definition: A single datum having to do with a metric for genomic sequence assembly quality control.    A "quality control measurement" can be defined as a measurement that has some norm within a definable context, e.g. for a certain subspecies.  It may be a calculated quantity.  A "quality control metric" is an upper or lower bound threshold that a measurement is compared to.  Surpassing the threshold may indicate an error situation.  A "measure" can indicate an amount of activity, consumption, transformation, etc. but doesn't itself convey an over-stepping of bounds in the way that a metric does.

label: reference genome identifier
definition: Identifier for a reference genome (used to build or compare an assembly)  that is used in the genome browsers and in the community

label: reference_genome
definition: A collection of sequences (often chromosomes) taken as the standard for a given organism and genome assembly.

label: sequence_assembly
definition: A sequence of nucleotides that has been algorithmically derived from an alignment of two or more different sequences.

label: British Columbia PHN number
definition: A British Columbia Patient Health Number (PHN) is is a patient identifier used within the British Columbia (Canada) provincial health care system.

label: Canadian federal lab strain ID
definition: A Canadian federal lab strain ID is a tracking identifier number assigned by a Federal Government of Canada laboratory for an isolate.

label: genome
definition: A genome is the sum of genetic material within a cell or virion.

label: pathological entity
definition: Pathological structure or process

label: sequence_collection
definition: A collection of discontinuous sequences.

label: individual treatment control strategy
definition: An infectious disease control strategy that immediately targets individuals.

label: infection acquisition through sexual activity with infectious host
definition: An infection acquistion from infectious host that is causally downstream of some potentially infectious sexual contacting

label: other (metadata value)
definition: other (metadata choice) indicates that for the given categorical variable, a respondent has chosen an other or additional response not listed.

label: personal health datum
definition: A personal health datum is a datum that pertains to the health situation or history of an individual.

label: simulation of population
definition: A simulation of the aggregate of organisms that are members of the population participating in a simulator.

label: specimen datum
definition: This is a catch-all category for listing specimen related terms

label: specimen food source or product datum
definition: A food source or product datum is a particular attribute (feature, quality or process history) of the food sample that an organism was found on or in.

label: transmission probability
definition: The probability of the occurence of an infection acquisition from one infected organism to another when in contact.

label: Undetermined
definition: A term referring to the lack of definitive clinical or pathologic criteria for a tumor to predict its clinical course or to classify it as benign or malignant.

label: human social gathering activity
definition: A type of social behavior in which a collection of humans intentionally gathers together on a temporary basis to engage socially.

label: exposure event end
definition: A date-time datum that marks the end of possible human or animal exposure to a pathogen agent, directly or indirectly.

label: exposure event start
definition: A date-time datum that marks the start of a human or animal exposure event to a suspected pathogen agent, directly or indirectly.

label: predicted exposure end
definition: A date-time datum that marks the predicted end of possible human or animal exposure to a pathogen agent, directly or indirectly, based on a suspected pathogen and first symptom date-time.

label: predicted exposure start
definition: A date-time datum that marks the predicted start of possible human or animal exposure to a pathogen agent, directly or indirectly, based on a suspected pathogen and first symptom date-time.

label: culture frozen date
definition: A culture frozen date is a date-time entity marking the beginning of a process in which a sample culture is frozen for preservation.

label: culture isolation date
definition: A culture isolation date is a date-time entity marking the end of a process in which a sample is isolated as a single colony or non-mixture culture

label: isolate received date
definition: date lab received isolate

label: isolate upload date
definition: date the isolate was entered into the database

label: sequencing run date
definition: date the sequencing run was performed

label: upload modified date
definition: Date an uploaded sample was re-uploaded or had its metadata modified.

label: notification date
definition: A notification date is the date that an outbreak is suspected by a laboratory or other agency and is reported per outbreak detection guidelines.

label: outbreak date
definition: An outbreak date is on which disease onset appears to have occured

label: outbreak over
definition: An outbreak over date is the date on which a disease outbreak appears to have abated

label: food cultural origin
definition: A food cultural origin datum indicates the cultural origin of a food product.

label: experimental subject role
definition: A role that inheres in a material that is input as the subject of interest in a scientific technique - either as an entity about which data is generated in an assay or study, or an entity that is transformed or modified in a material processing technique (e.g. the source from which a biological sample is taken)

label: contact role
definition: A person associated with another person or organization.

label: exposed person role
definition: An exposed person role is the role a person takes on who has been exposed to a pathogen.  In serious situations this may call for special treatment, e.g. quarantine.

label: Primary
definition: Occurring first in time or sequence; original; of greatest rank or importance or value.

label: Secondary
definition: Derived as a result of a primary condition; not direct or immediate; of second rank or importance or value.

label: number of expected base pairs per genome
definition: The estimated size of the genome prior to sequencing. Of particular importance in the sequencing of (eukaryotic) genome which could remain in draft form for a long or unspecified period.

label: number of reads passing filter
definition: Raw data are filtered to remove any reads that do not meet the overall quality as measured by a chastity filter. The chastity of a base call is calculated as the ratio of the brightest intensity divided by the sum of the brightest and second brightest intensities. Clusters passing filter are represented by PF in analysis reports. Clusters pass filter if no more than one base call in the first 25 cycles has a chastity of < 0.6.

label: phred quality score
definition: percentage of reads with a Phred quality score over 30, which indicates less than a 1/1000 chance that the base was called incorrectly

label: read coverage
definition: Coverage (read depth or depth) is the average number of reads representing a given nucleotide in the reconstructed sequence.

label: assembly genome size
definition: The assembly genome size is the sum of all lengths of a sequence assembly's contigs.

label: assembly status
definition: Attempting to convey the relative integrity and reliability of the data, six levels or terms have been proposed and applied to describe genome sequences.   See subclass choices.

label: base composition
definition: the relative amounts of the purines and pyrimidines in a nucleic acid.

label: breadth of coverage
definition: The breadth of coverage is the percentage of the genome that was sequenced to a prescribed depth of coverage.

label: contig count
definition: A contig count is the count of contigs that belong to a sequence assembly.

label: contig length
definition: A contig length is the count of base pairs in a given sequence assembly contig.

label: genome size delta ratio
definition: The 'genome size delta ratio' is a ratio of the difference between a sample's genome assembly size and the size of a given reference genome, over the reference genome size.   The formula:  | (reference_genome_size - assembly_genome_size) | / reference_genome_size  This yeilds a decimal / percentage ranging from 0 = exact length, to say .1 which is equivalent to a 10% variance.  If the ratio is too far from a quality control ratio that depends on the species in question, this indicates a bad assembly or a mis-identified sample.

label: genome size delta ratio QC threshold
definition: This is the upper acceptable limit of the 'genome size delta ratio' with respect to a particular species.  For Salmonella a 0.10 variance in length between an assembly size and a reference genome size may be acceptable.  For E-coli a more generous 0.30 or .40 variance should be allowed, given the pathogenic subspecies’ highly dynamic genome.

label: mean contig length
definition: The mean contig length is the count of base pairs in the average size contig of the sequence assembly.

label: contact specification - epi network contact
definition: An epi network contact is a person who may have recieved or transmitted an infectious disease related to an outbreak investigation.

label: contact specification - lab test requester
definition: A lab test requestor is the individual or agency requesting that one or more tests be performed on a specimen.

label: curator organization name
definition: The curator organization name is the name of an organization that manages a given repository of entities (samples, isolates, sequences ...)

label: identifier status
definition: An identifier status describes the principle role of an identifier assigned to an entity by its curator or handler. An entity may have a number of identifiers assigned to it over time.  An identifier may be phased-out as can happen when its content is transferred to another curator.

label: subject age at time of specimen collection
definition: A subject age at time of specimen extraction is the age (since birth) of the organism at the time a given specimen was extracted.

label: draft NCBI BioSample geo_loc_name model
definition: Geographical origin of the sample; use the appropriate name from this list http://www.insdc.org/documents/country-qualifier-vocabulary. Use a colon to separate the country or ocean from more detailed information about the location, eg "Canada: Vancouver" or "Germany: halfway down Zugspitze, Alps"

label: draft NCBI BioSample model - mixed clinical and environmental/food/other
draft NCBI isolate source location model
in process
definition: 'In process' is a categorical choice recorded while the data for a given measurable datum has not finished being collected, is awaiting a conclusion, or has not yet been communicated.

label: not collected
definition: 'Not collected' is a categorical choice recorded when a datum was not measured with respect to some entity during some process.

label: restricted access
definition: 'restricted access' is a categorical choice recorded when the data for a given measurable datum is available but not shared publicly because of information privacy concerns.

label: Turbidity Measurement
definition: The determination of the opacity of a sample.

label: bacteria density
definition: number of bacteria in sample

label: conductivity measurement datum
definition: electrical conductivity of water

label: dissolved oxygen concentration
definition: concentration of dissolved oxygen

label: nitrate concentration
definition: concentration of nitrate

label: nitrite concentration
definition: concentration of nitrite

label: redox potential
definition: redox potential, measured relative to a hydrogen cell, indicating oxidation or reduction potential

label: seasonal environment
definition: A plant treatment (EO:0001001) involving an exposure to a given conditions of regional seasons.

label: stream order categorical measurement datum
definition: Stream order is a measure of the relative size of streams (The smallest tributaries are referred to as first-order streams, while the largest river in the world, the Amazon, is a twelfth-order waterway).

label: total phosphorous concentration
definition: total phosphorus concentration, calculated by: total phosphorus = total dissolved phosphorus + particulate phosphorus. Can also be measured without filtering, reported as phosphorus

label: collection depth datum
definition: Please refer to the definitions of depth in the environmental packages

label: pH measurement
definition: In chemistry, pH is a numeric scale used to specify the acidity or basicity(alkalinity) of an aqueous solution

label: specimen collection site land use
definition: Human use of land involving the management and modification of natural environment or wilderness into built environment.

label: contig N50
definition: N50 statistic computed for the contigs produced by the assembly process. A contig N50 is calculated by first ordering every contig by length from longest to shortest. Next, starting from the longest contig, the lengths of each contig are summed, until this running sum equals one-half of the total length of all contigs in the assembly. The contig N50 of the assembly is the length of the shortest contig in this list.

label: contig N50 length QC threshold
definition: The contig N50 length QC threshold is a minimum length threshold that a contig N50 length datum should be above for good QC.  A lower length is indicative of assembly problems (insufficient read depth) or a mismatched reference genome.

label: contig N99
definition: The N99 length definition is identical to the N50 definition except that the threshold for determining the contigs is 1% of the nucleotides.  This contig basepair length can be compared to a minimum threshold to determine if gene annotation (where contigs greater than say 2000bp are necessary) would generally succeed.

label: contig N99 length QC threshold
definition: The contig N99 length QC threshold is the minimum length that a contig N99 or NG99 length datum can be for satisfactory QC.  This threshold avoids having too many gene coding regions prematurely clipped inside short contigs.  An assembly having 1% or more of its content in less than 2Kbp chunks is cause for concern. Bacterial genes are generally about 1Kbp in length.

label: contig NG50
definition: The NG50 length is the same as the N50 length except that the length of the reference genome is used in the calculation rather than the assembly genome size.

label: contig NG99
definition: The NG99 length is the same as the N99 length except that the length of the reference genome is used in the calculation rather than the sum of assembly contig lengths.

label: contig length QC threshold
definition: A 'contig length QC threshold' is an integer setting which can be applied by an algorithm to an array of assembly and annotation contig lengths to remove (filter out) all items less than the threshold value.  The reduced array is used for calculation of statistics.

label: bodily fluid
definition: Liquid components of living organisms. includes fluids that are excreted or secreted from the body as well as body water that normally is not.

label: egg yolk
definition: The yellow spheroidal mass of stored food that forms the inner portion of the egg of a bird or reptile and is surrounded by the white.

label: excreta
definition: A portion of organism substance that is the product of an excretion process that will be eliminated from the body. An excretion process is elimination by an organism of the waste products that arise as a result of metabolic activity

label: down feather
definition: A feather lacking a vane and having a rudimentary rachis and a tuft of non-interlocked barbs with elongated barbules extending from the calamus

label: original submission
definition: An identifier used in the initial submission of content to a repository.

label: previous (archaic) identifier
definition: An identifier that had been used previously but is no longer promoted.

label: data aggregated
definition: The 'data aggregated' role between a user and given data entails that the user is authorized to see aggregated results (like the patient count) via preset reports, queries or views.  The results are not obfuscated.

label: data obfuscated
definition: The 'data obfuscated' role between a user and given data entails that the user is authorized to see particular fields that have been transformed consistently such that statistics performed on those fields would yeild the same results as statistics applied to the un-obfuscated data. The purpose of obfuscation is to prevent related individuals or commercial organizations from being identified.  Aggregated results are by nature obfuscated (example: patient count).

label: data protected
definition: A 'data protected' role between a user and given data entails that a user must be authorized in order to view that data.

label: de-identified data
definition: A 'de-identified data' role between a user and given data entails that the user is authorized to see only those fields (including those that are encrypted) which do not contain information that could be use to identify particular individuals (whether patients or medical practitioners) or potentially organizations in the case where an investigation may implicate them.

label: limited data set
definition: A 'limited data set' role between a user and given data entails that a user is authorized to see some of the fields but the remainder are withheld (or encrypted).

label: latitude coordinate measurement datum
definition: A measurement datum that is the measure of the latitude coordinate of a site.

label: longitude coordinate measurement datum
definition: A measurement datum that is the measure of the longitude coordinate of a site.

label: IRIDA case ID
definition: An IRIDA case ID is a tracking identifier for a case used in the IRIDA.ca software system.  It is used to cross-reference anonymized IDs

label: INSDC country qualifier
definition: The INSDC country qualifier is a textual controlled vocabulary used to indicate the country of origin of a DNA sample.  It can also have the following format: country:sub_region, such as: "Canada:Vancouver".

label: gestation
definition: The state of a female and/or her offspring, and the processes which occur, during the period from conception to birth or termination of the pregnancy.

label: library preparation kit
definition: Packaged kits (containing adapters, indexes, enzymes, buffers etc), tailored for specific sequencing workflows, which allow the simplified preparation of sequencing-ready libraries for small genomes, amplicons, and plasmids.

label: read length
definition: number of base pairs per read

label: sequencer flow cell cluster density
definition: Cluster Generation is a process by which libraries amplified into clonal clusters on a flow cell. The density of those clusters in the lane, is the cluster density.

label: sequencing kit version
definition: The version is the configuration of the reagent cartidge.

label: sequencing location
definition: location the sequencing run was performed

label: sequencing workflow
definition: the workflow is the pre-defined sequence of steps to run the automated sequencing pipeline.

label: adapter sequence
definition: Adapters provide priming sequences for both amplification and sequencing of the sample-library fragments. Both adapters should be reported; in uppercase letters

label: email address of sequencing facility contact person
definition: An email address of the contact representative at the sequencing facility

label: isolate passage history datum
definition: An isolate passage history is a record of the cyclic growth process that led to it, including number of times its was put through the process, and the method used.

label: isolate raw read filename
definition: An isolate raw read filename is the file name (http://edamontology.org/data_1050) of the raw read file created by a genomic sequencing assay.

label: isolate sequence filename
definition: An isolate sequence filename is the file name (http://edamontology.org/data_1050) of the contig assembly file created by a bioinformatics assembly process.

label: library construction protocol
definition: Free form text describing the protocol by which the sequencing library was constructed.

label: library name
definition: The submitter's name for this library.

label: library preparation kit version
definition: The version identifier of a packaged kit tailored for specific sequencing workflows.

label: library selection
definition: Whether any method was used to select for or against, enrich, or screen the material being sequenced.

label: library source
definition: The library source specifies the type of source material that is being sequenced.

label: library strategy
definition: Sequencing technique intended for this library.

label: read adapter trimming
definition: the removal of adapter sequences from demultiplexed data reads

label: read adapter trimming software
definition: The name and version of the software product used for removal of adapter sequences from demultiplexed data reads

label: read paired-end merging software
definition: The name and version of the software used to merge paired-end reads before assembly.

label: read trimming and filtering software
definition: The name and version of software used in a bioinformatics workflow to improve the quality of sequencing reads.

label: sequence number
definition: A sequence number is a numeric identifier of a sequence with respect to a particular data table or dataset.

label: sequencing application
definition: the sequencing application is the use or purpose of the sequencing

label: sequencing assay
definition: the sequencing conditions and the analyte being measured

label: sequencing chemistry
definition: lab method to determine the order of nucleotides in a DNA molecule

label: sequencing count of chemistry cycles
definition: number of sequencing chemistry cycles

label: sequencing dna extraction method
definition: The procedure used to obtain genomic DNA from a sample through chemical, physical or mechanical means.

label: sequencing facility contact person
definition: A person who is the contact representative at the sequencing facility

label: sequencing instrument model
definition: A product name and model number of a manufacturer's genomic (dna) sequencer.

label: sequencing kit
definition: Pre-filled, ready-to-use reagent cartridges. Used to produce improved chemistry, cluster density and read length as well as improve quality (Q) scores. Reagent components are encoded to interact with the sequencing system to validate compatibility with user-defined applications.

label: sequencing platform (brand)
definition: A sequencing plaform (brand) is a name of a company that produces sequencer equipment.

label: sequencing run multiplex identifiers
definition: Molecular barcodes, called Multiplex Identifiers (MIDs), that are used to specifically tag unique samples in a sequencing run. Sequence should be reported in uppercase letters

label: CGF type
definition: output of CGF

label: MLST clonal complex
definition: Multilocus sequence typing (MLST) is a technique in molecular biology for the typing of multiple loci. The procedure characterizes isolates of microbial species using the DNA sequences of internal fragments of multiple housekeeping genes. Sequence types are grouped into clonal complexes by their similarity to a central allelic profile (genotype). As such, clonal complexes represent sequence types that share a number of identical alleles e.g. 5/7

label: genotype
definition: A genotype is a variant genome, complete or incomplete.

label: serotype phenotype
definition: A microbial phenotype that is distinguished by the presence a specific surface antigen.

label: MIRU24 - Canadian standard
definition: The MIRU24 - Canadian standard is a Mycobacterium tuberculosis typing method exactly like MIRU24 - international standard except that the report of the ordering of the matching loci is different.

label: MIRU24 - international standard
definition: The MIRU24 - international standard is a mycobacterial interspersed repetitive units (MIRU) typing method that classifies Mycobacterium tuberculosis complex (MBTC) bacteria according to a multiple locus VNTR [variable number of tandem repeats] analysis (MLVA) typing scheme of counts of repeats at 24 sequence loci.

label: antigenic formula
definition: An antigenic formula is a string composed of codes representing categorized results of tests performed on various viral, bacterial or immune cell surface antigens.

label: cluster identifier
definition: A cluster identifier is an identifier that locates a genomic variant of an organism within a community of past or present genetically related organisms.

label: phage type specification
definition: An integer and character referring to a pattern of opaque or confluent lysis caused by a panel of bacteriophage infections e.g. 14a.

label: serovar/serotype common name
definition: A serotype or serovar is a distinct variation within a species of bacteria or virus or among immune cells of different individuals. These microorganisms, viruses, or cells are classified together based on their cell surface antigens, allowing the epidemiologic classification of organisms to the sub-species level

label: soluble inorganic material
definition: concentration of substances such as ammonia, road-salt, sea-salt, cyanide, hydrogen sulfide, thiocyanates, thiosulfates, etc.

label: subgroup
definition: Taxonomy below subspecies; sometimes used in viruses to denote subgroups taken from a single isolate.

label: viral subtype
definition: A viral subtype is a classification name for a virus according to some protocol.

label: Multilocus Variable Number of Tandem Repeats Analysis typing
definition: MLVA stands for Multilocus Variable Number of Tandem Repeats Analysis. This method can be performed by three distinct methodologies: by running the amplified locus in a gel , using a capilary electrophoresis apparatus or sequencing the resulting amplified fragment. The first two infer the number of repeats on each locus indirectly by the fragment size.

label: lab sequencing datum
definition: A laboratory sequencing datum is a datum related to the sequencing assay process applied to an isolate.

label: phenotypic antimicrobial drug susceptibility test datum
primary enzyme (LMAAI)
definition: Restriction enzyme for first characterization

label: secondary enzyme (LMACI)
definition: Restriction enzyme for second characterization

label: NCBI culture collection
definition: An NCBI culture collection is a composite identifier containing “institution code:collection code”.

label: variant calling / pathogen identification and clustering
container record
definition: A container id is an identifier that refers to a container object about a patient specimen. Container ids are referenced in clinical patient records reported to be suspect, or lab test results.

label: identifier model
definition: An identifier moe3l indicates an identifier, the organization it has been issued by, and the status of the identifier - whether it is a primary one, active or archaic.

label: line list object
definition: A line list is a collection of suspected or known disease outbreak cases.  It may also include details about healthy patients associated with an exposure event (picnic, concert etc.) who have been interviewed in order to compare food intake, assess risk factors, etc.    Note that the health status of people associated with an exposure event can change from healthy or unknown status, to ill patient.

label: medical health record (history / timeline)
definition: A medical health record is a record of a single patient's medical history.

label: test specification
definition: A lab test specification indicates the inputs and outputs (results / conclusions) of a test.

label: Autonomous Region (China)
definition: A first-level administrative subdivision of China. Like Chinese provinces, an autonomous region has its own local government, but an autonomous region has more legislative rights. It is a minority entity and has a higher population of a particular minority ethnic group. There are five autonomous regions in China: the Tibetan people in Tibet, the Zhuang in Guangxi, the Uyghur in Xinjiang, the Mongols in Inner Mongolia, and the Hui in Ningxia.

label: Region (contiguous United States of America)
definition: Census Regions and Divisions are groupings of States that subdivide the United States.

label: AHA HIPPA standard
definition: The American Hospital Association has issued HIPAA Updated Guidelines for Releasing Information on the Condition of Patients

label: PulseNet submission standard
definition: PulseNet, a national and international surveillance system used to identify and respond to foodborne disease outbreaks, has a standardized laboratory method and data submission standard for pathogen isolate typing test results and related isolate contextual data.  From this information clusters of disease can be identified that might represent unrecognized outbreaks.

label: public health lab epidemiology contextual data standard
definition: This model contains data type specifications for whole genome sequencing and epidemiology investigation contextual data.

label: American HIPPA Protected Health Information (PHI) guidelines
definition: The American HIPPA Protected Health Information (PHI) guidelines cover information, including demographic information, which relates to:  - the individual’s past, present, or future physical or mental health or condition, - the provision of health care to the individual, or - the past, present, or future payment for the provision of health care to the individual, and that identifies the individual or for which there is a reasonable basis to believe can be used to identify the individual. Protected health information includes many common identifiers (e.g., name, address, birth date, Social Security Number) when they can be associated with the health information listed above."

label: Canadian Integrated Public Health Information System (iPHIS) Standard
definition: The Canadian Integrated Public Health Information System (iPHIS) System provides a standard for holding reportable disease cases from participating jurisdictions.

label: point
definition: A point is a geometric entity that is located in a zero-dimensional spatial region and whose position is defined by its coordinates in some coordinate system.

label: contact specification - specimen related organization
definition: Contact information for an organization related to specimen collection, processing or storage.

label: epidemiology contact network model
definition: An epidemiology contact network model is a definition of the information necessary to connect pathogen transmission patterns between individuals or animals in connection with an outbreak investigation.

label: Organism Strain
definition: A population or type of organisms that is genetically different from others of the same species and possessing a set of defined characteristics.

label: EBI ENA Webin environmental feature
definition: identifies sequences derived by direct molecular isolation from a bulk environmental DNA sample (by PCR with or without subsequent cloning of the product, DGGE, or other anonymous methods) with no reliable identification of the source organism. Environmental samples include clinical samples, gut contents, and other sequences from anonymous organisms that may be associated with a particular host. They do not include endosymbionts that can be reliably recovered from a particular host, organisms from a readily identifiable but uncultured field sample (e.g., many cyanobacteria), or phytoplasmas that can be reliably recovered from diseased plants (even though these cannot be grown in axenic culture).

label: specimen category
definition: Specimen category is a categorical variable that broadly indicates the source of a specimen in order for data processing systems like NCBI's biosample submission portal to anticipate other fields related to the source. Currently this distinguishes between "clinical or host associated" specimens and "environmental/food or other pathogen" specimens.

label: specimen description
definition: A description of the biological sample analysed.

label: specimen extraction agent
definition: The "specimen extraction agent" is a datum containing the name of persons or institute who collected a given specimen.

label: specimen extraction device
definition: The tool or device used to extract a specimen.

label: specimen history item
definition: A specimen history item is a time-related datum about a particular specimen

label: specimen source context
definition: Describes the physical, environmental and/or local geographical source of the biological sample from which the sample was derived.

label: specimen title
definition: A specimen (or sample) title should be short and informative. Each specimen title must be unique in a submission.

label: specimen with confirmed presence of disease agent
definition: A specimen which has been confirmed by laboratory test(s) to contain a disease-causing agent such as a pathogen

label: subject organism common name
definition: The natural language (non-taxonomic) name of the type of organism (human or animal) that is the subject of a given investigation, study and/or specimen.

label: email address of specimen provider principal investigator
definition: An email address of the principal investigator providing the specimens for the investigation

label: IRIDA user ID
definition: The IRIDA user ID is a user account identifier provided by the IRIDA.ca system.

label: sequence accession
definition: A persistent, unique identifier of a molecular sequence database entry.

label: INSDC institution code
definition: An INSDC institution code is an identifier of an organization from a list of sequence repository organizations managed by INSDC.

label: resolving health trend
definition: to restore to the normal state after some pathologic process.

label: congenital disease
definition: A disease existing at birth, or developping during the first month after birth.

label: missing
definition: 'missing' is a categorical choice recorded when a measurement value was known to be recorded in the past but the observed value cannot be located or retrieved for some reason.

label: not applicable
definition: 'Not applicable' is a categorical choice recorded when a measurable datum does not apply to a given context, as for example the measure of femur length for a patient with a missing limb.

label: recorded
definition: A recorded datum is known to be available for retrieval. Any datum that has a recorded value has this for its metadata "datum status"

label: 2D space
definition: This data type is for an item that can map to a point, line, set or area on a surface (2 dimensional space) or to the surface itself.  It can be a slice of a higher dimensional space.  It can be defined by a cartesian or radial coordinate system.

label: plane
definition: In mathematics, a plane is a flat, two-dimensional surface. A plane is the two-dimensional analogue of a point (zero dimensions), a line (one dimension) and three-dimensional space. Planes can arise as subspaces of some higher-dimensional space, as with the walls of a room, or they may enjoy an independent existence in their own right, as in the setting of Euclidean geometry."  "When working exclusively in two-dimensional Euclidean space, the definite article is used, so, the plane refers to the whole space.

label: quadratic surface
definition: In Euclidean space, quadrics have dimension D = 2, and are known as quadric surfaces.

label: coordinate system
definition: In geometry, a coordinate system is a system which uses one or more numbers, or coordinates, to uniquely determine the position of a point or other geometric element on a manifold such as Euclidean space.

label: one dimensional cartesian coordinate system
definition: a three dimensional cartesian coordinate system is a cartesian coordinate system which defines 3 orthogonal one dimensional axis and which may be used to describe a 3 dimensional spatial region

label: two dimensional cartesian coordinate system
definition: a 2 dimensional cartesian coordinate system is a cartesian coordinate system which defines 2 orthogonal one dimensional axes and which may be used to describe a 2 dimensional spatial region

label: cylindrical coordinate system
definition: A cylindrical coordinate system is a three-dimensional coordinate system that specifies point positions by the distance from a chosen reference axis, the direction from the axis relative to a chosen reference direction, and the distance from a chosen reference plane perpendicular to the axis. The latter distance is given as a positive or negative number depending on which side of the reference plane faces the point.

label: geodetic datum
definition: A coordinate system, and a set of reference points, used to locate places on the Earth (or similar objects).

label: three dimensional cartesian coordinate system
definition: a three dimensional cartesian coordinate system is a cartesian coordinate system which defines 3 orthogonal one dimensional axes and which may be used to describe a 3 dimensional spatial region

label: polar coordinate system
definition: In mathematics, the polar coordinate system is a two-dimensional coordinate system in which each point on a plane is determined by a distance from a fixed point and an angle from a fixed direction.

label: radius
definition: A length quality which is equal to the length of any straight line segment that passes from the center of a circle to any endpoint on the circular boundary. The radius is half of the diameter.

label: area calculation
definition: An area calculation datum is a functional mapping of a two dimensional surface area (can be anything from an abstract polygon, to a postal code or country) to a 1 dimensional scalar.  The original surface area may be curved, e.g. spheroid.  The surface area can also be described using only one input - for example the radius scalar of a polar coordinate plane described by pi*r^2.

label: datetime range intermediate
definition: A datetime range intermediate datum is a datetime item grouped under a process, and occuring  after some process start and before some process end.

label: datetime set item
definition: A datetime set item is a datetime that has been grouped semantically under a given type of process

label: 2D boundary
definition: A two dimensional boundary is a continuous path (loop) defined on a two dimensional surface.

label: 2D entity
definition: A two dimensional entity is an entity composed of one or more points on a two dimensional surface.

label: curve
definition: A curve is a geometric entity that may be located in n-dimensional spatial region whose extension may be n-dimensional,  is composed of at least two fully connected points and does not intersect itself.

label: geographic location
definition: A reference to a place on the Earth, by its name or by its geographical location.

label: geopolitical region
definition: a geopolitical region is a geographic region recognized by social or legal convention.

label: specimen extraction site
definition: The physical location that a specimen was extracted or collected at.  The location may be described by geographic coordinates, city or other geopolitical entity, biome, etc.

label: unordered set
definition: An unordered set is a set of elements which have no intrinsic (semantic) order with respect to each other. The set of all living people is not intrinsically ordered; an ordering can only be provided by looking at some partiular feature of the given set elements.

label: spheroid
definition: A spheroid, or ellipsoid of revolution, is a quadric surface obtained by rotating an ellipse about one of its principal axes; in other words, an ellipsoid with two equal semi-diameters.

label: decimal quantity unit
definition: A multiplier in the decimal number system that has been applied to an accompanying number or set of numbers often to simplfy their appearance.  Numbers described by multipliers may have lost significant digits through rounding or trimming.

label: AB SOLiD System
definition: is a DNA sequencer which is manufactured by Applied Biosystems and which enable DNA sequencing by ligation

label: HeliScope Single Molecule Sequencer
definition: is a DNA sequencer manufacturer by Helicos Corporation to carry out Single Molecule sequencing using reversible termination chemistry

label: Illumina Genome Analyzer II
definition: is a DNA sequence which is manufactured by Illumina (Solexa) corporation. it support sequencing of single or paired end clone libraries relying on sequencing by synthesis technology

label: MiSeq
definition: A DNA sequencer which is manufactured by the Illumina corporation. Built upon sequencing by synthesis technology, the machine provides an end-to-end solution (cluster generation, amplification, sequencing, and data analysis) in a single machine.

label: NextSeq 500
definition: A DNA sequencer which is a desktop sequencer ideal for smaller-scale studies manufactured by the Illumina corporation. It supports sequencing of single, long or short insert paired end clone libraries relying on sequencing by synthesis technology.

label: PacBio RS II
definition: A DNA sequencer which is manufactured by the Pacific Biosciences corporation. Built upon single molecule real-time sequencing technology, the machine is optimized for generation with long reads and high consensus accuracy.

label: circle
definition: A circle is a simple closed shape in Euclidean geometry. It is the set of all points in a plane that are at a given distance from a given point, the centre; equivalently it is the curve traced out by a point that moves so that its distance from a given point is constant.

label: polygon
definition: In elementary geometry, a polygon is a plane figure that is bounded by a finite chain of straight line segments closing in a loop to form a closed chain or circuit.

label: 454 Genome Sequence 20
definition: is a DNA sequencer which is manufactured by 454 Life Science Corporation and enables pyrosequencing to be performed. It comprises both optics and fluidics subsystems, which are controlled by a computer subsystem. The fluidics subsystem ensures accurate reagent dispensing. It consists of a reagents cassette (which holds the reagent containers), a sipper manifold, pumps, valves, and debubblers. The fluidics subsystem flows the sequencing reagents across the wells of the PicoTiterPlate device, and moves the spent reagents from the PicoTiterPlate device to the waste receptacle. The optics subsystem consists of a CCD camera and a camera controller. The camera captures the light emitted in the wells of the PicoTiterPlate device during each step of the sequencing cycle, and sends the digital images to the computer subsystem for processing. The computer controls the other Sequencer subsystems, and processes the digital images sent by the camera to extract the DNA sequence information.

label: 454 Genome Sequencer FLX
definition: is a DNA sequencer which is manufactured by 454 Life Science Corporation and enables pyrosequencing to be performed. It comprises both optics and fluidics subsystems, which are controlled by a computer subsystem. The fluidics subsystem ensures accurate reagent dispensing. It consists of a reagents cassette (which holds the reagent containers), a sipper manifold, pumps, valves, and debubblers. The fluidics subsystem flows the sequencing reagents across the wells of the PicoTiterPlate device, and moves the spent reagents from the PicoTiterPlate device to the waste receptacle. The optics subsystem consists of a CCD camera and a camera controller. The camera captures the light emitted in the wells of the PicoTiterPlate device during each step of the sequencing cycle, and sends the digital images to the computer subsystem for processing. The computer controls the other Sequencer subsystems, and processes the digital images sent by the camera to extract the DNA sequence information.

label: Illumina HiSeq 1000
definition: A DNA sequencer which is manufactured by the Illumina corporation, with a single flow cell and a throughput of up to 35 Gb per day. It supports sequencing of single, long or short insert paired end clone libraries relying on sequencing by synthesis technology.

label: Illumina HiSeq 2000
definition: A DNA sequencer which is manufactured by the Illumina corporation, with two flow cells and a throughput of up to 55 Gb per day. Built upon sequencing by synthesis technology, the machine is optimized for generation of data for multiple samples in a single run.

label: Illumina HiSeq 2500
definition: A DNA sequencer which is manufactured by the Illumina corporation, with two flow cells and a throughput of up to 160 Gb per day. Built upon sequencing by synthesis technology, the machine is optimized for generation of data for batching multiple samples or rapid results on a few samples.

label: Illumina HiSeq 3000
definition: A DNA sequencer manufactured by Illumina corporation, with a single flow cell and a throughput of more than 200 Gb per day.

label: Illumina HiSeq 4000
definition: A DNA sequencer manufactured by Illumina corporation, with two flow cell and a throughput of more than 400 Gb per day.

label: 5-methylcytidine antibody method
definition: Selection of methylated DNA fragments using an antibody raised against 5-methylcytosine or 5-methylcytidine (m5C).

label: CAGE method
definition: Cap-analysis gene expression.

label: CF-H method
definition: Cot-filtered highly repetitive genomic DNA

label: CF-M method
definition: Cot-filtered moderately repetitive genomic DNA

label: CF-S method
definition: Cot-filtered single/low-copy genomic DNA

label: CF-T method
definition: Cot-filtered theoretical single-copy genomic DNA

label: ChIP method
definition: Chromatin immunoprecipitation

label: DNAse method
definition: Deoxyribonuclease (MNase) digestion

label: HMPR method
definition: Hypo-methylated partial restriction digest

label: Hybrid Selection method
definition: Selection by hybridization in array or solution.

label: MBD2 protein methyl-CpG binding domain method
definition: Enrichment by methyl-CpG binding domain.

label: MF method
definition: Methyl Filtrated

label: MNase method
definition: Micrococcal Nuclease (MNase) digestion

label: MSLL method
definition: Methylation Spanning Linking Library

label: PCR method
definition: Source material was selected by designed primers.

label: RACE method
definition: Rapid Amplification of cDNA Ends.

label: RANDOM PCR method
definition: Source material was selected by randomly generated primers.

label: RANDOM method
definition: Random selection by shearing or other method.

label: RT-PCR method
definition: Source material was selected by reverse transcription PCR

label: Reduced Representation method
definition: Reproducible genomic subsets, often generated by restriction fragment size selection, containing a manageable number of loci to facilitate re-sampling.

label: Restriction Digest method
definition: DNA fractionation using restriction enzymes.

label: cDNA method
definition: PolyA selection or enrichment for messenger RNA (mRNA). complementary DNA.

label: other library method
definition: Other library enrichment, screening, or selection process.

label: size fractionation method
definition: Physical selection of size appropriate targets.

label: genomic source
definition: Genomic DNA (includes PCR products from genomic DNA).

label: metagenomic source
definition: Mixed material from metagenome.

label: metatranscriptomic source
definition: Transcription products from community targets

label: other library source
definition: Other, unspecified, or unknown library source material.

label: synthetic source
definition: Synthetic DNA.

label: transcriptomic source
definition: Transcription products or non genomic DNA (EST, cDNA, RT-PCR, screened libraries).

label: viral RNA source
definition: Viral RNA.

label: Bisulfite-Seq strategy
definition: MethylC-seq. Sequencing following treatment of DNA with bisulfite to convert cytosine residues to uracil depending on methylation status.

label: CTS strategy
definition: Concatenated Tag Sequencing

label: ChIP-Seq strategy
definition: Direct sequencing of chromatin immunoprecipitates.

label: DNase-Hypersensitivity strategy
definition: Sequencing of hypersensitive sites, or segments of open chromatin that are more readily cleaved by DNaseI.

label: EST strategy
definition: Single pass sequencing of cDNA templates

label: FL-cDNA strategy
definition: Full-length sequencing of cDNA templates

label: MBD-Seq strategy
definition: Direct sequencing of methylated fractions sequencing strategy.

label: MNase-Seq strategy
definition: Direct sequencing following MNase digestion.

label: MRE-Seq strategy
definition: Methylation-Sensitive Restriction Enzyme Sequencing strategy.

label: MeDIP-Seq strategy
definition: Methylated DNA Immunoprecipitation Sequencing strategy.

label: RNA-Seq strategy
definition: Random sequencing of whole transcriptome.

label: WCS strategy
definition: Random sequencing of a whole chromosome or other replicon isolated from a genome.

label: WGS strategy
definition: Random sequencing of the whole genome.

label: WXS strategy
definition: Random sequencing of exonic regions selected from the genome.

label: amplicon strategy
definition: Sequencing of overlapping or distinct PCR or RT-PCR products. For example, metagenomic community profiling using SSU rRNA

label: clone end strategy
definition: Clone end (5', 3', or both) sequencing.

label: clone strategy
definition: Genomic clone based (hierarchical) sequencing.

label: finishing strategy
definition: Sequencing intended to finish (close) gaps in existing coverage.

label: other library strategy
definition: Library strategy not listed.

label: pool clone strategy
definition: Shotgun of pooled clones (usually BACs and Fosmids).

label: TB lineage 3 - East-African Indian, includes CAS/Delhi
TB lineage 4 - Euro-American, includes Haarlem, LAM3, X, T, F11, H37Rv
country name
definition: A textual entity that denotes a geographic location that is a site or part of a site that is identified as a country in the political geography.

label: country of birth
definition: A country of birth is the country that a given person (or animal) was born in.

label: health status history datum
definition: A health status history datum is a record of the longer-term pattern or presence of a given patient's health status.

label: health status trend datum
definition: A health status trend is a short-term prognosis about whether health is improving, worsening or unchanging

label: host hospital service status
definition: A host hospital service status indicates the state of a host's interaction with hospital medical services.

label: life status
definition: life status is the quality of whether something is alive or dead.

label: patient as host datum
definition: A host datum is a datum that pertains to infection-related information about an organism (animal or human) who is likely bearing a pathogen

label: subject disease
definition: Name of disease in a subject that is related to a given investigation, study and/or specimen.

label: subject disease outcome
definition: A subject disease outcome is an assessment of the persistence of a given disease course in a subject (patient)

label: subject disease stage
definition: A subject disease stage is a measure of the acuteness of a subject organism's diagnosed disease, if any, at a given time in an investigation, study or specimen extraction event.

label: subject health status
definition: The condition of an organism in all aspects (e.g., functional or metabolic efficiency).

label: subject health status (GSCID-BRC)
definition: A description of whether a given subject organism appeared healthy, sick or deceased at the time of specimen extraction. If sick or deceased, additional details should be provided in project-specific fields.

label: Phenotypic abnormality
definition: A phenotypic abnormality.

label: treated and released (not admitted to hospital)
definition: Received treatment but not admitted.

label: treated and transferred
definition: Received treatment. Transferred to a different facility.

label: data protection role
definition: A data protection role is a role (or user permission) that a user has with respect to particular data.

label: MIC unit
definition: mg/L

label: MIC value
definition: The measured or quantified MIC

label: Microbial Susceptibility Test Result
definition: The outcome of a test to determine whether microbial growth is affected by an antimicrobial compound.

label: Minimum Inhibitory Concentration Test
definition: A laboratory test to determine the lowest concentration of a substance that will inhibit a biological or biochemical function, such as microorganism growth or enzymatic activity.

label: antimicrobial phenotype
definition: Qualitative description of a microbe’s response to antimicrobial agents and the expected clinical outcome. Bacteria may be susceptible or resistant to a broad range of antibiotic drugs or drug classes, with several intermediate states or phases.

label: antimicrobial resistance test platform
definition: System of analysis for determining antimicrobial susceptibility.

label: antimicrobial resistance testing reference standard
definition: Uses breakpoints to create standards for interpreting the clinical outcome of an MIC value for a particular microbial species and antimicrobial agent

label: antimicrobial resistance tissue specificity
definition: The tissue type used to select breakpoints from a particular standard, for the interpretation of MIC results.

label: automated testing platform vendor
