definition: Vendor of automated system of analysis for determining antimicrobial susceptibility.

label: in-vitro microbial susceptibility test
definition: An experimental test conducted outside of a living organism, usually in a tube or plate.

label: antimicrobial resistance test drug
definition: This is a collection of drugs used to test antimicrobial resistance.

label: antimicrobial resistance testing method version or reagent
definition: The commercial kit or product used to determine the MIC e.g. E-Test. If a commercial product was not used, include the type of media used.

label: antimicrobial resistance testing platform (deprecated)
definition: The instrumentation used to determine minimum inhibitory concentration values.

label: antimicrobial resistance testing platform vendor (deprecated)
definition: The manufacturer of an antibiotic resistance lab typing platform

label: antimicrobial resistance testing reference standard (deprecated)
definition: The clinical and laboratory guidelines or standards that prescribe the threshold values for determining resistance phenotypes.

label: antimicrobial resistance testing reference standard version
definition: The version of the antimicrobial reistance testing reference standard protocol used in assessing an isolate.

label: antimicrobial resistance tissue specificity (deprecated)
definition: The tissue type used to select breakpoints from a particular standard, for the interpretation of MIC results.

label: drug minimum inhibitory concentration unit (deprecated)
definition: The unit provided for an antibiotic drug test dosage.

label: measurement comparator
definition: The measurement comparator is a sign indicating that a measurement is above, equal to, or below a given threshold.

label: test drug maximum concentration
definition: This is the maximum concentration of a drug applied during an an assay.

label: test drug minimum concentration
definition: This is the minimum concentration of a drug applied during an an assay.

label: tuberculosis treatment drug
definition: A tuberculosis treatment antibiotic is an antibiotic used in the treatment of tuberculosis.

label: Microbial Susceptibility Test
definition: A method to determine whether microbial growth is affected by an antimicrobial compound.

label: German Institute for Standardization (DIN) (deprecated)
definition: DIN is recognized by the Federal Government of Germany as the competent standards organization for Germany and as the national standards body representing Germany in non-governmental international standards organizations.

label: British Society for Antimicrobial Chemotherapy (BSAC) (deprecated)
definition: BSAC is a British inter-professional organisation involved in antibiotic education, research and leadership

label: Clinical and Laboratory Standards Institute (CLSI) (Deprecated)
definition: The Clinical and Laboratory Standards Institute develops and implements clinical laboratory testing standards

label: European Committe on Antimicrobial Susceptibility Testing (EUCAST) (deprecated)
definition: EUCAST is a standing committee jointly organized by ESCMID, ECDC and European national breakpoint committees; it deals with breakpoints and technical aspects of phenotypic in vitro antimicrobial susceptibility testing.

label: National Committee on Clinical Laboratory Standards (NCCLS)
definition: On January 1, 2005 the National Committee on Clinical Laboratory Standards (NCCLS) changed its name to CLSI

label: Société Française de Microbiologie (SFM) (deprecated)
definition: The French Society of Microbiology (SFM) is a non-profit association which aims to bring together microbiologists from French-speaking countries, working in the domains of bacteria, viruses, Fungi and parasites, and related medical, industrial and environmental microbiology, physiology, genetics, taxonomy, hygiene, and antimicrobial agents.

label: GSCID-BRC Project and Sample Application Standard
definition: The GSCID-BRC Project and Sample Application Standard captures standardized human pathogen and vector sequencing metadata to support epidemiologic and genotype-phenotype association studies for human infectious diseases.

label: Minimum information about a marker gene sequence
definition: The "minimum information about a marker gene sequence" (MIMARKS) is a standard developed by the Genomic Standards Consortium (GSC) for reporting marker gene sequences.

label: Minimum Information about any (x) Sequence (MIxS)
definition: MixS is a unified standard for describing sequence data provided by the Genomic Standards Consortium (GSC)

label: Container
definition: An object that can be used to hold things.

label: Sponge
definition: A soft flexible, absorbent pad usually made from natural material such as gauze or cotton, used to absorb blood and other fluids, as in surgery or the dressing of a wound. The term also refers to a small absorbent contraceptive pad that contains a spermicide and is placed against the cervix of the uterus before sexual intercourse.

label: Swab
definition: A tuft of material on the end of a stick for applying solutions and suspensions
ui_definition: A portion of an absorbent material attached to one end of a small stick for the purpose of applying or collecting material.

label: Tube
definition: A hollow cylinder, especially one for holding or conveying liquids; anything shaped like such a hollow cylinder, e.g. an organic structure having the shape or function of a tube such as channel within a plant or animal body (e.g. fallopian tube).
ui_definition: A hollow cylinder, especially one for holding or conveying liquids.

label: Life Threatening
definition: A situation that imperils the existence of an entity.

label: Non-Pathological
definition: The absence of disease or pathology.

label: Vacutainer
definition: A brand of of test tube specifically designed for venipuncture; the tube contains a vacuum allowing it to suck blood though a needle and fill itself. The tube may contain additives to facilitate downstream processing and testing of the blood samples; the tube cap is color-coded to indicate the type of additive present.

label: infectious disease cluster
definition: A disease cluster in which two or more cases have been linked by an infectious disease transmission process.

label: assembly genome size specification
definition: A specification for the size of an assembled genome as measured in base pairs.

label: test drug minimum concentration specification
definition: This is the minimum concentration of a drug applied during an an assay.

label: unsigned long integer value specification
definition: A 64 bit integer ranging from 0 - 18446744073709551615

label: unsigned short integer value specification
definition: a 16 bit integer ranging from 0 - 65535

label: date value specification (ISO 8601)
definition: A date should be recorded as YYYY-MM-DD according to ISO 8601.  HOWEVER ... OWL 2.0 does not include xsd:date as a permitted data type, so this value specification only accepts xsd:dateTime

label: date of diagnosis (ISO 8601)
definition: The point at which a clinical diagnosis is made.

label: subject age at time of specimen collection specification
specimen extraction location - city
definition: The specimen extraction location - city is the city where a specimen was taken (extracted) from a subject or environment

label: specimen extraction location - city or region
definition: A specimen extraction location - city or region is the Gazetteer ontology identifier or textual name of the most precise geographical location available for the site of a specimen extraction event.

label: specimen extraction location - country
definition: A specimen location country is the country of the site of a given specimen collection event.

label: specimen extraction location - state/province/territory/region
definition: A specimen extraction location - city or region is the Gazetteer ontology identifier or textual name of the most precise geographical location available for the site of a specimen extraction event.

label: unsigned integer value specification
definition: A 32 bit number having a range 0 - 4294967295.

label: subject age specification
definition: A subject age is the age since birth of a given organism that is involved in an investigation or study at a given time.

label: non-wild type (NWT) (deprecated)
definition: A non-wild type (WT) resistance phenotype indicates a bacterial pathogen has an acquired or mutational resistance mechanism present with respect to the antimicrobial in question. The bacteria has a reduced susceptibility to this agent.

label: wild type (WT) (deprecated)
definition: A wild type (WT) resistance phenotype indicates a bacterial pathogen belongs to a "Naïve", susceptible wild-type population with respect to a given antimicrobial. No acquired or mutational resistance mechanisms are present to the antimicrobial in question.

label: isolate preparation service
definition: An isolate preparation service prepares isolates for molecular sequencing.

label: sequencing service
definition: A service provides sequencing service which is the realization of some sequencing such as RNA and DNA sequencing in which the service provider role is realized.

label: subject identifier specification
definition: A subject identifier specification is a specification including datatype pertaining to a given standard's subject identifier field.

label: animal rinse
definition: Animal rinse is a rinse derived from animal material of one or more animals.

label: plant rinse
definition: Plant rinse is a rinse derived from plant material from one or more plants.

label: earth surface
definition: Earth surface is the entire surface of planet Earth, at the general boundary between water or land, and the surrounding atmosphere, from a navigational (latitude, longitude, and altitude) perspective.

label: smoking behavior
definition: Inhaling and exhaling the smoke of tobacco or something similar to tobacco.

label: behavior
definition: The actions or reactions of an object or organism, usually in relation to the environment or surrounding world of stimuli. E.g. Fixed action pattern courtship behaviour in Drosophila. Forager behaviour in honey bees.

label: reproductive process
definition: A process in which an organism or part of an organism participates towards the generation of offspring.

label: transmission of infection
definition: A process that is the means during which the pathogen is transmitted directly or indirectly from its natural reservoir, a susceptible host or source to a new host.

label: Abnormal renal physiology
definition: An abnormal functionality of the kidney.

label: Abnormality of the upper urinary tract
definition: An abnormality of the upper urinary tract.

label: Abnormality of the urinary system physiology
Abnormality of blood and blood-forming tissues
definition: An abnormality of the hematopoietic system.

label: Abnormality of head or neck
definition: An abnormality of head and neck.

label: Abnormality of the cardiovascular system
definition: Any abnormality of the cardiovascular system.

label: Abnormality of the ear
definition: An abnormality of the ear.

label: Abnormality of the eye
definition: Any abnormality of the eye, including location, spacing, and intraocular abnormalities.

label: Abnormality of the genitourinary system
definition: The presence of any abnormality of the genitourinary system.

label: Abnormality of the immune system
definition: An abnormality of the immune system.

label: Abnormality of the integument
definition: An abnormality of the integument, which consists of the skin and the superficial fascia.

label: Abnormality of the musculature
definition: Abnormality originating in one or more muscles, i.e., of the set of muscles of body.

label: Abnormality of the nervous system
definition: An abnormality of the nervous system.

label: Abnormality of the skeletal system
definition: An abnormality of the skeletal system.

label: Constitutional symptom
definition: A symptom or manifestation indicating a systemic or general effect of a disease and that may affect the general well-being or status of an individual.

label: asymptomatic host of infectious agent
definition: An organism that is host to an infectious agent and has no symptoms of the infectious disease associated with the infectious agent.

label: Abnormality of the urinary system
definition: An abnormality of the urinary system.

label: Abnormality of the head
definition: An abnormality of the head.

label: Abnormal oral physiology
definition: A functional anomaly of the mouth (which is also known as the oral cavity).

label: Abnormality of the face
definition: An abnormality of the face.

label: Abnormality of the mouth
definition: An abnormality of the mouth.

label: Abnormality of the ocular adnexa
definition: An anomaly of the adjacent structures (i.e., adnexa) of the eye, defined as the lacrimal apparatus, the extraocular muscles and the eyelids, eyelashes, eyebrows and the conjunctiva.

label: Functional abnormality of the inner ear
definition: An abnormality of the function of the inner ear.

label: Abnormal eye physiology
definition: A functional anomaly of the eye.

label: Dermatochalasis
definition: Loss of elasticity of the upper and lower eyelids causing the skin to sag and bulge.

label: Blurred vision
definition: Lack of sharpness of vision resulting in the inability to see fine detail.

label: Abnormal ear morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the ear.

label: Abnormality of nervous system physiology
definition: A functional anomaly of the nervous system.

label: Abnormality of skeletal morphology
definition: An abnormality of the form, structure, or size of the skeletal system.

label: Abnormality of skin physiology
definition: Any abnormality of the physiological function of the skin.

label: Abnormality of joint mobility
definition: An abnormality in the range and ease of motion of joints across their normal range.

label: Joint stiffness
definition: Joint stiffness is a perceived sensation of tightness in a joint or joints when attempting to move them after a period of inactivity. Joint stiffness typically subsides over time.

label: Abnormality of body weight
definition: An abnormal increase or decrease of weight or an abnormal distribution of mass in the body.

label: Abnormality of the skin
definition: An abnormality of the skin.

label: Abnormal cry
definition: Any anomaly of the vocalizing of an infant's crying, i.e.,the typically loud voice production that is accompanied by tears and agitation.

label: Abnormal cardiovascular system physiology
definition: Abnormal functionality of the cardiovascular system.

label: Vertigo
definition: An abnormal sensation of spinning while the body is actually stationary.

label: Abnormal bleeding
definition: An abnormal susceptibility to bleeding, often referred to as a bleeding diathesis. A bleeding diathesis may be related to vascular, platelet and coagulation defects.

label: Internal hemorrhage
definition: The presence of hemorrhage within the body.

label: Abnormal homeostasis
definition: An anomaly in the processes involved in the maintenance of an internal equilibrium.

label: Abnormality of urine homeostasis
definition: An abnormality of the composition of urine or the levels of its components.

label: Episodic vomiting
definition: Paroxysmal, recurrent episodes of vomiting.

label: Projectile vomiting
definition: Vomiting that ejects the gastric contents with great force.

label: Feculent vomiting
definition: Vomiting of material that is of fecal origin.

label: Chronic diarrhea
definition: The presence of chronic diarrhea, which is usually taken to mean diarrhea that has persisted for over 4 weeks.

label: Secretory diarrhea
definition: Watery voluminous diarrhea resulting from an imbalance between ion and water secretion and absorption.

label: Bloody diarrhea
definition: Passage of many stools containing blood.

label: Nausea
definition: A sensation of unease in the stomach together with an urge to vomit.

label: Vomiting
definition: Forceful ejection of the contents of the stomach through the mouth by means of a series of involuntary spasmic contractions.

label: Acute constipation
definition: Constipation of sudden onset and lasting for less than three months.

label: Chronic constipation
definition: Constipation for longer than three months with fewer than 3 bowel movements per week, straining, lumpy or hard stools, and a sensation of anorectal obstruction or incomplete defecation.

label: Abdominal colic
definition: A type of abdominal pain that comes and goes in waves, most often starting and ending suddenly and being of severe intensity.

label: Abdominal cramps
definition: A type of abdominal pain characterized by a feeling of contractions and typically fluctuating in intensity.

label: Abdominal guarding
definition: A voluntary contraction of the abdominal wall musculature to avoid pain.

label: Abdominal rigidity
definition: Involuntary tightening of the abdominal musculature that occurs in response to touching the abdomen to avoid pain. Rigidity can occur in the presence of abdominal inflammation and usually involves only the inflamed area.

label: Dyspepsia
definition: A heterogeneous group of symptoms that are localized in the epigastric region. Typical dyspeptic symptoms include postprandial fullness, early satiation, epigastric pain and epigastric burning, but other upper gastrointestinal symptoms such as nausea, belching or abdominal bloating often occur.

label: Episodic abdominal pain
definition: An intermittent form of abdominal pain.

label: Hematochezia
definition: The passage of fresh (red) blood per anus, usually in or with stools. Most rectal bleeding comes from the colon, rectum, or anus.

label: Melena
definition: The passage of blackish, tarry feces associated with gastrointestinal hemorrhage. Melena occurs if the blood remains in the colon long enough for it to be broken down by colonic bacteria. One degradation product, hematin, imbues the stool with a blackish color. Thus, melena generally occurs with bleeding from the upper gastrointestinal tract (e.g., stomach ulcers or duodenal ulcers), since the blood usually remains in the gut for a longer period of time than with lower gastrointestinal bleeding.

label: Abnormality of immune system physiology
definition: A functional abnormality of the immune system.

label: Abnormal muscle physiology
definition: A functional abnormality of a skeletal muscle.

label: Abnormal urine cytology
definition: An anomalous finding in the examination of the urine for cells.

label: Protuberant abdomen
definition: A thrusting or bulging out of the abdomen.

label: Weight loss
definition: Reduction inexisting body weight.

label: Fever
definition: Elevated body temperature due to failed thermoregulation.

label: Gastrojejunal tube feeding in infancy
definition: Feeding problem necessitating gastrojejunal tube feeding.

label: Gastrostomy tube feeding in infancy
definition: Feeding problem necessitating gastrostomy tube feeding.

label: Nasal regurgitation
definition: Regurgitation of milk through the nose.

label: Nasogastric tube feeding in infancy
definition: Feeding problem necessitating nasogastric tube feeding.

label: Poor suck
definition: An inadequate sucking reflex, resulting in the difficult of newborns to be breast-fed.

label: Abnormality of the kidney
definition: An abnormality of the kidney.

label: Abnormal inflammatory response
definition: Any anomaly of the inflammatory response, a response to injury or infection characterized by local vasodilation, extravasation of plasma into intercellular spaces and accumulation of white blood cells and macrophages.

label: Functional abnormality of the gastrointestinal tract
definition: Abnormal functionality of the gastrointestinal tract.

label: Abnormality of blood circulation
definition: An abnormality of blood circulation.

label: Gastrointestinal hemorrhage
definition: Hemorrhage affecting the gastrointestinal tract.

label: Edema
definition: An abnormal accumulation of fluid beneath the skin, or in one or more cavities of the body.

label: Inflammatory abnormality of the skin
definition: The presence of inflammation of the skin. That is, an abnormality of the skin resulting from the local accumulation of fluid, plasma proteins, and leukocytes.

label: Vestibular dysfunction
definition: An abnormality of the functioning of the vestibular apparatus.

label: Paralysis
definition: Paralysis of voluntary muscles means loss of contraction due to interruption of one or more motor pathways from the brain to the muscle fibers. Although the word paralysis is often used interchangeably to mean either complete or partial loss of muscle strength, it is preferable to use paralysis or plegia for complete or severe loss of muscle strength, and paresis for partial or slight loss. Motor paralysis results from deficits of the upper motor neurons (corticospinal, corticobulbar, or subcorticospinal). Motor paralysis is often accompanied by an impairment in the facility of movement.

label: Slurred speech
definition: Abnormal coordination of muscles involved in speech.

label: Abdominal distention
definition: Distention of the abdomen.

label: Abdominal pain
definition: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) and perceived to originate in the abdomen.

label: Abnormal bowel sounds
definition: An anomaly of the amount or nature of abdominal sounds. Abdominal sounds (bowel sounds) are made by the movement of the intestines as they promote passage of abdominal contents by peristalsis.

label: Anorexia
definition: A lack or loss of appetite for food (as a medical condition).

label: Constipation
definition: Infrequent or difficult evacuation of feces.

label: Diarrhea
definition: Abnormally increased frequency of loose or watery bowel movements.

label: Feeding difficulties
definition: Impaired ability to eat related to problems gathering food and getting ready to suck, chew, or swallow it.

label: Scaphoid abdomen
definition: The anterior abdominal wall is sunken and presents a concave rather than a convex contour.

label: Limitation of joint mobility
definition: A reduction in the freedom of movement of one or more joints.

label: Increased muscle fatiguability
definition: An abnormal, increased fatiguability of the musculature.

label: Abnormal joint morphology
definition: An abnormal structure or form of the joints, i.e., one or more of the articulations where two bones join.

label: Delayed self-feeding during toddler years
definition: A delay in the development of skills required to feed oneself in the toddler period (between one and three years of age).

label: Feeding difficulties in infancy
definition: Impaired feeding performance of an infant as manifested by difficulties such as weak and ineffective sucking, brief bursts of sucking, and falling asleep during sucking. There may be difficulties with chewing or maintaining attention.

label: Hematuria
definition: The presence of blood in the urine. Hematuria may be gross hematuria (visible to the naked eye) or microscopic hematuria (detected by dipstick or microscopic examination of the urine).

label: Renal insufficiency
definition: A reduction in the level of performance of the kidneys in areas of function comprising the concentration of urine, removal of wastes, the maintenance of electrolyte balance, homeostasis of blood pressure, and calcium metabolism.

label: Abnormality of fluid regulation
definition: An abnormality of the regulation of body fluids.

label: Abnormality of temperature regulation
definition: An abnormality of temperature homeostasis.

label: Abnormality of vision
definition: Abnormality of eyesight (visual perception).

label: Ptosis
definition: The upper eyelid margin is positioned 3 mm or more lower than usual and covers the superior portion of the iris (objective); or, the upper lid margin obscures at least part of the pupil (subjective).

label: Episodic pain
definition: Intermittant pain, i.e., pain that occurs occasionally and at irregular intervals.

label: Myalgia
definition: Pain in muscle.

label: Abnormality of central motor function
definition: An anomaly of the control or production of movement in the central nervous system.

label: Behavioral abnormality
definition: An abnormality of mental functioning including various affective, behavioural, cognitive and perceptual abnormalities.

label: Dysphagia
definition: Difficulty in swallowing.

label: Headache
definition: Cephalgia, or pain sensed in various parts of the head, not confined to the area of distribution of any nerve.

label: Increased inflammatory response
definition: A abnormal increase in the inflammatory response to injury or infection.

label: Abnormality of esophagus physiology
definition: Any physiological abnormality of the esophagus.

label: Abnormality of the gastrointestinal tract
definition: An abnormality of the gastrointestinal tract.

label: Abnormality of digestive system physiology
definition: A functional anomaly of the digestive system.

label: Bloody mucoid diarrhea
definition: Passage of many stools containing blood and mucus.

label: Fatigue
definition: A subjective feeling of tiredness characterized by a lack of energy and motivation.

label: Pain
definition: An unpleasant sensory and emotional experience associated with actual or potential tissue damage, or described in terms of such damage.

label: Hyperactive bowel sounds
definition: An increased amount of bowel sounds.

label: Hypoactive bowel sounds
definition: An decreased amount of bowel sounds.

label: Lack of bowel sounds
definition: Complete lack of abdominal sounds as assayed by examination of the abdomen with a stethoscope.

label: Abnormal eyelid morphology
definition: An abnormality of the eyelids.

label: Abnormality of the inner ear
definition: An abnormality of the inner ear.

label: Abnormal ocular adnexa morphology
definition: A structural anomaly of the adjacent structures (i.e., adnexa) of the eye, defined as the lacrimal apparatus, the extraocular muscles and the eyelids, eyelashes, eyebrows and the conjunctiva.

label: Abnormal eating behavior
definition: Abnormal eating habit with excessive or insufficient consumption of food or any other abnormal pattern of food consumption.

label: Xerostomia
definition: Dryness of the mouth due to salivary gland dysfunction.

label: project relevance
definition: Indicates how the knowledge derived from the project can be applied, and to what field(s).

label: specification of data to be generated in an investigation
definition: An objective specification which indicates the type of data that will be generated and submitted to a database.

label: categorical label
definition: A label that is part of a categorical datum and that indicates the value of the data item on the categorical scale.

label: measurement unit label
definition: A measurement unit label is as a label that is part of a scalar measurement datum and denotes a unit of measure.

label: measurement
definition: A measurement is an information entity that is a recording of the output of a measurement such as produced by an instrument.

label: average value
definition: A  data item that is produced as the output of an averaging data transformation and represents the average value of the input data.

label: data set
definition: A data item that is an aggregate of other data items of the same type that have something in common. Averages and distributions can be determined for data sets.

label: datum status
definition: A datum status is the state of a measurable datum - whether it has been collected or determined, etc. - at some point in time (by default, the last known state) during a measurement process.  A datum's information privacy constraints can be defined mainly by way of the "data protection role".  The datum status's given states (missing, recorded, etc.) may be accompanied by values that they are represented as in 3rd party databases by using the "has database crossreference" hasDbXref relation, e.g. "hasDbXref 'NCBI Biosample: 'not collected'"   Note that a given datum's status value is metadata, i.e. a statement about a particular datum in the case where no actual data entry or categorical choice for that datum has been made.

label: measurement datum
definition: A measurement datum is an information content entity that is a recording of the output of a measurement such as produced by a device.

label: setting datum
definition: A settings datum is a datum that denotes some configuration of an instrument.

label: centrally registered identifier symbol
definition: A symbol that is part of a CRID and that is sufficient to look up a record from the CRID's registry.

label: numeral
definition: A symbol that denotes a number.

label: integer numeral
definition: a numeral that denotes an integer

label: value specification
definition: An information content entity that specifies a value within a classification scheme or on a quantitative scale.

label: adjunct characteristics of food
definition: Additional groups of descriptors of a miscellaneous nature. [FDA CFSAN 1995]

label: case definition
definition: An information content entity that specifies the criteria that an organism must meet to be considered to be in some abnormal state.

label: data item
definition: a data item is an information content entity that is intended to be a truthful statement about something (modulo, e.g., measurement precision or other systematic errors) and is constructed/acquired by a method which reliably tends to produce (approximately) truthful statements.

label: datum label
definition: A label is a symbol that is part of some other datum and is used to either partially define  the denotation of that datum or to provide a means for identifying the datum as a member of the set of data with the same label

label: directive information entity
definition: An information content entity whose concretizations indicate to their bearer how to realize them in a process.

label: document part
definition: an information content entity that is part of a document

label: symbol
definition: An information content entity that is a mark(s) or character(s) used as a conventional representation of another entity.

label: textual entity
definition: A textual entity is a part of a manifestation (FRBR sense), a generically dependent continuant whose concretizations are patterns of glyphs intended to be interpreted as words, formulas, etc.

label: transmission coefficient
definition: An information content entity that represents the rate that an infection moves from infected individuals to susceptible individuals in a population.

label: variable
definition: a variable is a data item which can assume any of a set of values, either as determined by an agent or as randomly occuring through observation.

label: temporal measurement
definition: A temporal entity is an entity that has temporal parts and that happens, unfolds or develops through time. An occurrent is something which exists over time, rather than existing completely at many times

label: MIC diffusion measurement datum
definition: A MIC test measurement resulting from a laboratory diffusion method.

label: MIC dilution measurement datum
definition: A MIC test measurement resulting from a laboratory dilution method.

label: N50
definition: the weighted median item size or N50 is a weighted median of the lengths of items, equal to the length of the longest item i such that the sum of the lengths of items greater than or equal in length to i is greater than or equal to half the length of all of the items. With regard to assemblies the items are typically contigs or scaffolds. It therefore denotes the ability of the software to create contigs and provides information about the resulting sequence assembly

label: length measurement datum
definition: A scalar measurement datum that is the result of measurement of length quality

label: mass measurement datum
definition: A scalar measurement datum that is the result of measurement of mass quality

label: time measurement datum
definition: A scalar measurement datum that is the result of measuring a temporal interval

label: data representational model
definition: Data representational model is an information content entity of the  relationships between data items. A data representational model is encoded in a data format specification such as for cytoscape or biopax.

label: action specification
definition: a directive information entity that describes an action the bearer will take

label: objective specification
definition: a directive information entity that describes an intended process endpoint. When part of a plan specification the concretization is realized in a planned process in which the bearer tries to effect the world so that the process endpoint is achieved.

label: plan specification
definition: A directive information entity with action specifications and objective specifications as parts that, when concretized, is realized in a process in which the bearer tries to achieve the objectives by taking the actions specified.

label: census
definition: The count of a specific entity in a specified region at a specified time.

label: disease cluster
definition: A disease cluster is an unusually high incidence of a particular disease or disorder occurring in close proximity in terms of both time and geography.

label: project data type
definition: A general label indicating the primary study goal. These are only relevant for Primary submission projects (not Umbrella projects).

label: study design
definition: A plan specification comprised of protocols (which may specify how and what kinds of data will be gathered) that are executed as part of an investigation and is realized during a study design execution.

label: target capture specification
definition: A plan specification which specifies how the material enrichment procedure will influence the scale, or type of material that will be assayed in the specimen.

label: investigation assay specification
definition: A plan specification which indicates the assay type used to obtain data.

label: specimen-based scope of investigation specification
definition: A plan specification which specifies the scope of an investigation based on the heterogeneity of organisms or type of material that are the specified input of specimen collection.

label: target material in specimen specification
definition: A plan specification which specifies the type of material that will be assayed in an investigation.

label: categorical measurement datum
definition: A measurement datum that is reported on a categorical scale

label: count
definition: a count is a data item denoted by an integer and represented the number of instances or occurences of an entity

label: geographic location datum
definition: A geographical location datum is a datum that refers to a real, hypothesized or fanciful spatial location

label: investigation datum
definition: A categorical investigation datum is a datum pertaining to some entity examined for scientific research or diagnostic purposes and which has a scope that is broader than one of the clinical, environmental or epidemiological domains.

label: scalar measurement datum
definition: a scalar measurement datum is a measurement datum that is composed of two parts, numerals and a unit label.

label: sequence data
definition: A measurement datum that representing the primary structure of a macromolecule(it's sequence) sometimes associated with an indicator of confidence of that measurement.

label: Name
definition: The words or language units by which a thing is known.

label: NCBI BioSample isolate (human name or description)
definition: identification or description of the specific individual from which this sample was obtained

label: NCBI pathotype
definition: A pathotype is a common name for a group of organisms (of the same species) that have the same pathogenicity on a specified host

label: comment on investigation
definition: A textual entity that is about any of the aspects of an investigation worth noting

label: description
definition: A description is language entity in which elements of a language (formal or natural) are used to characterize an entity.

label: detection limit
definition: The detection limit denotes the smallest measure that can be detected with reasonable certainty for a given analytical procedure.

label: investigation description
definition: A textual entity that describes an investigation.

label: investigation title
definition: A textual entity that denotes an investigation.

label: latitude and longitude coordinate (NCBI BioSample format)
definition: The geographical coordinates of the location where the sample was collected. Specify as degrees latitude and longitude in format "d[d.dddd] N|S d[dd.dddd] W|E", eg, 38.98 N 77.11 W

label: note
definition: A note is text that provides human-readable information on one or more subjects.

label: Proprietary Name
definition: The part of the name or logo associated with a specific product or service identifying and distinguishing it from varieties of the same product or service marketed by competing companies.

label: notes section
definition: A part of a document containing typically short notes about the document itself and/or the authors. Often the notes section contains subsections related to funding, competing interests, ethical approval, etc.

label: gestation period duration
definition: The length of time between when a fertilized egg implants in the wall of the uterus and the birth of offspring.

label: age measurement datum
definition: A time measurement datum that is the result of measurement of age of an organism

label: date of diagnosis
definition: The point at which a clinical diagnosis is made.

label: lifespan history item
definition: A livespan history item is a date-associated event pertaining to the life of a subject.

label: organism location history datum
definition: A time measurement datum that pertains to an organism's physical location.

label: sampling time measurement datum
definition: A time measurement datum when an observation is made or a sample is taken from a material as measured from some reference point.

label: treatment history datum
definition: A time measurement datum that pertains to a patient's medical treatment.

label: E-mail Address
definition: A text string identifier for a location to which e-mail can be delivered.

label: Postal Code
definition: Any system designed to expedite the sorting and delivery of mail by assigning a series of alphanumeric codes to each delivery area. Also used to refer to any individual delivery area code.

label: Canada postal code FSA
definition: The "Canadia postal code FSA" is the leading FSA (Forward Sortation Area) 3 character portion of a full 6 character Canadian postal code.  It can be used to reduce the geographic granularity of a postal code for data generalization or obfuscation.

label: IP number
definition: an IP number is an number to connect to a device on the internet.

label: PubMed ID
definition: A CRID symbol that is sufficient to look up a citation from the PubMed, a literature database of life sciences and biomedical information.

label: URL
definition: A Uniform Resource Locator or Universal Resource Locator (URL) is a specific character string that constitutes a reference to an Internet resource.

label: case identifier
definition: A case ID is a unique identifier associated with a particular episode of care for an individual or animal.

label: database field name
definition: The name of a field in a database.

label: document citation identifier
definition: Note: REPLACE WITH Citation: SIO_000174  ????

label: grant identifier
definition: A CRID symbol used to identify a grant.

label: individual organism identifier
definition: a CRID symbol used to distinguish one individual organism from another.

label: investigation identifier
definition: A CRID symbol used to identify an investigation.

label: isolate identifier
definition: An isolate identifier is an identifier assigned to a given isolate by a particular agency that is handling or storing it.

label: record identifier
definition: A record identifier is an identifier for a database entry.

label: sequencing run sample identifier
definition: A sequencing run sample identifier is an alphanumeric identifier for a sample.  In bioinformatics processing this identifier is assigned to a sample in order to track it through the process of sequencing and analysis.

label: specimen identifier
definition: A CRID symbol denotes a specimen and used to distinguish one specimen from another in an investigation.

label: strain identifier
definition: A strain identifier is the unique microbial or eukaryotic strain name from a reference database that a sample has been matched to.

label: user identifier
definition: A user identifier is an identifier provided as part of an authentication process of a client (user) to a service (server).  User identifiers normally persist over time, in contrast to session identifiers which are temporary.

label: source database
definition: Database that originally provided the interaction record for exchange purposes.

label: Telephone Number
definition: A sequence of decimal digits (0-9) that is used for identifying a destination telephone line or other device in a telephone network.

label: infectious agent carrier role
definition: An infectious agent host role borne by an organism in virtue of the fact that its extended organism contains an infectious agent, the infectious agent has the infectious disposition towards the host, and the host has no symptoms of the infectious disease caused by the infectious agent.

label: infectious agent host role
definition: A pathogen host role borne by an organism in virtue of the fact that its extended organism contains an infectious agent.

label: resistance to drug
definition: A protective resistance that mitigates the damaging effects of a drug.

label: antibiotic resistance
definition: A resistance to drug that mitigates the damaging effects of an antibiotic.

label: acute infectious disease course
definition: An infectious disease course that begins soon after infection is established and progresses rapidly to severe stages.

label: chronic infectious disease course
definition: An infectious disease course that unfolds over a long period of time.

label: colony
definition: An organism population persisting in a site it has colonized.

label: diseased population
definition: An organism population in whose members an infectious disease is being realized.

label: immune population
definition: An organism population whose members have acquired immunity to an infectious agent.

label: infected population
definition: An organism population whose members have an infection.

label: infectious agent population
definition: An organism population whose members each have an infectious disposition.

label: normal resident microbiota population
definition: An organism population whose members are participating in non-parasitic symbiosis with a particular host.

label: susceptible population
definition: An organism population whose members are not infected with an infectious agent and who lack immunity to the infectious agent.

label: pathogen host
definition: An organism bearing a pathogen host role.

label: symptomatic host of infectious agent
definition: An organism who is host to an infectious agent and has symptoms of the infectious disease associated with the infectious agent

label: infectious agent host
definition: An organism bearing an infectious agent host role.

label: long-term non-progressing infectious disease course
definition: A chronic infectious disease course that does not progress to severe stages for a long period of time.

label: infectious agent colony
definition: A colony whose members are infectious agents.

label: pathogen host role
definition: A host role borne by an organism in virtue of the fact that its extended organism contains a pathogen.

label: ASFIS
definition: ASFIS is a database curated by the United Nations Food And Agriculture Organization (FAO) Fisheries and Aquaculture Statistics and Information Branch (FIPS). It contains over 12,700 species items selected according to their interest or relation to fisheries and aquaculture.

label: EcoLexicon
definition: EcoLexicon is a terminological resource developed by the LexiCon Research Group at the University of Granada.

label: Geonames
definition: The GeoNames geographical database covers all countries and contains over eleven million placenames that are available for download free of charge.

label: ITIS
definition: The Integrated Taxonomic Information System (ITIS) contains authoritative taxonomic information on plants, animals, fungi, and microbes of North America and the world.

label: MESH
definition: MeSH is the National Library of Medicine's controlled vocabulary thesaurus. It consists of sets of terms naming descriptors in a hierarchical structure that permits searching at various levels of specificity.

label: NCIT
definition: The National Cancer Institute Thesaurus (NCIt) provides reference terminology for many NCI and other systems. It covers vocabulary for clinical care, translational and basic research, and public information and administrative activities.

label: NIFSTD
definition: The NIFSTD ontology of the Neuroscience Information Framework is composed of a collection of OWL modules with separate modules covering major domains of neuroscience: anatomy, cell, subcellular, molecule, organism, function and dysfunction.

label: PubMed
definition: PubMed comprises more than 26 million citations for biomedical literature from MEDLINE, life science journals, and online books. Citations may include links to full-text content from PubMed Central and publisher web sites.

label: SNOMEDCT
definition: SNOMED CT is a large clinical health terminology product owned and distributed by SNOMED International.

label: Wikipedia
definition: Wikipedia is a free online encyclopedia that aims to allow anyone to edit articles.

label: pathological anatomical entity
definition: Anatomically located instance of pathological response or entity.

label: healing and repair structure
definition: Physical entity or structure associated with normal or abnormal tissue healing or repair following extrinsic or intrinsic damage.

label: Mus musculus domesticus x M. m. molossinus
Mus musculus musculus x M. m. castaneus
Mus musculus musculus x M. m. domesticus
Salmonella enterica subsp. enterica serovar Enteritidis
Salmonella enterica subsp. enterica serovar Hadar
Salmonella enterica subsp. enterica serovar Heidelberg
Salmonella enterica subsp. enterica serovar Infantis
Salmonella enterica subsp. enterica serovar Javiana
Salmonella enterica subsp. enterica serovar Newport
Salmonella enterica subsp. enterica serovar Stanley
Salmonella enterica subsp. enterica serovar Typhimurium
Salmonella enterica subsp. enterica serovar Virchow
Country Code
definition: An alphanumeric system designed to identify countries. The ISO 3166 standard includes a two letter representation, a three letter representation, and a 3 number representation. The last two are identical to the UN system. The US State Department system maintains a separate two letter representation code set.

label: ANSI INCITS 38
definition: Information Technology – Codes For The Identification Of The States And Equivalent Areas Within The United States, Puerto Rico, And The Insular Areas

label: Darwin Core Terms
definition: The Darwin Core is body of standards. It includes a glossary of terms (in other contexts these might be called properties, elements, fields, columns, attributes, or concepts) intended to facilitate the sharing of information about biological diversity by providing reference definitions, examples, and commentaries.

label: EBI European Nucleotide Archive Webin
definition: The European Nucleotide Archive (ENA) provides a comprehensive record of the world's nucleotide sequencing information, covering raw sequencing data, sequence assembly information and functional annotation. Webin is an ENA interface and standard for sequence submissions.

label: Genomic Standards Consortium (GSC) standard
definition: A Genomic Standards Consortium standard is an international, community-driven standard to facilitate  genomic data integration, discovery and comparison.

label: I2B2 Data Protection role standard
definition: The I2B2 Workbench Data Protection role standard is a standard which names and lists data protection roles between a user and a given dataset that define the level of detail a user has access to.

label: INSDC standard
definition: The International Nucleotide Sequence Database Collaboration (INSDC) is a long-standing foundational initiative that operates between DDBJ, EMBL-EBI and NCBI. INSDC covers the spectrum of data raw reads, though alignments and assemblies to functional annotation, enriched with contextual information relating to samples and experimental configurations.

label: ISO3166-1
definition: ISO 3166-1 is part of the ISO 3166 standard published by the International Organization for Standardization (ISO), and defines codes for the names of countries, dependent territories, and special areas of geographical interest.

label: ISO3166-2
definition: ISO 3166-2 is part of the ISO 3166 standard published by the International Organization for Standardization (ISO), and defines codes for identifying the principal subdivisions (e.g., provinces or states) of all countries coded in ISO 3166-1.

label: NCBI standard
definition: The National Center for Biotechnology Information offers standards for submitting genomic project data to their BioProject and BioSample databases.

label: NHS standard
definition: United Kingdom National Health Service trusts, boards, etc. have some terminology in common for public disclosure of patient health conditions.

label: public health data standard
definition: A data standard related to public health research and service delivery.

label: the Global Microbial Identifier Minimum Data for Matching (MDM) Standard
definition: the Global Microbial Identifier "Minimum data for Matching" (MDM) standard is a standard that defines essential contextual data fields to be included in genomic sequence repository records.

label: National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Disease standard
definition: NIAID provides The GSCID/BRC Project and Sample Application Standard. It is designed to capture standardized human pathogen and vector sequencing metadata to support epidemiologic and genotype-phenotype association studies for human infectious diseases.

label: Stx toxin subtype
definition: shiga toxin variant

label: Stx toxin type
definition: pathogenic shiga toxin produced by STEC E. coli

label: Stx1 Toxin PCR result
definition: qPCR result of STX1 gene amplification

label: Stx1 cell culture level
definition: level of stx toxin derived tissue culture toxicity

label: Stx2 Toxin PCR result
definition: qPCR result of STX2 gene amplification

label: Stx2 cell culture level
definition: level of stx toxin derived tissue culture toxicity

label: Children 2-11 Years Old
definition: A person from 2 years to 11 years of age.

label: School Age Child
definition: A child between the ages of five and twelve years.

label: Toddler
definition: A child that is approximately between 12 and 18 months of age.

label: Extremely Preterm Infant
definition: A newborn infant less than 28 weeks, 0 days gestational age.

label: Healthy Preterm Newborn
definition: A healthy newborn whose only diagnoses are those related to prematurity. (NIAID)

label: Healthy Term Newborn
definition: AGA infant delivered after full 37 weeks gestation whose 5 minute Apgar score was above 7, has no major congenital anomalies and was discharged home with mother without any additional diagnoses except for physiologic hyperbilirubinemia. (NIAID)

label: Late Preterm Infant
definition: A newborn infant greater than or equal to 34 weeks, 0 days and less than 37 weeks, 0 days gestational age.

label: Moderate to Late Preterm Infant
definition: A baby born alive with a gestational age between 32 to less than 37 weeks.

label: Postterm Infant
definition: A newborn infant greater than or equal to 42 weeks, 0 days gestational age.

label: Preterm Infant
definition: A newborn infant less than 37 weeks, 0 days gestational age.

label: Term Infant
definition: A newborn infant greater than or equal to 37 weeks, 0 days and less than or equal to 41 weeks, 6 days gestational age.

label: Very Preterm Infant
definition: A newborn infant greater than 28 weeks, 0 days and less than 34 weeks, 0 days.

label: Adult 18-65 Years Old
definition: A person from 18 years to 65 years of age.

label: Middle Adult
definition: A person between young adult and elderly, approximately 40-60 years of age.

label: Young Adult
definition: An indefinite term describing a person who has reached sexual maturity but whose character and personality are still developing. In psychology this generally covers the age range of 20-40.

label: surface wipe
definition: A surface wipe is a type of swab designed to collect specimen material from some envirronmental surface using a fabric or other material.

label: Alpha-2 Country Code
definition: The two-letter country codes specified by the ISO 3166-1 country code standard.

label: Alpha-3 Country Code
definition: The three-letter country codes specified by the ISO 3166-1 country code standard.

label: Numeric Country Code
definition: The numeric, three-digit country codes specified by the ISO 3166-1 country code standard.

label: Adolescent
definition: A juvenile between the onset of puberty and maturity; in the state of development between puberty and maturity.

label: Adult
definition: A human who has reached reproductive age.

label: Child
definition: A person who is not yet an adult. The specific cut-off age will vary by purpose.

label: Elderly
definition: An age group comprised by people 65 years of age and older.

label: In Utero
definition: The period of time during which the embryo or fetus is present in the uterus of the female. Also describes the location of the embryo or fetus as being in the uterus in contrast to outside the uterus (ex utero).

label: Infant And Toddler
definition: A person from 28 days to 23 months of age.

label: Youth
definition: The time of life between childhood and maturity.  This period overlaps with adolescence.

label: First Name
definition: A word or group of words indicating a person's first (personal or given) name; the name that precedes the surname.

label: Last Name
definition: A word or group of words indicating a person's last (family) name.

label: Login Name
definition: The account name used by a person to access a computer system.

label: Maiden Name
definition: A woman's surname before marriage.

label: Pseudonym
definition: A fictitious name used when the person performs a particular social role.

label: Subject Name
definition: The name of the individual of interest.

label: Zip Code
definition: A system designed to expedite the sorting and delivery of mail by assigning a series of numbers to each delivery area in the United States.  Also used to refer to any individual delivery area code.

label: Canada postal code
definition: A Canadian postal code is a postal code that pertains to a geographic region of Canada.

label: Newborn
definition: An infant during the first month after birth.

label: Accidental Death
definition: An indication that the subject's death was due to a mishap.

label: Brain Death
definition: Irreversible absence of cortical and brain stem functioning.

label: Cancer-Related Death
definition: A death attributed to the progression of a cancer-related pathologic condition.

label: Cardiac Death
definition: The cessation of life due to heart abnormalities or disease.

label: Death During, or within 90 Days of, Index Hospital Admission
definition: An indication that death occurred on or within 90 days of a patient's initial admission to a hospital.

label: Death Related to Adverse Event
definition: The termination of life associated with an adverse event.

label: Death by Natural Cause
definition: Death that is attributed to the progression of a disease or pre-existing condition, and which is not attributable to any outside action or force.

label: Died in a Medical Facility
definition: The patient died while in a medical center such as a hospital, skilled nursing facility (SNF), intermediate care facility (ICF), or a freestanding hospice center. (ACC)

label: Early Intrauterine Death
definition: A death of the embryo occurring inside the uterus.

label: Intrauterine Fetal Death
definition: Death of a fetus after 10 weeks gestation.

label: Late Intrauterine Death
definition: A death of the fetus occurring inside the uterus.

label: Non-Cancer Related Death
definition: A death attributed to any cause other than the progression of a cancer-related pathologic condition.

label: Pediatric Death
definition: Death of a fetus, neonate, or patient 20 years or younger.

label: Presumed Dead
definition: The status of an individual who in all likelihood is not living, but has not been officially declared dead.

label: Pronounced Dead
definition: The status of an individual is officially declared not living by an authority.

label: Stillbirth
definition: A fetus of at least 20 weeks gestation, or of a birth weight of at least 350 grams if the gestational age is unknown, that is born without signs of life at the time of delivery, and with an Apgar score of zero at both one and five minutes.

label: Sudden Death
definition: An unexpected death without warning.

label: Unscheduled Death
definition: The cessation of life at an unplanned time.

label: Cryovial
definition: A vial used to store specimens in a cryopreservative at very low temperatures.

label: Glass Vial
definition: A glass container designed for use with parenteral drug products.

label: Plastic Vial
definition: A plastic container designed for use with parenteral drug products.

label: Job Title
definition: A local name for an individual's occupation.

label: Person Name
definition: A word or group of words indicating the identity of a person usually consisting of a first (personal) name and a last (family) name with an optional middle name. In some cultural traditions the family name comes first.

label: Organization Name
definition: A textual identifier for an organization.

label: Bag
definition: A sac or pouch.

label: Bottle
definition: A vessel with a narrow neck designed to accept a specific closure.

label: Vial
definition: A small, often stoppered glass or plastic bottle for holding fluids.

label: Induction Death
definition: Death of the patient due to the toxic side effects of induction therapy.

label: Antepartum Stillbirth
definition: Fetal death greater than or equal to 20 weeks of gestation prior to labor with Apgar scores of 0 at 1 minute, 5 minutes and beyond.

label: Early Stillbirth
definition: Delivery of a dead fetus greater than 22 weeks but less than 28 weeks gestational age, and/or whose birth weight is greater than 500 grams but less than 1,000 grams.

label: Intrapartum Stillbirth
definition: Fetal death greater than or equal to 20 weeks of gestation during labor with Apgar scores of 0 at 1 minute, 5 minutes and beyond.

label: Late Stillbirth
definition: Delivery of a dead fetus greater than 28 weeks gestational age and/or greater than 1,000 grams birth weight.

label: Embryo
definition: An organism in its initial stage of development following fertilization. The human embryonic period lasts approximately eight weeks, during which time organogenesis takes place.

label: Fetus
definition: An unborn or unhatched vertebrate in the later stages of development showing the main recognizable features of the mature being.

label: Infant
definition: A young child between one month and two years of age.

label: Early Fetal Death
definition: Death of a fetus at 10 weeks, 0 days to 15 weeks, 6 days of gestation.

label: Late Fetal Death
definition: Death of a fetus at 16 weeks, 0 days to 19 weeks, 6 days of gestation.

label: Non-Sudden Cardiac Death
definition: An expected natural death from a cardiac cause. This condition usually occurs in persons with pre-existing cardiac abnormalities or disease.

label: Sudden Cardiac Death
definition: An unexpected natural death from a cardiac cause within a short time period from the onset of symptoms.

label: Neonatal Death
definition: Death of a live newborn during the first 28 days of life.

label: Perinatal Mortality
definition: Fetal or infant death during the period of time that includes the antepartum, intrapartum, and neonatal stages.

label: Post Neonatal Death
definition: Death between 28 days and 1 year of life.

label: Sudden Unexplained Death in Childhood
definition: Unexpected death of a child over one year of age, which remains unexplained when all known and possible causes of death have been ruled out.

label: subject organism
definition: An investigative subject which is an organism.

label: Early Neonatal Death
definition: Death of a live newborn during the first 7 days of life.

label: Late Neonatal Death
definition: Death of live newborn between 7and 27 days after birth.

label: Post-Natal Death at 16-20 Weeks Gestation
definition: A fetus of 16-20 weeks gestational age that shows signs of life at birth but dies after delivery.

label: Sudden Infant Death Syndrome
definition: Unexpected death in infancy which remains unexplained following autopsy, review of the medical history, and investigation of the death circumstances and death scene.

label: Sudden Unexplained Infant Death
definition: Unexpected death of an infant less than one year of age, whose cause of death is not immediately obvious prior to investigation.

label: Very Early Neonatal Death
definition: Death of a live newborn during the first 24 hours of life

label: populated place, Canada
definition: A populated place. A city in Alberta, Canada. Brooks was incorporated as a village on 1910-07-14, and as a town on 1911-09-08. It became a city on 2005-09-01 and is located 168 km east of Calgary on the Trans-Canada Highway and 10 km east of Highway 36.

label: populated place, Democratic Republic of Congo
populated place, Republic of South Africa
populated place, Zambia
definition: A small town and administrative district in the Western Province of Zambia, on the plains west of the Zambezi River and the Barotse Floodplain, about 70 km from the border with Angola.

label: populated place, contiguous United States of America
Antimicrobial Dose Dependent Susceptibility Result
definition: A microbial susceptibility test result in which the growth of microorganisms may be inhibited when higher than normal dosages of an antimicrobial agent are used and maximal possible blood concentration of the antimicrobial agent is achieved.

label: Antimicrobial Intermediate Susceptibility Result (deprecated)
definition: A microbial susceptibility test result in which the growth of microorganisms may be inhibited by the usually achievable concentrations of antimicrobial agent when the recommended dosage is used for the site of infection. The response rates may be lower than for susceptible isolates.

label: Antimicrobial Nonsusceptibility Result (deprecated)
definition: A microbial susceptibility test result in which the growth of microorganisms is not inhibited by the usually achievable concentrations of antimicrobial agent when the recommended dosage is used for the site of infection. This category may be applied to new antimicrobial agents for which no resistant microorganisms have been encountered at the time the initial interpretive criteria are determined. Microorganisms that test with an MIC above or a zone measurement below the susceptible interpretive criteria may be designated as nonsusceptible. A designation of nonsusceptible does not necessarily mean that a resistance mechanism(s) exists in the microorganism.

label: Antimicrobial Resistance Result (deprecated)
definition: A microbial susceptibility test result in which the growth of microorganisms is not inhibited by the usually achievable concentrations of antimicrobial agent with normal dosage, or microorganisms demonstrate minimum inhibitory concentrations (MIC) or zone diameters that fall in the range where specific microbial resistance mechanisms are likely in effect, or clinical efficacy of the agent against the microorganism has not been reliably shown in treatment studies.

label: Antimicrobial Susceptibility Result (deprecated)
definition: A microbial susceptibility test result in which the growth of microorganisms is inhibited by the usually achievable concentrations of antimicrobial agent when the recommended dosage is used for the site of infection.

label: antibiotic resistance not defined
definition: A not defined resistance indicates that an isolate was not tested against a given antibiotic, or the result of the test was inconclusive.

label: Agar Dilution Method
definition: A method to determine microbial susceptibility to antibiotics in which test bacteria is inoculated onto agar plates with serial dilutions of know quantities of antibiotics. The minimum inhibitory concentration of antibiotic is assessed.

label: broth dilution method
definition: The microbial species are inoculated in liquid growth medium containing incremental dilutions (usually 2-fold) of the antimicrobial agent.

label: diffusion method
definition: Microbial species are inoculated in a growth medium onto which antimicrobial agents are transferred by diffusion.

label: Epsilometry
definition: A method to determine microbial susceptibility to antibiotics in which a plastic strip impregnated with the antibiotic of interest is placed on an agar plate that has been inoculated with bacteria. The antibiotic diffuses from the strip producing a concentration gradient of drug on the agar. The point at which the elliptical shaped area of growth inhibition meets the strip is the minimum inhibitory concentration of the drug of interest.

label: Unincorporated Territory (USA)
definition: An area of the United States of America under United States jurisdiction, to which Congress has determined that only select parts of the United States of America Constitution apply.

label: material processing
definition: A planned process which results in physical changes in a specified input material

label: service
definition: A planned process in which a service provider performs a task (i.e. a planned process) for a service consumer.

label: treatment
definition: A processual entity whose completion is hypothesized (by a healthcare provider) to alleviate the signs and symptoms associated with a disorder

label: assay
definition: A planned process with the objective to produce information about the material entity that is the evaluant, by physically examining it or its proxies.

label: counting
definition: The planned process of finding the number of elements in a finite set of objects.

label: data transformation
definition: A planned process that produces output data from input data.

label: investigation
definition: a planned process that consists of parts: planning, study design execution, documentation and which produce conclusion(s).

label: population survey
definition: A planned process involving counting numbers of a organism population, possibly including counting sub-populations fulfilling specific criteria.

label: specimen collection process
definition: A planned process with the objective of collecting a specimen.

label: device
definition: A material entity that is designed to perform a function in a scientific investigation, but is not a reagent.

label: culture medium
definition: a processed material that provides the needed nourishment for microorganisms or cells grown in vitro.

label: reagent
definition: A biological or chemical entity that bears a reagent role in virtue of it being intended for application in a scientific technique  to participate in (or have molecular parts that participate in) a chemical reaction that facilitates the generation of data about some distinct entity, or the generation of some distinct material specified output.

label: molecular assay
definition: An assay that generates data about the presence, abundance, structure, function, or activity of biological molecules, or a process that occurs at a molecular level of granularity.

label: real time polymerase chain reaction assay
definition: An assay, based on the PCR, that amplifies and simultaneously quantifies a specific DNA molecule based on the use of complementary probes/primers. It enables both detection and quantification (as absolute number of copies or relative amount when normalized to DNA input or additional normalizing genes) of one or more specific sequences in a DNA sample.

label: sequencing assay
definition: An assay the uses chemical or biochemical means to infer the sequence of a biomaterial

label: isolation medium
definition: An isolation medium is a culture medium which has the disposition to encourage growth of particular bacteria to the exclusion of others in the same growth environment.

label: separation method
definition: A method that results in the separation of two or more components according to some property.

label: material component separation
definition: a material processing in which components of an input material become segregated in space

label: material sample role
definition: A material sample role is a specimen role borne by a material entity that is the output of a material sampling process.

label: ethnic group
definition: A group of people with a common cultural heritage that sets them apart from others in a variety of social relationships. (MSH); A social group characterized by a distinctive social and cultural tradition maintained from generation to generation, a common history and origin and a sense of identification with the group; members of the group have distinctive features in their way of life, shared experiences and often a common genetic heritage; these features may be reflected in their experience of health and disease. (NCI); Ethnicity - an arbitrary classification of the social group a person belongs to, and either identifies with or is identified with by others, as a result of a complex of cultural, biological, geographical and other factors such as linguistic, dietary and religion traditions; ancestry, background, allegiance, or association; and physical characteristics traditionally associated with race. Increasingly the concept is used synonymously with race but this use trend has a pragmatic basis rather than scientific. (NCI); The concept of ethnic origin is an attempt to classify people, not according to their current ethnicity, but according to where their ancestors came from. Ethnic origin has become a popular classification in statistics, where the concept of race has been largely discarded. (from Wikipedia) (NCI); a group of people with a common cultural heritage that sets them apart from others in a variety of social relationships. (CSP)

label: Repository
definition: A facility where items can be deposited for storage or safekeeping.

label: grant agency
definition: An organization that provides funding support for projects such as investigations.

label: molecular analysis facility organization
definition: An organization that provides molecular analysis service.

label: organization of sequencing facility contact person
definition: An organization that is the affiliation of the contact representative at the sequencing facility

label: organization of specimen collector
definition: An organization that is the affiliation of the person collecting the specimen

label: specimen processing organization type
definition: An organization related to the collection, isolate production, sequencing or storage of specimen material or data.

label: specimen repository organization
definition: An organization that provides a service to store and distribute specimens

label: organization of specimen provider principal investigator
definition: An organization that is the affiliation of the principal investigator providing the specimens for the investigation

label: next generation DNA sequencing
definition: A DNA sequencing technique that became commercially available in 2004 and is used by specific commercial platforms that embody a complex interplay of enzymology, chemistry, high-resolution optics, hardware, and software engineering. These instruments allow highly streamlined sample preparation steps prior to DNA sequencing, which provides a significant time savings and a minimal requirement for associated equipment in comparison to the highly automated, multistep pipelines necessary for clone-based high-throughput sequencing. Each technology amplifies single strands of a fragment library and perform sequencing reactions on the amplified strands. The fragment libraries are obtained by annealing platform-specific linkers to blunt-ended fragments generated directly from a genome or DNA source of interest. Because the presence of adapter sequences means that the molecules then can be selectively amplified by PCR, and no bacterial cloning step is required to amplify the genomic fragment in a bacterial intermediate as is done in traditional sequencing approaches.

label: Data Standard
definition: A statement that defines conventions, guidelines, characteristics or methods for consistent data handling to facilitate exchange or processing of the data. This set of criteria are reviewed by and agreed upon by the user community or a governing body before they are released and adopted for use.

label: data standard component
definition: A data standard component is a utility class used to organize some of the draft or finalized data representational model standards related components that are part of one or more standards.

label: draft data standard
definition: The 'draft data standard' class contains draft representations of formal or defacto third party standards and related components.  These representations may have been crafted without any involvement of related standards issuers and so no guarantee can be provided about their currency, accuracy or veracity.

label: field specification
definition: A field specification is the specification of a data field used in a data standard or database table. This includes at least a database field name, and optionally display name, description, and data type (binary blob, numeric, categorical, textual or cross-reference).

label: collecting specimen from organism
definition: a process with the objective to obtain a material entity that was part of an organism for potential future use in an investigation

label: environmental material collection process
definition: environmental_material_collection is an acquisition where an object is taken from an environment and put into a storage container. Roles include, environment, thing collected, container, acquirer.

label: reproduction number
definition: The average value of transmissions of the infectious agent from one infected organism to another, resulting in an infection.

label: SOLiD 3 Plus System
definition: A DNA sequencer which is manufacted by the Applied Biosystems corporation. Built upon SOLiD sequencing technology, the machine generates greater than 1 billion mappable reads per run.

label: SOLiD 4 System
definition: An AB SOLid System which is manufacted by the Applied Biosystems corporation. Built upon SOLiD sequencing technology, the machine generates greater than 1 billion mappable reads per run.

label: Genome Analyzer IIe
definition: An Illumina Genome Analyzer II which is manufactured by the Illumina corporation. It supports sequencing of single, long or short insert paired end clone libraries relying on sequencing by synthesis technology. The Genome Analyzer IIe makes industry-leading next-generation sequencing technology accessible to more laboratories.

label: Genome Analyzer IIx
definition: An Illumina Genome Analyzer II which is manufactured by the Illumina corporation. It supports sequencing of single, long or short insert paired end clone libraries relying on sequencing by synthesis technology. The Genome Analyzer IIx is the most widely adopted next-generation sequencing platform and proven and published across the broadest range of research applications.

label: massively parallel signature sequencing
definition: A DNA sequencing by ligation technique that involves a bead-based method that uses a complex approach of adapter ligation followed by adapter decoding, reading the sequence in increments of four nucleotides; this method made it susceptible to sequence-specific bias or loss of specific sequences.

label: Solexa sequencing
definition: is a DNA sequencing which allows sequence identification by relying on use of DNA polymerase and reversible terminator. The methods requires immobilization of genomic DNA fragment onto a surface and a specific clonal amplification step known as bridge PCR. Reliance on reversible terminator allow cycles of DNA chain extension by DNA polymerase and imaging without the need of electrophoretic separation of newly synthesized DNA fragment as with Sanger sequencing.

label: chain termination sequencing
definition: is a DNA sequencing which rely on the use of dideoxynucleotides used in 4 distinct sequencing reaction on the same DNA sample. The dideoxynucleotides, once incorporated in the complementary DNA strand being synthesized by the DNA polymerase prevent any further chain elongation. The newly generated sequences are resolved on a polyacrylamide gel using electrophoresis and labels (either fluorochrome or radioactivity) are used to determine the nucleotide present at a given position

label: cycle sequencing
definition: A DNA sequencing by synthesis technique used to increase the sensitivity of the DNA sequencing process and permits the use of very small amounts of DNA starting material. This is accomplished by using a temperature cycling process similar to that employed in the polymerase chain reaction.

label: DNA sequencer
definition: A DNA sequencer is an instrument that determines the order of deoxynucleotides in deoxyribonucleic acid sequences.

label: material supplier role
definition: a role realized through the process of supplying materials such as animal subjects, reagents or other materials used in an investigation.

label: measurement device
definition: A device in which a measure function inheres.

label: needle
definition: a needle is a sharp, hollow device used to penetrate tissue or soft material. When attached to a syringe. it allows delivery of a specific volume of liquid or gaseous mixture.

label: subject identifier
definition: A subject identifier is an identifier of a subject organism within the context of a particular investigation, study, or specimen extraction event.

label: age since birth measurement datum
definition: An age measurement datum that is the result of the measurement of the age of an organism since birth, the process of emergence and separation of offspring from the mother.

label: subject age
definition: A subject age is the age since birth of a given organism that is involved in an investigation or study at a given time.

label: material service
definition: A service which has a material entity as specified input and/or specified output.

label: census reference date
