definition: A information content entity that specifies the date of a census.

label: material storage service
definition: A storage service in which a service consumer provides some material as input which a service provider stores and returns as output.

label: material analysis service
definition: A service in which a service consumer provides some input material and a service provider performs some analysis of this material to generate data that is returned to the service consumer.

label: material maintenance service
definition: A material processing service in which a service provider makes physical modifications to a specified input material, such that at least one of the specified outputs of this process is a modified version of a specified input material.

label: BCCDC sample ID
definition: A BCCDC sample ID is is a sample identifier assigned by the British Columbia Centre for Disease Control which is unique within that agency.

label: NCBI specimen voucher
definition: The NCBI specimen voucher is an identifier composed of “institution code:collection code:specimen id” parts. In addition to a specimen identifier, it includes an institution-code (and optional collection-code) taken from a controlled vocabulary maintained by the INSDC that denotes the museum or herbarium collection where the specimen resides.

label: specimen identifier assigned by sequencing facility
definition: A specimen identifier which is assigned by a sequencing facility

label: specimen identifier assigned by specimen repository
definition: A specimen identifier which is assigned by a specimen repository

label: National Laboratory for Enteric Pathogens Identifier
definition: An NLEP ID is a unique identifier code for a sample registered with the Canadian "National Laboratory for Enteric Pathogens" (NLEP)

label: phenotypic observation data from specimen
definition: phenotypic descriptive data.

label: proteome data derived from specimen
definition: Proteome material is protein or peptide sequences.

label: purified chromosome from specimen
definition: Purified chromosome: one or more chromosomes or replicons were experimentally purified.

label: other material derived from specimen
definition: Other: specify the material that was used.

label: reagent derived material from specimen
definition: Reagent: material studied was obtained by chemical reaction, precipitation.

label: transcriptome data from specimen
definition: Transcriptome: transcript and/or expression data.

label: synthetic sample scope
definition: A synthetic sample scope involves a sample synthesized in a laboratory.

label: environment sample scope
definition: An environment sample scope indicates that the species content of the sample is not known. Generally, nucleic acid is directly isolated from an environmental sample for analysis. This is used for metagenome studies.

label: monoisolate sample scope
definition: A monoisolate sample scope involves specimens from a single animal, cultured cell-line, inbred population, or possibly a heterogeneous population when a single genome assembly is generated from a pooled sample because multiple individuals are needed to collect enough material and an inbred line is not available; however, this situation is not preferred.

label: multiisolate sample scope
definition: A multiisolate sample scope contains multiple individuals that represent distinct specimen collections, a population (representative of a species).

label: multispecies sample scope
definition: A multi-species sample scope involves a sample representing multiple species.

label: other specimen scope
definition: Other: specify the sample scope that was used.

label: analysis objective
definition: An "analysis project objective" indicates there was an other analysis not otherwise indicated, includes submission of BAM files.

label: sequence annotation objective
definition: sequence annotation data

label: assembly objective
definition: submission of genome assembly (AGP data)

label: epigenetic markers objective
definition: DNA methylation, histone modification, chromatin accessibility datasets

label: transcript or protein expression objective
definition: Expression: assays of transcript or protein existence or abundance

label: mapping objective
definition: Maps: non-sequence based map data; e.g., genetic, radiation hybrid, cytogenetic, etc.

label: other project objective
definition: Other project objective: specify an objective not listed above

label: phenotype project objective
definition: Phenotype: phenotypic measurements for submission to dbGaP

label: raw sequence read objective
definition: A raw sequence reads project objective has the goal of submission of raw reads to SRA or Trace repositories

label: sequence project objective
definition: A sequence project objective has a goal of submission of sequence data to standard archival sequence databases (yielding accession.version identifiers; e.g., whole genome shotgun, cDNA sequences, transcript shotgun assemblies)

label: sequence variation project objective
definition: Variation: identification of sequence variation data for submission to dbSNP or dbVAR

label: array project method
definition: select Array if that is the primary method and no sequence data is submitted

label: mass spectrometry project method
definition: select Mass Spectrometry if that is the primary method

label: other project method
definition: specify the project method

label: other capture type
definition: other capture type is a free text description provided to indicate a target capture specification not covered by the other types.

label: clone end data capture
definition: CloneEnds: capturing clone end data.

label: exome specific data capture
definition: Exome: capturing exon-specific data.

label: random survey data capture
definition: sequences generated from a random sampling of the collected sample; not intended to be comprehensive sampling of the material

label: Targeted Locus Loci data capture
definition: TargetedLocusLoci: capturing specific loci (gene, genomic region, bar code standard).

label: whole genomic data capture
definition: Whole: the project makes use of the whole sample material (most common case). Use this for whole genome sequencing studies, transcriptome studies that are not targeting specific loci, epigenetic studies of a genome, and metagenomes or unbiased transcriptome studies of metagenomes.

label: DNA sequencing service
definition: A DNA sequencing  process provided as a service - which is the realization of some DNA sequencing in which the service provider role is realized.

label: region, province, state or territory specification
specimen extraction site specification
definition: A specification for a geographic location that a specimen was extracted or collected at.

label: subject disease specification
definition: Name of disease in a subject that is related to a given investigation, study and/or specimen.

label: subject organism (host) taxonomic species
definition: The species of the host organism from which a specimen (pathogen) organism was obtained. Use the full taxonomic name, eg, "Homo sapiens".

label: subject sex specification
definition: A subject sex is the phenotypic sex of given subject (human or animal) related to a given investigation, study, and/or specimen.

label: travel destination specification
definition: A travel destination is a destination city (or populated place of some scale) which a given human has travelled to on a particular trip.

label: MIC diffusion measurement specification
definition: A MIC test measurement resulting from a laboratory diffusion method.

label: MIC dilution measurement specification
definition: A MIC test measurement resulting from a laboratory dilution method.

label: latitude specification (ISO 6709)
definition: A decimal latitude measurement in degrees in conformance with the ISO 6709 standard.

label: longitude specification (ISO 6709)
definition: A decimal longitude measurement in degrees in conformance with the ISO 6709 standard.

label: boolean value specification
definition: A boolean value specification indicates a presence (true value) or absence (false value) of a given feature.

label: categorical value specification
definition: A value specification that is specifies one category out of a fixed number of nominal categories

label: scalar value specification
definition: A value specification that consists of two parts: a numeral and a unit label

label: sequencing facility organization
definition: An organization that provides sequence determination service

label: adapter-sequence trimming
definition: A data transformation in which adapter sequences at the end of a molecular sequence are cut (removed).

label: Archaea
definition: The Archaea constitute a domain and kingdom of single-celled microorganisms

label: susceptible organism
definition: An organism that is not infected with an infectious agent and lacks protective immunity to the infectious agent.

label: host
definition: An organism bearing a host role.

label: infectious agent
definition: is a material entity bearing the disposition to infect an organism

label: infectious agent vector
definition: An organism bearing an infectious agent vector role.

label: specimen provider principal investigator
definition: A person who is a principal investigator and provides the specimen

label: Isolate
definition: A specific individual microbe and its genetically identical progeny separated on a single occasion from a sample taken from a host or culture system.

label: rinse
definition: Rinse is the liquid output of rinsing plant, animal or other material with liquid with the objective of extracting specimen material from that liquid.

label: specimen from organism
definition: A specimen that derives from an anatomical part or substance arising from an organism. Examples of tissue specimen include tissue, organ, physiological system, blood, or body location (arm).

label: sequence trimming
definition: A data transformation in which subsequences of a molecular sequence are cut (removed).

label: nucleic acid extraction
definition: a material separation to recover the nucleic acid fraction of an input material

label: ABI 377 automated sequencer
definition: is a DNA sequencer which is manufactured by Applied Biosystems corporation (formerly Perkin-Elmer). It allows automated chain termination DNA sequencing. It has part polyacrylamide gel electrophoresis system and a laser -based detection system to detect fluorescence intensity emitted by the dyes attached to the dideoxyterminator nucleotides or to the primers.

label: Li-Cor 4300 DNA Analysis System
definition: is a DNA sequencer which is manufactured by Li-Cor corporation and enable automated chain termination based DNA sequencing

label: Illumina Genome Analyzer
definition: A DNA sequencer manufactured by Solexa as one of its first sequencer lines, launched in 2006, and capable of sequencing 1 gigabase (Gb) of data in a single run.

label: Illumina HiSeq X Ten
definition: A DNA sequencer that consists of a set of 10 HiSeq X Sequencing Systems.

label: Amniocentesis
definition: A prenatal diagnostic procedure in which a small sample of amniotic fluid is removed from the uterus by a needle inserted into the abdomen. This procedure is used to detect various genetic abnormalities in the fetus and/or the sex of the fetus.

label: Aspiration
definition: Procedure using suction, usually with a thin needle and syringe, to remove bodily fluid or tissue.

label: Biopsy
definition: The removal of tissue specimens or fluid from the living body for microscopic examination, performed to establish a diagnosis.

label: Phlebotomy
definition: The collection of blood from a vein, most commonly via needle venipuncture.

label: exudate collection
definition: The process of collecting bodily fluids that have been discharged from blood vessels usually arising from inflammation or injury.

label: feces collection
definition: The process of collecting a portion of feces from an organism.

label: lavage
definition: A protocol application to separate cells and/or cellular secretions from an anatomical space by the introduction and removal of fluid

label: rinsing for specimen collection
definition: The process of removal and collection of specimen material from the surface of an entity by washing, or a similar application of fluids.

label: sputum collection
definition: The process of collecting a portion of urine from an organism.

label: swabbing for specimen collection
definition: The process of collecting specimen material using a swab collection device.

label: vacuuming for specimen collection
definition: The removal or collection of specimen material through the use of suction.

label: necropsy
definition: A postmortem examination of the body of an animal to determine the cause of death or the character and extent of changes produced by disease. [database_cross_reference: Merriam-Webster:Merriam-Websters_Online_Dictionary--11th_Ed]

label: extraction
definition: A material separation in which a desired component of an input material is separated from the remainder

label: bronchoalveolar lavage (BAL)
definition: A technique by which cells and fluid from bronchioles and lung alveoli are removed for diagnosis of disease or evaluation of treatment. A bronchoscope is wedged into a bronchus and sterile saline is pumped in and then removed along with the fluid and cells to be analyzed.

label: RNA sequencing assay
definition: An assay that determines the sequence of an RNA molecule.

label: DNA extraction
definition: A DNA extraction is a nucleic acid extraction where the desired output material is DNA.

label: allergy
definition: is a disease in which an abnormally strong inflammatory immune response is triggered against non-self entities, and the immune response has no protective effect

label: infectious disease
definition: is a disease caused by an infectious agent

label: infectious disease course
definition: A disease course that is the realization of an infectious disease.

label: Critical Illness
definition: Vital signs are unstable and not within normal limits. Patient may be unconscious. Indicators are unfavorable.

label: Pooled Sample
definition: A mix of specimens from multiple individuals representing multiple sex groups.

label: phenotypic sex
definition: Phenotypic sex refers to an individual's sex as determined by their internal and external genitalia, expression of secondary sex characteristics, and behavior.

label: size
definition: A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's physical magnitude.

label: amount
definition: The number of entities of this type that are part of the whole organism.

label: deviation(from_normal)
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the whether the bearer differs from normal or average.

label: abnormal
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's deviation from normal or average.

label: decreased quality
definition: A quality that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.

label: absent
definition: A quality denoting the lack of an entity.

label: present
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's existence.

label: 1-D extent
definition: A size quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's extension in one dimension.

label: 2-D extent
definition: A size quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's extension in two dimensions.

label: Castrated Female
definition: A female individual who has had her ovaries removed.

label: intact female
definition: Female quality of having complete, unaltered reproductive organs

label: castrated male
definition: Male quality of being incapable to reproduce because of functional loss of the testicles from surgical removal or chemical means.

label: intact male
definition: Male quality of having complete, unaltered reproductive organs.

label: pathological
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being abnormal and having a destructive effect on living tissue.

label: conductivity
definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to transmit of an entity through a medium.

label: mass density
definition: A physical quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of some influence is exerted by the bearer's mass per unit size.

label: proportionality to
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's magnitude in respect to a related entity.

label: strength
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's power or force.

label: temperature
definition: A physical quality of the thermal energy of a system.

label: decreased strength
definition: A strength which is relatively low.

label: decreased object quality
definition: A quality of an object that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.

label: molecular quality
definition: A quality which inheres in a molecular entity, a single molecule, atom, ion, radical etc.

label: morphology
definition: A quality of a single physical entity inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer's size or shape or structure.

label: organismal quality
definition: A quality that inheres in an entire organism or part of an organism.

label: physical quality
definition: A quality of a physical entity that exists through action of continuants at the physical level of organisation in relation to other entities.

label: dissolved
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's passing into solution.

label: soluble in
definition: A solubility quality inhering in a substance by virtue of the bearer's disposition to dissolve in a liquid.

label: depth
definition: A 1-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's downward or backward or inward dimenision.

label: length
definition: A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the distance between two points.

label: area
definition: A 2-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's two dimensional extent.

label: female pseudohermaphrodite
definition: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population by virtue of having internal reproductive organs of female and external sexual characteristics of male.

label: male pseudohermaphrodite
definition: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population by virtue of having internal reproductive organs of male and external sexual characteristics of female.

label: Intersex
definition: A person (one of unisexual specimens) who is born with genitalia and/or secondary sexual characteristics of indeterminate sex, or which combine features of both sexes.

label: female
definition: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population that only produces gametes that can be fertilised by male gametes.

label: hermaphrodite
definition: A biological sex quality inhering in an organism or a population with both male and female sexual organs in one individual.

label: male
definition: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population whose sex organs contain only male gametes.

label: pseudohermaphrodite
definition: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population by virtue of having internal reproductive organs of one sex and external sexual characteristics of the other sex.

label: neuter
definition: An animal that has had a substantial part of its reproductive organs removed surgically.

label: pooled male and female
definition: 'pooled male and female' is a categorical value used when the male and female categories or levels of a factor are combined. If used to describe a single organism, then the organism will be one or the other.

label: biological sex
definition: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ability to undergo sexual reproduction in order to differentiate the individuals or types involved.

label: solubility
definition: A molecular quality that inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of the bearer's disposition to dissolve in a liquid.

label: single-species collection of organisms
definition: A material entity that has as parts two or more organisms, viruses, or viroids of the same species and no members of any other species.

label: At-Risk Population
definition: Population groups with an increased likelihood of a disease or other health issue, eg smoking, drug use, teen pregnancy.

label: population of organisms
definition: A collection of organisms, all of the same species, that live in the same place.

label: baby shower
definition: A human social gathering at which the key participant is an expectant parent and other guests bring presents for the soon to be born baby.

label: human community event
definition: A human social event in which humans living in the same area or neighborhood gather to carry out activiites relevent to the people living in the area.

label: party
definition: A human social gathering in which the intention is to have a good time. Often the intention is to celebrate something like a birthday, anniversary, or holiday, but there is not always a purpose.

label: wedding
definition: A human social gathering at which two people are married. May include a legal or social ceremony.

label: achene fruit
definition: A fruit (PO:0009001) which develops from a carpel (PO:0009030) or gyneocium (PO:0009062) and at maturity comprises a dry exocarp (PO:0009085), a dry mesocarp (PO:0009087), and a dry endocarp (PO:0009086) that are connected to a seed coat (PO:0009088) by a funicle (PO:0020006).

label: berry fruit
definition: A fruit (PO:0009001) which at maturity comprises a fleshy endocarp (PO:0009086), fleshy mesocarp (PO:0009087), and fleshy exocarp (PO:0009085).

label: capsule fruit
definition: A fruit (PO:0009001) which develops from a gynoecium (PO:0009062) and at maturity comprises a dry exocarp (PO:0009085), dry mesocarp (PO:0009087), and dry endocarp (PO:0009086) that usually dehisce.

label: caryopsis fruit
definition: A fruit (PO:0009001) which develops from a gynoecium (PO:0009062) and at maturity comprises a dry exocarp (PO:0009085), dry mesocarp (PO:0009087), and dry endocarp (PO:0009086) that are fused to a seed coat (PO:0009088).

label: drupe fruit
definition: A fruit (PO:0009001) which develops from a carpel (PO:0009030) and at maturity comprises a fleshy exocarp (PO:0009085), fleshy mesocarp (PO:0009087), and a stony endocarp (PO:0009086).

label: follicle fruit
definition: A fruit (PO:0009001) which develops from a carpel (PO:0009030) and at maturity comprises a dry exocarp (PO:0009085), dry mesocarp (PO:0009087), and dry endocarp (PO:0009086) that dehisce along a single fruit valve (PO:0000033).

label: legume fruit
definition: A fruit (PO:0009001) which develops from a carpel (PO:0009030) and at maturity comprises a dry exocarp (PO:0009085), dry mesocarp (PO:0009087), and dry endocarp (PO:0009086) that dehisce along two fruit valves (PO:0000033).

label: nut fruit
definition: A fruit (PO:0009001) which develops from a gynoecium (PO:0009062) and at maturity comprises a dry exocarp (PO:0009085), dry mesocarp (PO:0009087), and dry endocarp (PO:0009086) that are not fused to a seed coat (PO:0009088).

label: samara fruit
definition: A fruit (PO:0009001) which develops from a carpel (PO:0009030) and at maturity comprises a dry exocarp (PO:0009085), dry mesocarp (PO:0009087), and dry endocarp (PO:0009086) that are elongated into a wing-like structure.

label: schizocarp fruit
definition: A fruit (PO:0009001) which develops from a gynoecium (PO:0009062) and at maturity comprises a dry exocarp (PO:0009085), dry mesocarp (PO:0009087), and dry endocarp (PO:0009086) that separate into mericarps (PO:0020075).

label: silique fruit
definition: A fruit (PO:0009001) which develops from a gynoecium (PO:0009062) and at maturity comprises a dry exocarp (PO:0009085), dry mesocarp (PO:0009087), and dry endocarp (PO:0009086), that dehisce along two fruit valves (PO:0000033) and separate from a persistent fruit replum (PO:0025267).

label: multi-tissue plant structure
definition: A plant structure (PO:0009011) that has as parts two or more portions of plant tissue (PO:0009007) of at least two different types and which through specific morphogenetic processes forms a single structural unit demarcated by primarily bona-fide boundaries from other structural units of different types.

label: fruit
definition: A multi-tissue plant structure (PO:0025496) that develops from a gynoecium (PO:0009062), or a single carpel (PO:0009030), and at maturity may have as parts one or more seeds (PO:0009010).

label: seed
definition: A multi-tissue plant structure (PO:0025496) that develops from a plant ovule (PO:0020003) and has as parts a plant embryo (PO:0009009) enclosed in a seed coat (PO:0009088).

label: circumscissile capsule fruit
definition: A capsule fruit (PO:0030091) which at maturity dehisces through the release of a fruit operculum (PO:0025298).

label: coccarium capsule fruit
definition: A capsule fruit (PO:0030091) which at maturity dehisces through both the fruit septa (PO:0025268) and the fruit locules (PO:0025270).

label: loculicidal capsule fruit
definition: A capsule fruit (PO:0030091) which at maturity dehisces through fruit locules (PO:0025270).

label: poricidal capsule fruit
definition: A capsule fruit (PO:0030091) which at maturity dehisces through pores on a pericarp (PO:0009084).

label: septicidal capsule fruit
definition: A capsule fruit (PO:0030091) which dehisces through a fruit septa (PO:0025268).

label: utricle capsule fruit
definition: A circumscissile capsule fruit (PO:0030096) which at maturity contains one seed (PO:0009010) that is not attached to a pericarp (PO:0009084).

label: loment fruit
definition: A legume fruit (PO:0030100) which at maturity separates into indehiscent, one-seeded segments.

label: hesperidium fruit
definition: A berry fruit (PO:0030108) which develops from a superior gynoecium (PO:0009062) and at maturity comprises a thickened exocarp (PO:0009085), thickened mesocarp (PO:0009087), and endocarp (PO:0009086), and has as parts juice sacs (PO:0006013) on a carpel adaxial epidermis (PO:0025618).

label: pepo fruit
definition: A berry fruit (PO:0030108) which develops from an inferior carpel (PO:0009030) and at maturity comprises a fleshy exocarp (PO:0009085), fleshy mesocarp (PO:0009087), and fleshy endocarp (PO:0009086), and has as a part a hard receptacle (PO:0009064) which surrounds, and is indistinct from, the exocarp (PO:0009085).

label: pome fruit
definition: A berry fruit (PO:0030108) which develops from an inferior gynoecium (PO:0009062) and at maturity comprises a fleshy exocarp (PO:0009085), fleshy mesocarp (PO:0009087), and hardened endocarp (PO:0009086) and has as a part a fleshy hypanthium (PO:0009065) which is indistinct from the exocarp (PO:0009085).

label: restriction enzyme
definition: an enzyme that has a specific target cleavage sites within nucleic acids

label: environmental system
definition: A system which has the disposition to environ one or more material entities.

label: 2D coordinate system
definition: A 2D coordinate system is a coordinate system in 2 dimensional space.  Each coordinate is composed of an offset from the origin of each dimension

label: cartesian coordinate system
definition: A Cartesian coordinate system is a coordinate system that specifies each point uniquely in a plane by a pair of numerical coordinates, which are the signed distances from the point to two fixed perpendicular directed lines, measured in the same unit of length.

label: genomic coordinate system
definition: a genomic coordinate system is a coordinate system to describe position of sequence on a genomic scaffold (assembly of chromosome, contig....)

label: spherical coordinate system
definition: In mathematics, a spherical coordinate system is a coordinate system for three-dimensional space where the position of a point is specified by three numbers: the radial distance of that point from a fixed origin, its polar angle measured from a fixed zenith direction, and the azimuth angle of its orthogonal projection on a reference plane that passes through the origin and is orthogonal to the zenith, measured from a fixed reference direction on that plane.

label: count of cases in an epidemic
definition: A count of disease cases in an infected population that meet the case definition criteria within a particular epidemic interval.

label: count of contagious population
definition: The count of individuals in a contagious population (empirical or virtual).

label: count of resistant population
definition: The count of individuals in a resistant population (empirical or virtual).

label: count of simulated population
definition: The count of (simulated organisms) in a simulated population.

label: exposure group healthy count
definition: The count of healthy individuals or animals on a certain date/time from a group that was likely exposed to a pathogen

label: exposure group ill count
definition: The count of ill individuals or animals on a certain date/time from a group that was likely exposed to a pathogen

label: exposure group unknown health status count
definition: The count of individuals or animals for which no health status is available on a certain date/time from a group that was likely exposed to a pathogen.

label: number of PCR cycle
definition: number of PCR cycle is a count which enumerates how many iterations of 'annealing, renaturation, amplification,' rounds (or cycles) are performed during a polymerase chain reaction (PCR) or an assay relying on PCR.

label: number of degrees of freedom
definition: The number degree of freedom is a count evaluating the number of values in a calculation that can vary. In statistics, the number of degrees of freedom ν is equal to N-1 in the case of the direct measurement of a quantity estimated by the arithmetic mean of N independent observations.

label: number of doses in a treatment course
definition: The count of the number of doses that are part of a treatment course.

label: sequence read count
definition: sequence read count is a data item determining how many sequence reads generated by a DNA sequencing assay for a given stretch of DNA can counted

label: significant digits
definition: Wikipedia: "The significant figures of a number are digits that carry meaning contributing to its measurement resolution."

label: dichotomous variable
definition: a dichotomous variable  is a categorical variable  which is defined to have only 2 categories or possible values

label: channel1/channel2 fluorescence intensity ratio
definition: is a data item formed by dividing the fluorescence intensity obtained in one channel to that obtained in the other channel, typically the case when considering 2-color microarray data when imaging is done for Cy3 and Cy5 dyes.

label: allele frequency
definition: The allele frequency is a data item which denotes the incidence of a gene variant in a population. It is calculated as a ratio, by dividing the number of copies of a particular allele by the number of copies of all alleles at the genetic place (locus) in a population.

label: dimensionless ratio
definition: A ratio where the numerator and denominator are expressed in the same unit.

label: survival rate
definition: A measurement data that represents the percentage of people or animals in a study or treatment group who are alive for a given period of time after diagnosis or initiation of monitoring.

label: reaction rate
definition: reaction rate is a measurement datum which represents the speed of a chemical reaction turning reactive species into product species of event (i.e the number of such conversions)s occuring over a time interval

label: signal to noise ratio
definition: signal to noise ratio is a measurement datum comparing the amount of meaningful, useful or interesting data (the signal) to the amount of irrelevant or false data (the noise). Depending on the field and domain of application, different variables will be used to determinate a 'signal to noise ratio'. In statistics, the definition of signal to noise ratio is the ratio of the mean of a measurement to its standard deviation. It thus corresponds to the inverse of the coefficient of variation

label: true negative rate
definition: specificity is a measurement datum qualifying a binary classification test and is computed by substracting the false positive rate to the integral numeral 1

label: true positive rate
definition: sensitivity is a measurement datum qualifying a binary classification test and is computed by substracting the false negative rate to the integral numeral 1

label: chromosome coordinate system
definition: chromosome coordinate system is a genomic coordinate which uses chromosome of a particular assembly build process to define start and end positions. This coordinate system is unstable and will change with each new genome sequence assembly build.

label: threshold cycle
definition: Threshold cycle (or Ct or Cq) is a count which is defined as the fractional PCR cycle number at which the reporter fluorescence is greater than the threshold in the context of the RT-qPCR assay. The Ct is a basic principle of real time PCR and is an essential component in producing accurate and reproducible data.

label: ordinal variable
definition: ordinal variable is a categorical variable where  the discrete possible values are ordered or  correspond to an implicit ranking

label: polychotomous variable
definition: a polychotomous variable  is a categorical variable  which is defined to have minimally 2 categories or possible values

label: categorical variable
definition: a categorical variable  is a variable  which that can only assume a finite number  of value and cast observation in a small number of categories

label: continuous variable
definition: A continuous variable is one for which, within the limits the variable ranges, any value is possible.

label: random variable
definition: a random variable (or aleatory variable or stochastic variable) in probability and statistics,  is a variable whose value is subject to variations due to chance (i.e. randomness, in a mathematical sense)

label: odds ratio
definition: Odds ratio is a ratio that measures effect size, that is the strength of association between 2 dichotomous variables, one describing an exposure and one describing an outcome. It represents the odds that an outcome will occur given a particular exposure, compared to the odds of the outcome occurring in the absence of that exposure ( the probability of the event occuring divided by the probability of an event not occurring). The odds ratio is a ratio of describing the strength of association or non-independence between two binary data values by forming the ratio of the odds for the first group and the odds for the second group. Odds ratio are used when one wants to compare the odds of something occurring to two different groups.

label: false negative rate
definition: the false negative rate is a data item which denotes the proportion of missed detection of elements known to be meeting the detection criteria

label: false positive rate
definition: a false positive rate is a data item which accounts for the proportion of incorrect rejection of a true null hypothesis.

label: fold change
definition: Fold change is a number describing how much a quantity changes going from an initial to a final value or one condition to another condition

label: direct transmission
definition: Direct and essentially immediate transfer of infectious agents to a receptive portal of entry through which human or animal infection may take place. This may be by direct contact such as touching, kissing, biting, or sexual intercourse or by the direct projection (droplet spread) of droplet spray onto the conjunctiva or the mucous membranes of the eyes, nose, or mouth. It may also be by direct exposure of susceptible tissue to an agent in soil, compost, or decaying vegetable matter or by the bite of a rabid animal. Transplacental transmission is another form of direct transmission.

label: indirect transmission
definition: Indirect transmission is a transmission process during which the pathogen is indirectly transferred from a reservoir, source or host to another host by intermediary vehicles, vectors or as airborne dust particles.

label: congenital
definition: Congenital transmission is a direct transmission process during which the pathogen is transmitted directly from mother to child at or around the time of birth.

label: contact
definition: Contact transmission is a direct transmission process during which the pathogen is transmitted from a reservoir, source or host to another host by kissing, skin-to-skin contact, sexual intercourse, or by contact with soil or vegetation containing the pathogen.

label: droplet spread
definition: Droplet spread transmission is a direct transmission process during which the pathogen is transmitted from a reservoir, source or host to another host by spray of aerosols over a short distance, spray from sneezing, coughing or talking.

label: common vehicle transmission
definition: Transmission of a disease agent (infectious pathogen, toxic chemical, etc.) from a source that is common to those who acquire the disease. Common vehicles include air, water, food, injected substances. Legionellosis is an example of common vehicle spread in air that has passed through air conditioning equipment contaminated by the causal organism. HIV disease and hepatitis B and C can be spread among illicit drug users by the common vehicle of contaminated needles and syringes. Cholera and many other waterborne diseases are spread by the common vehicle of contaminated water.

label: vehicle-born ingestion
definition: Vehicle-borne ingestion transmission is an indirect vehicle-borne transmission process during which the pathogen is indirectly transferred from a reservoir, source or host to another host by ingestion of fluids or foods or food products including: food, water, milk, or meat products.

label: life cycle stage
definition: A spatiotemporal region encompassing some part of the life cycle of an organism.

label: feather
definition: one of the epidermal growths that form the distinctive outer covering, or plumage, on birds. Feathers are formed in tiny follicles in the epidermis, or outer skin layer, that produce keratin proteins.

label: epithelial tube
definition: Epithelial tubes transport gases, liquids and cells from one site to another and form the basic structure of many organs and tissues, with tube shape and organization varying from the single-celled excretory organ in Caenorhabditis elegans to the branching trees of the mammalian kidney and insect tracheal system.

label: respiratory tube
definition: A tube in the respiratory system. Examples: bronchus, bronchiole, trachea.

label: abdominal lymph node
definition: A lymph node that is part of an abdomen [Automatically generated definition].

label: brachial lymph node
definition: The lymph nodes located along the brachial vein that receive drainage from most of the free upper limb and send efferent vessels to the central axillary lymph nodes.

label: bronchial lymph node
definition: A lymph node that is part of a bronchus.

label: cervical lymph node
definition: Cervical lymph nodes are lymph nodes found in the neck. [WP,unvetted].

label: deep lymph node
definition: A lymph node that is located deeper within the organism, further from the surface.

label: ileocolic lymph node
definition: One of the lymph nodes that form a chain around the ileocolic artery.

label: lymph node of head
definition: A lymph node that is part of a head.

label: lymph node of lower limb
definition: A lymph node that is part of a hindlimb.

label: lymph node of upper limb
definition: A lymph node that is part of a forelimb.

label: paraaortic lymph node
definition: The paraaortic lymph nodes (also known as para-aortic, periaortic, and peri-aortic) are a group of lymph nodes that lie in front of the lumbar vertebral bodies near the aorta. These lymph nodes receive drainage from the lower gastrointestinal tract and the pelvic organs.

label: pelvic lymph node
definition: Any lymph node within the abdominal pelvic region.

label: peripheral lymph node
definition: The lymph nodes located outside the thoracic and abdominal cavities, such as the submandibular, prescapular, axillary, inguinal and popliteal lymph nodes

label: renal lymph node
definition: A lymph node that is located in a kidney [Automatically generated definition].

label: retroperitoneal lymph node
definition: A lymph node located in the retroperitoneal space.

label: sacral lymph node
definition: A lymph node located in the sacral region.

label: splenic lymph node
definition: The splenic lymph nodes (or pancreaticolienal) accompany the lienal (splenic) artery, and are situated in relation to the posterior surface and upper border of the pancreas; one or two members of this group are found in the gastrolienal ligament. Their afferents are derived from the stomach, spleen, and pancreas, their efferents join the celiac group of preaortic glands.

label: subcutaneous lymph node
definition: A lymph node that is part of a hypodermis.

label: superficial lymph node
definition: A lymph node that is located close to the surface.

label: thoracic lymph node
definition: A lymph node that is part of a thorax. Includes lymph nodes of the lungs and mediastinal lymph nodes

label: tracheobronchial lymph node
definition: A lymph node located near the bifurcation of the trachea.

label: acellular anatomical structure
definition: Anatomical structure that consists of cell parts and cell substances and together does not constitute a cell or a tissue.

label: anatomical system
definition: Multicellular, connected anatomical structure that has multiple organs as parts and whose parts work together to achieve some shared function.

label: ectoderm-derived structure
definition: An anatomical structure that develops (entirely or partially) from the ectoderm.

label: endoderm-derived structure
definition: An anatomical structure that develops (entirely or partially) from the endoderm.

label: lateral structure
definition: Any structure that is placed on one side of the left-right axis of a bilaterian.

label: mesoderm-derived structure
definition: An anatomical structure that develops (entirely or partially) from the mesoderm.

label: morphological feature
definition: A part of an organism or organ that is continuous with its surroundings and distinguished from its surroundings based on morphology.

label: multicellular anatomical structure
definition: An anatomical structure that has more than one cell as a part.

label: muscle structure
definition: Muscle structures are contractile cells, tissues or organs that are found in multicellular organisms[GO].

label: organ
definition: Anatomical structure that performs a specific function or group of functions [WP].

label: structure with developmental contribution from neural crest
definition: An anatomical structure that has some part that develops from the neural crest.

label: surface structure
definition: Anatomical structure that overlaps the outer epithelial layer and is adjacent to the space surrounding the organism.

label: abdomen element
definition: An organ or element that is in the abdomen. Examples: spleen, intestine, kidney, abdominal mammary gland.

label: compound organ
definition: Anatomical structure that has as its parts two or more multi-tissue structures of at least two different types and which through specific morphogenetic processes forms a single distinct structural unit demarcated by bona fide boundaries from other distinct anatomical structures of different types.

label: digestive system element
definition: Any of the organs or elements that are part of the digestive system. Examples: tongue, esophagus, spleen, crop, lunge feeding organ, tooth elements.

label: gland
definition: an organ that functions as a secretory or excretory organ

label: hemopoietic organ
definition: Organ that is part of the hematopoietic system.

label: immune organ
definition: An organ that is part of a immune system [Automatically generated definition].

label: muscle organ
definition: Organ consisting of a tissue made up of various elongated cells that are specialized to contract and thus to produce movement and mechanical work[GO].

label: reproductive organ
definition: An organ involved in reproduction

label: respiration organ
definition: Organ that functions in gaseous exchange between an organism and its environment. In plants, microorganisms, and many small animals, air or water makes direct contact with the organism's cells or tissue fluids, and the processes of diffusion supply the organism with dioxygen (O2) and remove carbon dioxide (CO2). In larger animals the efficiency of gaseous exchange is improved by specialized respiratory organs, such as lungs and gills, which are ventilated by breathing mechanisms.

label: skeletal element
definition: Organ consisting of skeletal tissue. Encompasses whole bones, fused bones, cartilaginious elements, teeth, dermal denticles.

label: trunk region element
definition: An organ or element that part of the trunk region. The trunk region can be further subdividied into thoracic (including chest and thoracic cavity) and abdominal (including abdomen and pelbis) regions.

label: urethra
definition: the fibromuscular tubular canal through which urine is discharged from the bladder to the exterior via the external urinary meatus; in males, the urethra is joined by the ejaculatory ducts and serves as a passageway for semen during ejaculation, as well as a canal for urine during voiding; in females, the urethra is shorter and emerges above the vaginal opening

label: integumentary adnexa
definition: Anatomical structure embedded in or located in the integument that is part of the integumental system. Examples: hair, follicles, skin glands, claws, nails, feathers.

label: nasopharynx
definition: the section of the pharynx that lies above the soft palate

label: vertebral column
definition: Subdivision of skeletal system that consists of all the vertebra and associated skeletal elements and joints in the body[modified from VSAO].

label: death stage
definition: End of the life of an organism.

label: embryo stage
definition: A life cycle stage that starts with fertilization and ends with the fully formed embryo.

label: infant stage
definition: Nursing stage that follows the neonate stage in mammals and ends at weaning.

label: juvenile stage
definition: The stage of being no more dependent of the nest and/or from caregivers for subsistence while having not reach sexual maturity.

label: larval stage
definition: A distinct juvenile stage many animals undergo before metamorphosis into adults. Animals with indirect development such as insects, amphibians, or cnidarians typically have a larval phase of their life cycle.

label: neonate stage
definition: Of or pertaining to the period of time immediately following birth, or to the newborn.

label: prime adult stage
definition: A life cycle stage that starts at completion of development and growth of the sexually mature adult animal, and ends before senescence.

label: bronchus
definition: the upper conducting airways of the lung; these airways arise from the terminus of the trachea

label: trachea
definition: The trachea is the portion of the airway that attaches to the bronchi as it branches [GO:dph].

label: ascending colon
definition: Section of colon which is distal to the cecum and proximal to the transversecolon.[FMA,modified]

label: descending colon
definition: The portion of the colon between the left colic flexure and the sigmoid colon at the pelvic brim; the portion of the descending colon lying in the left iliac fossa is sometimes called the iliac colon.

label: sigmoid colon
definition: The part of the large intestine that is closest to the rectum and anus. It forms a loop that averages about 40 cm. in length, and normally lies within the pelvis, but on account of its freedom of movement it is liable to be displaced into the abdominal cavity.

label: spiral colon
definition: A variant of the ascending colon in ruminants and pigs.

label: transverse colon
definition: The proximal-distal subdivision of colon that runs transversely across the upper part of the abdomen, from the right to the left colic flexure. Continuous with the descending colon[BTO,modified].

label: lung
definition: Respiration organ that develops as an oupocketing of the esophagus.

label: excreted gas
definition: Any gaseous product of an excretory process.

label: feces
definition: Portion of semisolid bodily waste discharged through the anus[MW,modified]

label: urine
definition: Excretion that is the output of a kidney

label: arterial blood
definition: A blood that is part of a artery.

label: capillary blood
definition: A blood that is part of a capillary.

label: umbilical cord blood
definition: blood that remains in the placenta and in the attached umbilical cord after childbirth[WP].

label: venous blood
definition: A blood that is part of a vein.

label: blood
definition: A fluid that is composed of blood plasma and erythrocytes.

label: blood plasma
definition: The liquid component of blood, in which erythrocytes are suspended.

label: blood serum
definition: The portion of blood plasma that excludes clotting factors.

label: lymph
definition: Lymph is the fluid that is formed when interstitial fluid enters the conduits of the lymphatic system through lymph capillaries[WP].

label: saliva
definition: A fluid produced in the oral cavity by salivary glands, typically used in predigestion, but also in other functions.

label: secretion of serous gland
definition: Any fluid produced by a serous gland.

label: albumen
definition: Albumen is the clear liquid contained within an egg and consists of water and proteins, among which are ovomucin and ovomucoid. It protects the egg yolk and provides additional nutrition for the growth of the embryo.

label: bodily gas
definition: Any substance in the body or expelled from the body that is in a gaseous state.

label: respiratory system fluid/secretion
definition: A portion of organism substance that secreted_by a respiratory system.

label: secretion of exocrine gland
definition: A portion of organism substance that is produced by exocrine glands.

label: extended organism
definition: An object aggregate consisting of an organism and all material entities located within the organism, overlapping the organism, or occupying sites formed in part by the organism.

label: organism substance
definition: Material anatomical entity in a gaseous, liquid, semisolid or solid state; produced by anatomical structures or derived from inhaled and ingested substances that have been modified by anatomical structures as they pass through the body.

label: respiratory system
definition: Functional system which consists of structures involved in respiration.

label: adult organism
definition: A multicellular organism that existence_ends_with a post-juvenile adult stage and existence_starts_with a post-juvenile adult stage.

label: embryo
definition: Anatomical entity that comprises the organism in the early stages of growth and differentiation that are characterized by cleavage, the laying down of fundamental tissues, and the formation of primitive organs and organ systems. For example, for mammals, the process would begin with zygote formation and end with birth. For insects, the process would begin at zygote formation and end with larval hatching. For plant zygotic embryos, this would be from zygote formation to the end of seed dormancy. For plant vegetative embryos, this would be from the initial determination of the cell or group of cells to form an embryo until the point when the embryo becomes independent of the parent plant.

label: thoracic segment organ
definition: An organ that part of the thoracic segment region. This region can be further subdividied chest and thoracic cavity regions.

label: eggshell
definition: A product of the somatic follicle cell epithelium and a structure that supports the egg in a hostile environment, minimizing water loss whilst allowing gas exchanges essential for embryonic respiration[GO].

label: bone marrow
definition: the soft tissue that fills the cavities of bones

label: embryonic tissue
definition: A portion of tissue that is part of an embryo.

label: epithelium
definition: Portion of tissue, that consists of one or more layers of epithelial cells connected to each other by cell junctions and which is underlain by a basal lamina. Examples: simple squamous epithelium, glandular cuboidal epithelium, transitional epithelium, myoepithelium[CARO].

label: muscle tissue
definition: Muscle tissue is a contractile tissue made up of actin and myosin fibers[GO].

label: digestive tract epithelium
definition: An epithelium that lines the lumen of the digestive tract.

label: ecto-epithelium
definition: Epithelium composed of cells that develops from the ectoderm[FMA,modified].

label: endo-epithelium
definition: Epithelium that derives from the endoderm. Examples: urothelium, transitional epithelium of ureter, epithelium of prostatic gland.[FMA]

label: epithelium of mucosa
definition: A layer of epithelial cells on the surface of the mucosa.

label: unilaminar epithelium
definition: Epithelium which consists of a single layer of epithelial cells. Examples: endothelium, mesothelium, glandular squamous epithelium.[FMA]

label: bladder organ
definition: A membranous sac in animals that serves as the receptacle of a liquid or contains gas.

label: kidney
definition: A paired organ of the urinary tract which has the production of urine as its primary function.

label: epithelium of foregut-midgut junction
definition: An epithelium that is part of a foregut-midgut junction.

label: oral epithelium from ectoderm
definition: An epithelium that develops_from a ectoderm and is part of a oral epithelium.

label: equine glandular stomach
definition: Stomach found in horses; includes cardiac, proper gastric and pyloric glandular zones.

label: gizzard
definition: The muscular enlargement of the alimentary canal that has usually thick muscular walls and a tough horny lining for grinding the food and when the crop is present follows it and the proventriculus.

label: ruminant stomach
definition: The ruminants' stomach consists of four compartments: rumen, reticulum, omasum and abomasum. The first three compartments comprise the forestomach (proventriculus). They are lined with nonglandular membrane. The fourth compartment, the abomasum comprises the true stomach of the ruminants. It is lined with glandular mucous membrane. The rumen lies on the left of the abdominal cavity, the reticulum cranially and the omasum on the right. The abomasum lies ventrally, its proximal end lies ventral to the rumen, reticulum and omasum

label: respiratory tract
definition: Anatomical structure that is part of the respiratory system. In mammals consists of upper and lower tracts

label: nematode pharynx
definition: The feeding organ, a neuro-muscular pump in the head of the animal, used to ingest food, bacteria suspended in liquid, filter them out, grind them up and transport posteriorly into the instestine.

label: material anatomical entity
definition: Anatomical entity that has mass.

label: deep inguinal lymph node
definition: One of several small inconstant lymph nodes, proximal, intermediate and distal deep to the fascia lata and medial to the femoral vein; they receive lymph from the deep structures of the lower limb, from the glans penis and from superficial inguinal nodes; efferents pass to the external iliac nodes.

label: superficial inguinal lymph node
definition: A group of 12-20 lymph nodes that lie in the subcutaneous tissue below the inguinal ligament and along the terminal part of the great saphenous vein; they drain the skin and subcutaneous tissue of the lower abdominal wall, perineum, buttocks, external genitalia, and lower limbs.

label: sphincter muscle
definition: A structure, usually a circular muscle, that normally maintains constriction of a natural body passage or orifice and which relaxes as required by normal physiological functioning.

label: meconium
definition: A dark greenish mass that accumulates in the bowel during fetal life and is discharged shortly after birth.

label: right lung
definition: Lung which consists of the right upper lobe, middle lobe and right lower lobe.[FMA]

label: shelled egg
definition: The hard-shelled reproductive body produced by a bird and especially by the common domestic chicken; also: its contents used as food.

label: abdominal viscera
definition: A viscus that is part of a abdomen.

label: urinary bladder
definition: distensible musculomembranous organ situated in the anterior part of the pelvic cavity in which urine collects before excretion[MP].

label: left kidney
definition: A kidney that is part of a left side of organism [Automatically generated definition].

label: right kidney
definition: A kidney that is part of a right side of organism [Automatically generated definition].

label: liver
definition: An exocrine gland which secretes bile and functions in metabolism of protein and carbohydrate and fat, synthesizes substances involved in the clotting of the blood, synthesizes vitamin A, detoxifies poisonous substances, stores glycogen, and breaks down worn-out erythrocytes[GO].

label: digestive system gland
definition: Any gland that is part of the digestive system.

label: anterior cervical lymph node
definition: The anterior cervical lymph nodes are a group of nodes found on the anterior part of the neck.

label: deep cervical lymph node
definition: The deep cervical lymph nodes are a group of cervical lymph nodes found near the internal jugular vein. They can be divided into upper and lower groups, or superior and inferior groups. Alternatively, they can be divided into deep anterior cervical lymph nodes and deep lateral cervical lymph nodes. They can also be divided into three groups: superior deep jugular, middle deep jugular, and 'inferior deep jugular'.

label: lateral cervical lymph node
definition: A cervical lymph nodes are found in proximity to an internal or external jugular vein.

label: superficial cervical lymph node
definition: A group of nodes lying along the external jugular vein; they drain the skin and superficial structures over the region of the sternocleidomastoid muscle and anterior cervical regions. Efferent vessels drain to the deep cervical lymph nodes. Lymph nodes can be further subdivided into anterior and lateral groupings.

label: supraclavicular lymph node
definition: A lymph node which is located above the clavicle.

label: lumbar lymph node
definition: The lumbar lymph nodes (paraaortic nodes) are a group of lymph nodes residing in the lumbar region. They consist of the following groups: right and left lateral aortic lymph nodes preaortic lymph nodes retroaortic lymph nodes (or 'postaortic')

label: pancreatic lymph node
definition: A lymph node that is part of a pancreas [Automatically generated definition].

label: anterior mediastinal lymph node
definition: A lymph node located in the superior mediastinum that collects lymph from the thymus, the pericardium, and the right side of the heart.

label: node of ligamentum arteriosum
definition: An inconstant lymph node of the anterior mediastinal group located adjacent to the ligamentum arteriosum.

label: endocrine gland
definition: Endocrine glands are glands of the endocrine system that secrete their products directly into the circulatory system rather than through a duct.[WP, modified].

label: exocrine gland
definition: A gland that secretes products (excluding hormones and other chemical messengers) into ducts (duct glands) which lead directly into the external environment[WP]. Typical exocrine glands include sweat glands, salivary glands, mammary glands, stomach, liver, pancreas

label: external integument structure
definition: Structures of the dermis, epidermis, glands and pigment cells recognizable on the external surfaces of the integument.

label: outer epithelium
definition: The epidermis is the entire outer epithelial layer of an animal, it may be a single layer that produces an extracellular material (e.g. the cuticle of arthropods) or a complex stratified squamous epithelium, as in the case of many vertebrate species[GO].

label: cavitated compound organ
definition: Compound organ that contains one or more macroscopic anatomical spaces.

label: circulatory organ
definition: A hollow, muscular organ, which, by contracting rhythmically, contributes to the circulation of lymph, blood or analogs. Examples: a chambered vertebrate heart; the tubular peristaltic heart of ascidians; the dorsal vessel of an insect; the lymoh heart of a reptile.

label: respiratory airway
definition: An airway through which respiratory air passes in organisms.

label: external genitalia
definition: The external genitalia are the outer sex organs, such as the penis or vulva in mammals

label: internal genitalia
definition: The internal genitalia are the internal sex organs such as the uterine tube, the uterus and the vagina in female mammals, and the testis, seminal vesicle, ejaculatory duct and prostate in male mammals

label: oral epithelium
definition: An epithelium that is part of the mouth and lines the oral cavity, typically stratified squamous, and may be para-, ortho- or non- keratinized. Primary barrier between oral environment and deeper tissues

label: epithelial sac
definition: An epithelial tube that is open at one end only.

label: foregut epithelium
definition: A epithelium that is part of a foregut.

label: axillary lymph node
definition: the lymph nodes located around the axillary vein that receive lymphatic drainage from the upper or forelimb, scapular region and pectoral region

label: inguinal lymph node
definition: the lymph nodes located in the groin area

label: popliteal lymph node
definition: the lymph nodes which drain the legs; contained in the popliteal fossa

label: submandibular lymph node
definition: The submandibular lymph nodes (submaxillary glands in older texts), three to six in number, are placed beneath the body of the mandible in the submaxillary triangle, and rest on the superficial surface of the submaxillary salivary gland. One gland, the middle gland of Stahr, which lies on the external maxillary artery as it turns over the mandible, is the most constant of the series; small lymph glands are sometimes found on the deep surface of the submaxillary salivary glands. The afferents of the submaxillary glands drain the medial palpebral commissure, the cheek, the side of the nose, the upper lip, the lateral part of the lower lip, the gums, and the anterior part of the margin of the tongue. Efferent vessels from the facial and submental glands also enter the submaxillary glands. Their efferent vessels pass to the superior deep cervical glands. [WP,unvetted].

label: ileocecal valve
definition: The ileocecal valve is a sphincter muscle situated at the junction of the small intestine (ileum) and the large intestine. Its critical function is to limit the reflux of colonic contents into the ileum.

label: tube
definition: Any hollow cylindrical anatomical structure containing a lumen through which substances are transported.

label: endodermal part of digestive tract
definition: A portions of the gut that is derived from endoderm.

label: gall bladder
definition: An organ that aids digestion and stores bile produced by the liver[WP].

label: oropharynx
definition: the portion of the pharynx that lies between the soft palate and the upper edge of the epiglottis

label: proximo-distal subdivision of respiratory tract
definition: An section of a respiratory tract.

label: heart
definition: A myogenic muscular circulatory organ found in the vertebrate cardiovascular system composed of chambers of cardiac muscle. It is the primary circulatory organ.

label: mesenteric lymph node
definition: The lymph nodes located in the mesentery, of which there are 3 classes: ileocolic, juxtaintestinal mesenteric, and central superior group.

label: ectodermal part of digestive tract
definition: A portion of the gut that is derived from ectoderm.

label: spleen
definition: the organ that functions to filter blood and to store red corpuscles and platelets

label: hepatic diverticulum
definition: An out-pocket of thickened ventral foregut epithelium adjacent to the developing heart. Constitutes the first morphological sign of the embryonic liver. The anterior portion of the hepatic diverticulum gives rise to the liver and intrahepatic biliary tree, while the posterior portion forms the gall bladder and extrahepatic bile ducts.

label: integumentary projection
definition: Anatomical projection that is part of the integumentl system.

label: gastrointestinal sphincter
definition: A sphincter muscle that is part of the gastrointestinal system

label: deep anterior cervical lymph node
definition: The deep anterior cervical lymph nodes are found near the middle cricothyroid ligament and the trachea.

label: deep lateral cervical lymph node
definition: The deep lateral cervical lymph nodes are found near the upper part of the internal jugular vein in the neck, lateral or posterior to the carotid sheath.

label: superficial anterior cervical lymph node
definition: The superficial anterior cervical lymph nodes are found in proximity to the anterior jugular vein.

label: superficial lateral cervical lymph node
definition: The superficial lateral cervical lymph nodes are found in proximity to the external jugular vein.

label: Rathkes pouch epithelium
definition: A epithelial sac that is part of a Rathke's pouch.

label: cardiac stomach
definition: In starfishes the cardiac stomach is connected to a pyloric stomach which is located above it. Food can be brought into the stomach through the mouth or, in many species, the cardiac stomach can be extended out through the mouth to digest food outside the body. Suspension-feeding starfish use their tube feet to pass food to the mouth.

label: colon
definition: Last portion of the large intestine before it becomes the rectum.

label: colorectum
definition: The subdivision of the digestive tract that consists of the colon and the rectum.

label: digestive tract diverticulum
definition: Branch or outpocketing of the digestive tract.

label: duodenal ampulla
definition: The very first part of the duodenum which is slightly dilated.

label: duodenum
definition: The first part of the small intestine. At the junction of the stomach and the duodenum the alimentary canal is inflected. The duodenum first goes anteriorly for a short distance, turns dorsally, and eventually caudally, thus it is a U-shaped structure with two horizontal sections (a ventral and a dorsal one).

label: echinoderm pyloric cecum
definition: The pyloric ceca (or digestive glands) and the cardiac stomach produce digestive enzymes in starfishes. Digested material is absorbed through the pyloric ceca for transport to the rest of the body. Each pyloric cecum extends the length of each arm.

label: esophagus
definition: Tube that connects the pharynx to the stomach. In mammals, the oesophagus connects the buccal cavity with the stomach. The stratified squamous non-keratinised epithelium lining the buccal cavity is continued through the pharynx down into the oesophagus. The lowest part of the oesophagus (ca. 2 cm) is lined with gastric mucosa and covered by peritoneum. The main body of the oesophagus is lined with small, simple mucous glands. Each gland opens into the lumen by a long duct which pierces the muscularis mucosae (Wilson and Washington, 1989). A sphincter is situated at the point where the oesophagus enters the stomach to prevent gastro-oesophageal reflux, i.e. to prevent acidic gastric contents from reaching stratified epithelia of the oesophagus, where they can cause inflammation and irritation (Wilson and Washington, 1989; Brown et al., 1993).

label: foregut
definition: Anterior subdivision of a digestive tract.

label: hindgut
definition: The caudalmost subdivision of a digestive tract.

label: ileum
definition: the portion of the small intestine that extends from the jejunum to the colon

label: intestine
definition: Segment of the alimentary canal extending from the stomach to the anus and, in humans and other mammals, consists of two segments, the small intestine and the large intestine.

label: jejunum
definition: the portion of the small intestine that extends from the duodenum to the ileum

label: large intestine
definition: A subdivision of the digestive tract that connects the small intestine to the cloaca or anus. Lacks or has few villi[Kardong].

label: lower digestive tract
definition: The region of the digestive tract extending from the beginning of the intestines to the anus[GO - gut definition].

label: lower esophagus
definition: The lower one third of the esophagus in which the muscle layer is composed of muscle cells predominantly of the smooth type.

label: middle part of esophagus
definition: The middle one third of the esophagus in which the muscle layer is composed of muscle cells of the striated and smooth types.

label: midgut
definition: Middle subdivision of a digestive tract[CJM]. In vertebrates: The middle part of the alimentary canal from the stomach, or entrance of the bile duct, to, or including, the large intestine[GO].

label: midgut loop
definition: Portion of midgut after it bends around the superior mesenteric artery

label: mouth
definition: The proximal portion of the digestive tract, containing the oral cavity and bounded by the oral opening. In vertebrates, this extends to the pharynx and includes gums, lips, tongue and parts of the palate. Typically also includes the teeth, except where these occur elsewhere (e.g. pharyngeal jaws) or protrude from the mouth (tusks).

label: pharynx
definition: The pharynx is the part of the digestive system immediately posterior to the mouth[GO].

label: proximal-distal subdivision of colon
definition: A section dividing a colon along a proximal-distal axis.

label: pyloric stomach
definition: The mouth of a starfish is located on the underside of the body, and opens through a short esophagus into firstly a cardiac stomach, and then, a second, pyloric stomach. Each arm also contains two pyloric caeca, long hollow tubes branching outwards from the pyloric stomach. Each pyloric caecum is lined by a series of digestive glands, which secrete digestive enzymes and absorb nutrients from the food. A short intestine runs from the upper surface of the pyloric stomach to open at an anus in the center of the upper body

label: rectum
definition: the terminal portion of the intestinal tube, terminating with the anus

label: reticulorumen
definition: The first chamber in the alimentary canal of a ruminant stomach, composed of the rumen and reticulum.

label: small intestine
definition: Subdivision of digestive tract that connects the stomach to the large intestine and is where much of the digestion and absorption of food takes place (with the exception of ruminants). The mammalian small intestine is long and coiled and can be differentiated histologically into: duodenum, jejunem, ileum[WP,cjm,Kardong].

label: stomach
definition: An expanded region of the vertebrate alimentary tract that serves as a food storage compartment and digestive organ. A stomach is lined, in whole or in part by a glandular epithelium.

label: tailgut
definition: The extension of the hindgut of the primitive digestive tube of the embryo, caudal to the location of the anal opening

label: terminal part of digestive tract
definition: The distalmost portion of the digestive tract, derived from the hindgut, and terminating with the anus.

label: upper digestive tract
definition: The region of the digestive tract extending from the mouth cavity through pharynx esophagus stomach and duodenum.

label: upper esophagus
definition: The upper one third of esophagus in which the muscle layer is composed of muscle cells of the striated type.

label: lymph node
definition: Any of the rounded masses of lymphoid tissue that are surrounded by a capsule of connective tissue, are distributed along the lymphatic vessels, and contain numerous lymphocytes which filter the flow of lymph.

label: pelvic region element
definition: An organ or element that is part of the pelvic region. Examples: reproductive organs (in some organisms), urinary bladder, bones of the pelvis.

label: abdominal segment element
definition: An organ or element that is part of the adbominal segment of the organism. This region can be further subdivided into the abdominal cavity and the pelvic region.

label: viscus
definition: An organ that is located within the body cavity (or in its extension, in the scrotum); it consists of organ parts that are embryologically derived from endoderm, splanchnic mesoderm or intermediate mesoderm; together with other organs, the viscus constitutes the respiratory, gastrointestinal, urinary, reproductive and immune systems, or is the central organ of the cardiovascular system. Examples: heart, lung, esophagus, kidney, ovary, spleen.

label: thoracic cavity element
definition: An organ or element that is in the thoracic cavity. Examples: lung, heart, longus colli.

label: embryonic structure
definition: Anatomical structure that is part of an embryo.

label: Aspirate
definition: Fluid withdrawn from a body cavity, organ, cyst, or tumor.

label: haemolymphatic fluid
definition: Circulating fluid that is part of the hemolymphoid system. Blood, lymph, interstitial fluid or its analogs.

label: sputum
definition: Matter ejected from the lungs, bronchi, and trachea, through the mouth.

label: transudate
definition: Any bodily fluid that has passed through a membrane such as the capillary wall, as a result of unbalanced hydrostatic and osmotic forces

label: chordate pharynx
definition: A portion of the respiratory and digestive tracts; its distal limit is the superior part of the esophagus and it connects the nasal and oral cavities with the esophagus and larynx; it contains the valleculae and the pyriform recesses; its upper limits are the nasal cavity and cranial base.[FEED].

label: Hepatic
definition: Pertaining to, affecting, or associated with the liver.

label: gravid organism
definition: An organism containing a developing embryo, fetus, or unborn offspring within the body.

label: intercostal lymph node
definition: The intercostal lymph nodes (intercostal glands ) occupy the posterior parts of the intercostal spaces, in relation to the intercostal vessels. They receive the deep lymphatics from the postero-lateral aspect of the chest; some of these vessels are interrupted by small lateral intercostal glands.

label: mediastinal lymph node
definition: A lymph node that is part of a mediastinum. Each consists of several lymph node groups, especially along the trachea (5 groups), along the esophagus and between the lung and the diaphragm. In the mediastinal lymph nodes arises lymphatic ducts, which draines the lymph to the left subclavian vein (to the venous angle in the confluence of the subclavian and deep jugular veins). The mediastinal lymph nodes along the esophagus are in tight connection with the abdominal lymph nodes along the esophagus and the stomach. That fact facilitates spreading of tumors cells through these lymphatics in cases of cancers of the stomach and particularly of the esophagus. Through the mediastinum, the main lymphatic drainage from the abdominal organs goes via the thoracic duct (ductus thoracicus), which drains majority of the lymph from the abdomen to the above mentioned left venous angle.

label: parasternal lymph node
definition: Any of the lymph nodes of the breast located under the ribcage, near the sternum.

label: peritoneal fluid
definition: Transudate contained in the peritoneal cavity.

label: synovial fluid
definition: Joint fluid is a transudate of plasma that is actively secreted by synovial cells.

label: cerebrospinal fluid
definition: A clear, colorless, bodily fluid, that occupies the subarachnoid space and the ventricular system around and inside the brain and spinal cord.

label: proximal deep inguinal lymph node
definition: One of the deep inguinal lymph nodes located in or adjacent to the femoral canal; sometimes mistaken for a femoral hernia when enlarged.

label: actinopterygian pyloric caecum
definition: A finger-like out-pocketing of the intestine where it meets the end of the stomach (pylorus). Also spelled cecum (ceca). Serves to aid digestion.

label: caecum
definition: A pouch in the digestive tract that connects the ileum with the ascending colon of the large intestine. It is separated from the ileum by the ileocecal valve, and is the beginning of the large intestine. It is also separated from the colon by the cecocolic junction.

label: echinoderm gastric caecum
definition: non-contractile pouch that is connected to the anterior stomach through a slit-like opening. This pouch is also well-connected to the haemal system through numerous haemal ducts within its connective tissue layer.

label: hepatic cecum
definition: A ventral evagination extending anteriorly in the mid-portion of the intestine in Amphioxi.

label: anatomical conduit
definition: Any tube, opening or passage that connects two distinct anatomical spaces.

label: multicellular organism
definition: Anatomical structure that is an individual member of a species and consists of more than one cell.

label: organ part
definition: A multicellular structure that is a part of an organ.

label: organ system subdivision
definition: A subdivision of an anatomical system.

label: reproductive structure
definition: Any anatomical structure that is part of the reproductive system.

label: tissue
definition: Multicellular anatomical structure that consists of many cells of one or a few types, arranged in an extracellular matrix such that their long-range organisation is at least partly a repetition of their short-range organisation.

label: subdivision of skeletal system
definition: Anatomical cluster consisting of the skeletal elements and articular elements that are part of an individual subdivision of the organism.

label: retropharyngeal lymph node
definition: The retropharyngeal lymph nodes, from one to three in number, lie in the buccopharyngeal fascia, behind the upper part of the pharynx and in front of the arch of the atlas, being separated, however, from the latter by the Longus capitis. Their afferents drain the nasal cavities, the nasal part of the pharynx, and the auditory tubes. Their efferents pass to the superior deep cervical glands. They are in the retropharyngeal space.

label: cloaca
definition: Common chamber into which the intestines and excretory system opens. Arises during development in all vertebrates, but in many it becomes subdivided, lost or incorporated into other structures

label: subdivision of digestive tract
definition: A proximal-distal subdivision of the digestive tract.

label: cutaneous appendage
definition: Anatomical projection that protrudes from the skin. Examples: hair, nail, feather, claw, hoof, horn, wattle, spur, beak, antler, bristle and some scales.

label: food storage organ
definition: An organ of the digestive tract that is capable of retaining and storing food

label: primary circulatory organ
