definition: A hollow, muscular organ, which, by contracting rhythmically, keeps up the circulation of the blood or analogs[GO,modified].

label: deep parotid lymph node
definition: The deep parotid lymph nodes are lymph nodes found below the parotid gland. The afferents of the subparotid glands drain the nasal part of the pharynx and the posterior parts of the nasal cavities. Their efferents pass to the superior deep cervical glands.

label: superficial parotid lymph node
definition: A parotid lymph node that is located superficially.

label: celiac lymph node
definition: the visceral glands that are associated with the branches of the celiac artery, including the gastric, hepatic, and pancreaticolienal (splenic) lymph nodes

label: gastric lymph node
definition: A lymph node along the left gastric artery or greater omentum.

label: hepatic lymph node
definition: Any of the lymph nodes adjacent to the stomach and duodenum.

label: mesocolic lymph node
definition: A lymph node that located_in a colon.

label: pancreaticosplenic lymph node
definition: lymph nodes of the pancreatic tail and spleen, receiving afferents from both organs plus the greater curvature of the stomach; they drain to the celiac lymph nodes.

label: facial lymph node
definition: Any of the lymph nodes that are part of a face.

label: mastoid lymph node
definition: The mastoid lymph nodes (retroauricular lymph nodes, posterior auricular glands), usually two in number, are situated on the mastoid insertion of the Sternocleidomastoideus, beneath the Auricularis posterior. Their afferent vessels drain the posterior part of the temporoparietal region, the upper part of the cranial surface of the auricula or pinna, and the back of the external acoustic meatus; their efferents pass to the superior deep cervical glands.

label: occipital lymph node
definition: A lymph node located in the back of the head adjacent to the trapezius muscle.

label: parotid lymph node
definition: A lymph node found near the parotid gland.

label: submental lymph node
definition: The submental lymph nodes (or suprahyoid) are situated between the anterior bellies of the Digastrici. Their afferents drain the central portions of the lower lip and floor of the mouth and the apex of the tongue. Their efferents pass partly to the submandibular lymph nodes and partly to a gland of the deep cervical group situated on the internal jugular vein at the level of the cricoid cartilage.

label: mandibular lymph node
definition: The mandibular lymph node is a lymph node found near the jaw.

label: common iliac lymph node
definition: The external iliac lymph nodes, from eight to ten in number, lie along the external iliac vessels. They are arranged in three groups, one on the lateral, another on the medial, and a third on the anterior aspect of the vessels; the third group is, however, sometimes absent. Their principal afferents are derived from the inguinal lymph nodes, the deep lymphatics of the abdominal wall below the umbilicus and of the adductor region of the thigh, and the lymphatics from the glans penis vel clitoridis, the membranous urethra, the prostate, the fundus of the urinary bladder, the cervix uteri, and upper part of the vagina.

label: internal iliac lymph node
definition: The internal iliac lymph nodes (or hypogastric) surround the internal iliac artery and its branches (the hypogastric vessels), and receive the lymphatics corresponding to the distribution of the branches of it, i. e. , they receive lymphatics from all the pelvic viscera, from the deeper parts of the perineum, including the membranous and cavernous portions of the urethra, and from the buttock and back of the thigh. It does not receive lymph from the ovary, testis, or superior half of the rectum; the gonads drain to the paraaortic lymph nodes, while the superior half of the rectum drains to the pararectal lymph nodes.

label: infraclavicular lymph node
definition: A lymph node located in the area below the clavicle.

label: anterior auricular lymph node
definition: The preauricular deep parotid lymph nodes (anterior auricular glands or preauricular glands), from one to three in number, lie immediately in front of the tragus. Their afferents drain the lateral surface of the auricula and the skin of the adjacent part of the temporal region; their efferents pass to the superior deep cervical glands.

label: infra-auricular lymph node
definition: The infra-auricular deep parotid lymph nodes are a group of lymph nodes found underneath the ear.

label: sciatic lymph node
definition: A lymph node that is medial to the gluteus superficialis m., caudal to gluteus medius m. and sciatic nerve lymph node

label: anatomical projection
definition: A projection or outgrowth of tissue from a larger body or organ.

label: zone of stomach
definition: A division of the stomach. The stomach can be divided based on mucosal histology (glandular epithelium and gastric glands) and the relative position and type of gastric gland.

label: gas excreted from digestive tract
definition: Any excreted gas that is produced by the digestive tract.

label: deep intraparotid lymph node
definition: The intraglandular deep parotid lymph nodes are a group of lymph nodes found inside the parotid gland.

label: subsegmental lymph node
definition: The lymph nodes around the subsegmental bronchi.

label: angle unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the figure or space formed by the junction of two lines or planes.

label: base unit
definition: A unit which is one of a particular measure to which all measures of that type can be related.

label: concentration unit
definition: A unit which represents a standard measurement of how much of a given substance there is mixed with another substance.

label: conduction unit
definition: A unit which represents a standard measurement of the transmission of an entity through a medium.

label: density unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the influence exerted by some mass.

label: dimensionless unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of physical quantity consisting of only a numerical number without any units.

label: electric potential difference unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the work done per unit charge as a charge is moved between two points in an electric field.

label: length unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the distance between two points.

label: speed/velocity unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the rate of movement. Speed is measured in the same physical units of measurement as velocity, but does not contain the element of direction that velocity has. Speed is thus the magnitude component of velocity.

label: substance unit
definition: A unit which is a standardised quantity of an element or compound with uniform composition.

label: temperature unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the average kinetic energy of the particles in a sample of matter.

label: time unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the dimension in which events occur in sequence.

label: turbidity unit
definition: A unit used to indicate the clarity of water or other solutions or suspensions, as measured by the ability of the solution or suspension to scatter light of a defined wavelength range.

label: volume unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the amount of space occupied by any substance, whether solid, liquid, or gas.

label: angstrom
definition: A length unit which is equal to 10 [-10] m.

label: centiMorgan
definition: A unit used to express distances on a genetic map. In genetic mapping, distances between markers are determined by measuring the rate of meoitic recombination between them, which increases proportionately with the distance separating them. A cM is defined as the length of an interval in which there is a 1% probability of recombination. On the average, 1 cM is roughly equivalent to 1 megabase (Mb) of DNA, although this can vary widely due to hot and cold spots of recombination.

label: centiRay
definition: A unit of genetic map distance defined corresponding to an interval in which there is a 1% probability of X-irradiation induced breakage. To be completely specified, the unit must be qualified by the radiation in dosage in rads (e.g. cR8000), because this determines the actual breakage probability.

label: centimeter
definition: A length unit which is equal to one hundredth of a meter or 10^[-2] m.

label: meter
definition: A length unit which is equal to the length of the path traveled by light in vacuum during a time interval of 1/299 792 458 of a second.

label: micrometer
definition: A length unit which is equal to one millionth of a meter or 10^[-6] m.

label: millimeter
definition: A length unit which is equal to one thousandth of a meter or 10^[-3] m.

label: nanometer
definition: A length unit which is equal to one thousandth of one millionth of a meter or 10^[-9] m.

label: picometer
definition: A length unit which is equal to 10^[-12] m.

label: century
definition: A time unit which is equal to 100 years.

label: day
definition: A time unit which is equal to 24 hours.

label: half life
definition: A time unit which represents the period over which the activity or concentration of a specified chemical or element falls to half its original activity or concentration.

label: hour
definition: A time unit which is equal to 3600 seconds or 60 minutes.

label: microsecond
definition: A time unit which is equal to one millionth of a second or 10^[-6] s.

label: millisecond
definition: A time unit which is equal to one thousandth of a second or 10^[-3] s.

label: minute
definition: A time unit which is equal to 60 seconds.

label: month
definition: A time unit which is approximately equal to the length of time of one of cycle of the moon's phases which in science is taken to be equal to 30 days.

label: nanosecond
definition: A time unit which is equal to one thousandth of one millionth of a second or 10^[-9] s.

label: picosecond
definition: A time unit which is equal to 10^[-12] s.

label: second
definition: A time unit which is equal to the duration of 9 192 631 770 periods of the radiation corresponding to the transition between the two hyperfine levels of the ground state of the caesium 133 atom.

label: week
definition: A time unit which is equal to 7 days.

label: year
definition: A time unit which is equal to 12 months which is science is taken to be equal to 365.25 days.

label: degree Celsius
definition: A temperature unit which is equal to one kelvin degree. However, they have their zeros at different points. The centigrade scale has its zero at 273.15 K.

label: degree Fahrenheit
definition: A temperature unit which is equal to 5/9ths of a kelvin. Negative 40 degrees Fahrenheit is equal to negative 40 degrees Celsius.

label: kelvin
definition: A thermodynamic temperature unit which is equal to the fraction 1/273.16 of the thermodynamic temperature of the triple point of water.

label: Ounce
definition: The traditional unit of mass. The avoirdupois ounce is equal to 1/16 pound, or 28.349 5 grams, or 0.911 457 troy ounce.

label: Pound
definition: The traditional unit of mass. By international agreement, one avoirdupois pound is equal to exactly 0.453 592 37 kilogram, 16 ounces, or 1.215 28 troy pounds.

label: micromole
definition: A substance unit equal to a millionth of a mol or 10^[-6] mol.

label: colony forming unit per volume
definition: A concentration unit which a measure of viable bacterial numbers in a given volume.

label: mass percentage
definition: A dimensionless concentration unit which denotes the mass of a substance in a mixture as a percentage of the mass of the entire mixture.

label: mass volume percentage
definition: A dimensionless concentration unit which denotes the mass of the substance in a mixture as a percentage of the volume of the entire mixture.

label: mole fraction
definition: A concentration unit which denotes the number of moles of solute as a proportion of the total number of moles in a solution.

label: pH
definition: A dimensionless concentration notation which denotes the acidity of a solution in terms of activity of hydrogen ions (H+).

label: volume per unit volume
definition: A dimensionless concentration unit which denotes the given volume of the solute in the total volume of the resulting solution.

label: gram per cubic centimeter
definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in grams divided by the volume in cubic centimeters.

label: gram per deciliter
definition: A mass density unit which is equal to mass of an object in grams divided by the volume in deciliters.

label: gram per liter
definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in grams divided by the volume in liters.

label: gram per milliliter
definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in grams divided by the volume in milliliter.

label: kilogram per cubic meter
definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in kilograms divided by the volume in cubic meters.

label: kilogram per liter
definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in kilograms divided by the volume in liters.

label: microgram per liter
definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in micrograms divided by the volume in liters.

label: microgram per milliliter
definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in micrograms divided by the volume in millliters.

label: milligram per liter
definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in milligrams divided by the volume in liters.

label: milligram per milliliter
definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in milligrams divided by the volume in milliliters.

label: nanogram per milliliter
definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in nanograms divided by the volume in milliliters.

label: cubic centimeter per mole
definition: A molar volume unit which is equal to 1 cubic centimeter occupied by one mole of a substance in the form of a solid, liquid, or gas.

label: cubic meter per mole
definition: A molar volume unit which is equal to 1 cubic meter occupied by one mole of a substance in the form of a solid, liquid, or gas.

label: cubic meter per kilogram
definition: A specific volume unit which is equal to one cubic meter volume occupied by one kilogram of a particular substance.

label: liter per kilogram
definition: A specific volume unit which is equal to one liter volume occupied by one kilogram of a particular substance.

label: microliter per kilogram
definition: A specific volume unit which is equal to one millionth of a liter per kilogram or 10^[-6] l/kg.

label: milliliter per kilogram
definition: A specific volume unit which is equal to a thousandth of a liter per kilogram or 10^[-3] l/kg.

label: meter per second
definition: A speed/velocity unit which is equal to the speed of an object traveling 1 meter distance in one second.

label: cubic centimeter
definition: A volume unit which is equal to one millionth of a cubic meter or 10^[-9] m^[3], or to 1 ml.

label: cubic decimeter
definition: A volume unit which is equal to one thousand of a cubic meter or 10^[-3] m^[3], or to 1 L.

label: cubic meter
definition: A volume unit which is equal to the volume of a cube with edges one meter in length. One cubic meter equals to 1000 liters.

label: deciliter
definition: A volume unit which is equal to one tenth of a liter or 10^[-1] L.

label: femtoliter
definition: A volume unit which is equal to 10^[-15] L.

label: liter
definition: A volume unit which is equal to one thousandth of a cubic meter or 10^[-3] m^[3], or to 1 decimeter.

label: microliter
definition: A volume unit which is equal to one millionth of a liter or 10^[-6] L.

label: milliliter
definition: A volume unit which is equal to one thousandth of a liter or 10^[-3] L, or to 1 cubic centimeter.

label: molar volume unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the volume of a homogeneous substance containing 6.02 x 1023 atoms or molecules.

label: nanoliter
definition: A volume unit which is equal to one thousandth of one millionth of a liter or 10^[-9] L.

label: picoliter
definition: A volume unit which is equal to 10^[-12] L.

label: specific volume unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the volume of a given mass of substance (the reciprocal of density).

label: plane angle unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the angle formed by two straight lines in the same plane.

label: degree
definition: A plane angle unit which is equal to 1/360 of a full rotation or 1.7453310^[-2] rad.

label: radian
definition: A plane angle unit which is equal to the angle subtended at the center of a circle by an arc equal in length to the radius of the circle, approximately 57 degrees 17 minutes and 44.6 seconds.

label: mass density unit
definition: A density unit which is a standard measure of the mass of a substance in a given volume.

label: count unit
definition: A dimensionless unit which denotes a simple count of things.

label: ratio
definition: A dimensionless unit which denotes an amount or magnitude of one quantity relative to another.

label: confluence percentage
definition: A dimensionless percent unit which denotes the density of an attached or monolayer culture (e.g., cell culture).

label: purity percentage
definition: A dimensionless percent unit which denotes the homogeneity of a biomaterial.

label: volume percentage
definition: A dimensionless concentration unit which denotes the volume of the solute in mL per 100 mL of the resulting solution.

label: base pair
definition: A count unit which contains one nucleotide.

label: gigabasepair
definition: A unit equal to one billion base pairs.

label: kilobasepair
definition: A unit equal to one thousand base pairs.

label: megabasepair
definition: A unit equal to one million base pairs

label: fraction
definition: A dimensionless ratio unit which relates the part (the numerator) to the whole (the denominator).

label: percent
definition: A dimensionless ratio unit which denotes numbers as fractions of 100.

label: colony forming unit per milliliter
definition: A colony forming unit which a measure of viable bacterial numbers in one milliliter.

label: colony forming unit per 100 millilitre
definition: A colony forming unit count which is a ratio of viable bacterial numbers in 100 milliliters of liquid.

label: millivolt
definition: An electric potential difference unit which is equal to one thousandth of a volt or 10^[-3] V.

label: electrical conduction unit
definition: A unit which represents a standard measurement of the movement of electrically charged particles through a transmission medium (electrical conductor).

label: siemens
definition: An electrical conduction unit which is equal to A/V.

label: formazin nephelometric unit
definition: 1000 formazin turbidity units (FNU) on the empirical formazin turbidity scale represents reflectance of insol. reaction products of 0.0725 g hydrazine sulfate with 0.7250 g hexamethylenetetramine diluted to 1 L.

label: African American/Afro-Caribbean
definition: People who defined themselves as American with an admixture of west african, amerindian and european

label: Hispanic/Latin American
definition: An admixed population

label: host profile or identifers
definition: The host profile or identifiers text is the "identification or description of the specific individual from which this sample was obtained".

label: standard operating procedure
definition: A standard operating procedure is a specification approved for use in specific environments.

label: subject description
definition: A subject description is a field containing additional information about an organism (related to an investigation, study and/or specimen) that is not included in other defined vocabulary fields.

label: Country
definition: A collective generic term that refers here to a wide variety of dependencies, areas of special sovereignty, uninhabited islands, and other entities in addition to the traditional countries or independent states.

label: centre point
definition: A centre point is a point used in the description of an n-dimentional entity from which other (given) aspects of the entity are most efficienty described. A point of symmetry.  The entity must have only one such point.

label: origin
definition: In mathematics, the origin of a Euclidean space is a special point, usually denoted by the letter O, used as a fixed point of reference for the geometry of the surrounding space.  In physical problems, the choice of origin is often arbitrary, meaning any choice of origin will ultimately give the same answer. This allows one to pick an origin point that makes the mathematics as simple as possible, often by taking advantage of some kind of geometric symmetry.

label: line segment
definition: A line segment is a line and a part of a curve that is (inclusively) bounded by two terminal points.

label: polygon edge
definition: A polygon edge is a line segment joining two polygon vertices.

label: points in 2 dimensions
definition: A set of points that exist in a 2-dimensional plane. (This plane may be a cross-section of points defined in n > 2 dimensions).

label: line
definition: A line is curve that extends in a single dimension (e.g. straight line; exhibits no curvature), and is composed of at least two fully connected points.

label: Canadian National Microbiology Laboratory (NML) ID
definition: in-house tracking ID number

label: Alive
definition: Showing characteristics of life; displaying signs of life.

label: age at death
definition: The age at which death occurs.

label: age at menarche
definition: The age of onset of (human) menarche, the beginning of the first menstrual cycle in an individual

label: age at menopause
definition: The age of onset of (human) menopause, the beginning of the first menstrual cycle in an individual

label: age at onset
definition: The age at which some process, or disease started in a human individual.

label: gestational age
definition: The age of the conceptus, beginning from the time of FERTILIZATION. In clinical obstetrics, the gestational age is often estimated as the time from the last day of the last MENSTRUATION which is about 2 weeks before OVULATION and fertilization.

label: age at assessment
definition: The age of an individual at the time an assessment takes place

label: age at voice drop
definition: The age of onset of (human) voice drop, the deepening of the voice of adolescents as they reach puberty

label: adult
definition: A maturity quality inhering in an individual by virtue of the individual having attained sexual maturity and full growth

label: embryo stage
definition: A life cycle stage that starts with fertilization and ends with the fully formed embryo.

label: progression free survival
definition: Progression free survival is a measurement from a defined time point e.g. diagnosis and indicates that the disease did not progress i.e. tumours did not increase in size and new incidences did not occur. PFS is usually used in analyzing results of treatment for advanced disease.

label: delay from symptoms to treatment
definition: The duration between the appearance of symptoms of a disease and the start of a treatment.

label: duration of treatment course
definition: A duration that measures the temporal interval occupied by a treatment course.

label: infectious period duration
definition: A duration of the parts of an infection during which the host bears an infectious disposition in a population of hosts.

label: latent period duration
definition: A duration of the time interval between the host acquiring an infection and the host bearing a contagiousness disposition during the same disease course within a population of hosts.

label: time delay of treatment detection
definition: The duration from the time an individual receives a treatment until the time a system designed to detect that the treatment occurred detects it in a population

label: time delay to case detection
definition: The duration from the time an organism satisfies a case definition until a process or system detects the organism as satisfying that case definition

label: disease free survival
definition: A temporal measurement of the period after successful treatment in which there is no appearance of the symptoms or effects of the disease.

label: metastasis free survival
definition: The percentage of subjects in a study who have survived without cancer spread for a defined period of time. Usually reported as time since diagnosis or treatment. Can be reported for an individual or a study population.

label: biological replicate
definition: A biological replicate is a replicate role that consists of independent biological replicates made from different individual biosamples.

label: technical replicate
definition: A technical replicate is a replicate role where the same BioSample is use e.g. the same pool of RNA used to assess technical (as opposed to biological) variation within an experiment.

label: event free survival time
definition: Is the survival of a subject (or group of subjects) measured from the date of diagnosis until  locoregional or systemic recurrence,  second malignancy, or death from any cause or disease progression or relapse, institution of new unplanned anticancer treatment, or death from any cause.

label: overall survival
definition: A measurement of the survival rate for a group of individuals suffering from a disease.

label: age
definition: A temporal measurement of the time period elapsed since an identifiable point in the life cycle of an organism. If a developmental stage is specified, the identifiable point would be the beginning of that stage. Otherwise the identifiable point must be specified such as planting (e.g. 3 days post planting).

label: duration
definition: A temporal measurement of the time between two specified points.

label: timepoint
definition: Time point at which a sample or observation is made or taken from a biomaterial as measured from some reference point.

label: clinical temporal measurement
definition: A temporal measurement related to disease progression

label: initial time point
definition: The first time point measured at the start of some process.

label: date of birth
definition: The point in time at which an individual was born.

label: African
definition: Denotes a person with African ancestral origins who self identifies, or is identified, as African. The concept does not refer to those of other ancestry, for example, European and South Asian. In practice, the term mainly refers to people originated from forty-eight sub-Saharan Africa nations; and excudes individuals from North Africa countries, e.g. such as Algeria, Morocco, Egypt, Tunisia with Arab and Berber ethnicity.

label: African American
definition: A term used in the United States to categorize a population group comprised of persons having origins in any of the black racial groups of Africa. Includes population subgroups (e.g., Kenyan, Nigerian, Haitian). The concept refers also to individuals who classify themselves as described.

label: Asian
definition: Denotes a person having origins in any of the original peoples of the Far East, Southeast Asia, or the Indian subcontinent, including Cambodia, China, India, Japan, Korea, Malaysia, Mongolia, Pakistan, the Philippine Islands, Thailand, and Vietnam.

label: Asian Indian
definition: In North America the term is used to distinguish a person having origins in the original peoples of the Indian sub-continent from Native Americans.

label: Asian/Pacific Islander
definition: Denotes a person having origins in any of the original peoples of Hawaii, Guam, Samoa, or other Pacific Islands. The term covers particularly people who identify themselves as part-Hawaiian, Native Hawaiian, Guamanian or Chamorro, Carolinian, Samoan, Chuukese (Trukese), Fijian, Kosraean, Melanesian, Micronesian, Northern Mariana Islander, Palauan, Papua New Guinean, Pohnpeian, Polynesian, Solomon Islander, Tahitian, Tokelauan, Tongan, Yapese, or Pacific Islander, not specified.

label: Caucasian
definition: Denotes person with European, Middle Eastern, or North African ancestral origin who identifies, or is identified, as White.

label: Chinese
definition: Denotes the inhabitants of China, a person from there, or their descendants elsewhere.

label: Hawaiian
definition: Denotes a person having origins in any of the original peoples of Hawaii, a person from there, or their descendants elsewhere.

label: Hispanic
definition: A person of Mexican, Puerto Rican, Cuban, Central or South American or other Spanish culture or origin, regardless of race. An arbitrary ethnic classification.

label: Iranian
definition: Denotes the inhabitants of Iran, a person from there, or their descendants elsewhere.

label: Irish
definition: Denotes the inhabitants of Ireland, a person from there, or their descendants elsewhere.

label: Latino
definition: A person of Mexican, Puerto Rican, Cuban, Central or South American or other Spanish culture or origin, regardless of race. An arbitrary ethnic classification.

label: Northern and Western European
definition: Population of northern and western European ancestry.

label: Filipino
definition: Denotes the inhabitants of the Philippine Islands, a person from there, or their descendants elsewhere.

label: Japanese
definition: Denotes the inhabitants of Japan, a person from there, or their descendants elsewhere.

label: Korean
definition: Denotes the inhabitants of Korea, a person from there, or their descendants elsewhere.

label: Han Chinese
definition: Han Chinese are an ethnic group native to East Asia. Han Chinese constitute about 92% of the population of the People's Republic of China (mainland China)

label: body mass index
definition: An indicator of body density as determined by the relationship ofÂ BODY WEIGHT to BODY HEIGHT. BMI=weight (kg)/height squared (m2). BMI correlates with body fat (ADIPOSE TISSUE). Their relationship varies with age and gender. For adults, BMI falls into these categories: below 18.5 (underweight); 18.5-24.9 (normal); 25.0-29.9 (overweight); 30.0 and above (obese). (National Center for Health Statistics, Centers for Disease Control and Prevention)

label: Yoruba
definition: The Yoruba people are one of the largest ethnic groups in West Africa.

label: distant metastasis free survival
definition: Is a temporal measure from a defined start point e.g. diagnosis, or treatment of the period to appearance of a distant metastasis. A distant metastasis refers to cancer that has spread from the original (primary) tumor to distant organs or distant lymph nodes. Also known as distant cancer.

label: age of onset
definition: The age group in which disease manifestations appear.

label: last follow up
definition: The date or time of the last check of a patient by a medical professional.

label: survival time
definition: Time of survival is an information entity which is about the length of time a material entity has survived after some adverse event, such as infection from a disease.

label: age at diagnosis
definition: The age, measured from some defined time point e.g. birth at which a subject (e.g. a human patient) is diagnosed with some disease e.g. breast cancer.

label: alive at endpoint
definition: A clinical temporal measurement indicating that the subject is alive at the end of the clinical investigation.

label: disease progression measurement
definition: quantification of some aspect of disease progression such as speed or symptom variability. Disease progression can be quantified in a number of ways, for example as a correlated measure of progression scores from different symptom areas

label: disease recurrence
definition: The recurrence of a disease after treatment

label: isolation date (deprecated)
definition: date the strain was isolated

label: GSCID-BRC data item (deprecated)
definition: A GSCID/BRC data item is a field in one of the GSCID/BRC Project and Sample Application Standard subsets.

label: INSDC MDM standard (deprecated)
definition: The INDISC consortium "Minimum data for Matching" standard aims to define a format to capture reads and minimum metadata.  It is developed by the "Repository and storage of sequence and meta-data" workgroup 2.  It is used in the Global Microbial Identifier platform.

label: MIxS data item (deprecated)
definition: a MixS data item is a term or field defined in the Genomic Standards Consortium MIxS standard.

label: NCBI BioProject ID (deprecated)
definition: This is a subset of OBI investigation identifier.  It pertains only to NCBI Biosample projects

label: NCBI BioProject data item (deprecated)
definition: An NCBI BioProject data item is a datum within the NCBI BioProject standard collection

label: NCBI BioProject model (deprecated)
definition: The NCBI BioProject model includes all datums associated with the current NCBI BioProject specification.

label: NCBI antibiogram data item (deprecated)
definition: An NCBI antibiogram data item is an antimicrobial susceptibility and resistance datum related to drug resistant pathogens. This information is provided within an antibiogram table on BioSample records.

label: US postal code (deprecated)
definition: A "USA zip code" is a five digit (Zone Improvement Plan) or 9 digit postal code pertaining to a region of the United States of America. The optional trailing 4 digits of a 9 digit zip code provide greater granularity of delivery target.

label: antibiotic intermediate resistance (I) (deprecated)
definition: Intermediate resistance indicates that an isolate is observed to offer an intermediate level of resistance to a given antibiotic.

label: antibiotic nonsensitive (high resistance) (deprecated)
definition: non-susceptible indicates that an isolate is observed to offer complete resistance to a given antibiotic.

label: antibiotic resistant (R) (deprecated)
definition: Resistant indicates that an isolate is observed to offer a greater than intermediate level of resistance to a given antibiotic.

label: antibiotic sensitive (S) (deprecated)
definition: Susceptible indicates that an isolate is observed to offer a detectable but less than intermediate level of resistance to a given antibiotic.

label: antimicrobial resistance phenotype (deprecated)
definition: The resistance phenotype of an isolate represents the interpretation of an MIC value with regard to some breakpoint threshold e.g. resistant (R), sensitive (S), intermediate (I), wild type (WT), or non-wild type (NWT)

label: antimicrobial resistance phenotype - epidemiological cut-off values
antimicrobial resistance testing method (deprecated)
definition: The type of assay used to determine the minimum inhibitory concentration.

label: cafeteria (deprecated)
definition: A cafeteria is a type of food service location in which there is little or no waiting staff table service, whether a restaurant or within an institution such as a large office building or school.

label: categorical tree specification (deprecated)
definition: A categorical tree specification datum is a categorical value specification which takes its value from the ontology URI identifier of any one of its subclass items; these may be organized in a hierarchy.

label: delicatessen (deprecated)
definition: A delicatessen or deli is a retail establishment that sells a selection of unusual or foreign prepared foods.

label: draft GenEpiO BioProject standard (deprecated)
definition: This is an organizational category for grouping parameters relevant to biomedical research projects.

label: draft GenEpiO BioSample standard (deprecated)
definition: This is an organizational category for grouping parameters relevant to a biomedical sample.

label: fluid - aspirate (deprecated)
definition: [WHICH DEFINITION?] See http://medical-dictionary.thefreedictionary.com/aspirate

label: food kiosk (deprecated)
definition: A food kiosk is a kiosk (a booth with an open window on one side) that sells food.

label: grocery store (deprecated)
definition: A grocery store is a retail store that primarily sells food.

label: laboratory sequencing datum (deprecated)
definition: A laboratory sequencing datum is a datum related to the sequencing assay process applied to an isolate.

label: long term care facility (deprecated)
definition: A long term care facility provides a type of residential care. It is a place of residence for people who require continual nursing care and have significant difficulty coping with the required activities of daily living.

label: market (obsolete)
definition: A market, or marketplace, is a location where people regularly gather for the purchase and sale of provisions, livestock, and other goods

label: obsolete air temperature
definition: A temperature that inheres in some portion of air.

label: ordinal variable (deprecated)
definition: An ordinal variable is a categorical variable whose values have sequential order, but no distance metric between them.

label: restaurant (deprecated)
definition: A restaurant or an eatery, is a business which prepares and serves food and drinks to customers in exchange for money.

label: sensitive - dose dependent (deprecated)
definition: Susceptible - dose dependent indicates that an isolate is observed to offer resistance to a given antibiotic when a sufficient dose is given.

label: specialty/ethnic store (deprecated)
definition: A specialty/ethnic food store is a store specializing in a particular variety of food or food of cultural / regional origin.

label: specimen from subject datum (deprecated)
definition: An organism isolate datum is any datum pertaining to an isolate organism

label: specimen source environmental material (deprecated)
definition: The environmental material level refers to the material that was displaced by the sample, or material in which a sample was embedded, prior to the sampling event. Environmental material terms are generally mass nouns. Examples include: air, soil, or water. EnvO (v 2013-06-14) terms can be found via the link: www.environmentontology.org/Browse-EnvO

label: specimen source material category (deprecated)
definition: This is the scientific role or category that the subject organism or material has with respect to an investigation.

label: subject species (deprecated)
definition: The natural (as opposed to laboratory) full scientific taxonomic name of a subject related to a given investigation, study and/or specimen.

label: take out restaurant (deprecated)
definition: A restaurant providing prepared meals or other food items that the purchaser intends to eat elsewhere

label: awaiting ontology review/placement
definition: This class is a temporary holding bin for items that need a class hierarchy home, definition, and/or subclass items.

label: Street Address
definition: The street name and building number where a person or organization can be found.

label: Father
definition: A male parent.

label: Mother
definition: A female parent.
